(13, 1, 44, 2, 38, 1, null, 99, null, '<p>&ldquo;the gift of the holy spirit.&rdquo; When God gives His nature to people so they can be empowered with spirit power, that nature, called &ldquo;the holy spirit,&rdquo; is a gift to the person who receives it. The Bible specifically calls it &ldquo;the gift of holy spirit&rdquo; (Acts 2:38; 10:45). God is not a gift to people, so when the Bible speaks of &ldquo;the gift of holy spirit,&rdquo; it is not speaking of God or of a third &ldquo;Person&rdquo; in the Trinity.</p>'),
