(14, 1, 45, 1, 4, 0, null, 99, '2022-06-14 18:39:31', '<p>See comms on the argument for ἐν δυνάμει modifying υἱοῦ θεοῦ or ὁρισθεντος.</p> <p>Since the point in time from which the sonship dates is given, here ὁρίζω must mean install, even though elsewhere it means determined, declared, decreed. The pre-Pauline formula (which probably lacked the ἐν δυνάμει of v. 4) states &ldquo;that Jesus, by his earthly origins a descendant of David, was the earthly messiah, whom God declared the Son of God in connection with his resurrection from the dead, and thus enthroned him as messianic king&rdquo; (EDNT)</p>'),
(14, 1, 45, 1, 7, 0, null, 99, '2022-05-24 18:50:24', '<p>κλητοὶ Ἰησοῦ Χριστοῦ &ndash; &ldquo;called (by God) to belong to Jesus Christ&rdquo;; a genitive of possession. See Longnecker [NIGTC], Murray [NICNT].</p>'),
(14, 1, 45, 1, 16, 1, null, 99, '2022-04-03 15:20:39', null),
(14, 1, 45, 2, 12, 0, null, 99, '2022-08-12 14:19:51', '<p>This is the first occurrence of law (nomos) in Romans. Exactly what Paul means by the term has been the subject of much scholarly debate. According to J. A. Fitzmyer (Romans [AB], 131-35; 305-6) there are at least four different senses: (1) figurative, as a &ldquo;principle&rdquo;; (2) generic, meaning &ldquo;a law&rdquo;; (3) as a reference to the OT or some part of the OT; and (4) as a reference to the Mosaic law. This last usage constitutes the majority of Paul&rsquo;s references to &ldquo;law&rdquo; in Romans. (NET note)</p>'),
(14, 1, 45, 2, 16, 0, null, 99, '2022-08-12 19:56:51', '<p>What is meant by μου &lsquo;my&rsquo; in the phrase τὸ εὐαγγέλιόν μου &lsquo;my gospel&rsquo;? Paul is not referring to some form of teaching particularly characteristic of himself, but rather to the gospel which is common to all Christians, and which God entrusted to Paul to proclaim [ICC2, NICNT]. He called it &lsquo;my gospel&rsquo; because he loved the gospel that had been conveyed to him by the Lord [NTC]. It is the gospel Paul was commissioned to deliver [Ho], and was given to him by revelation from Jesus Christ [NAC]. By this phrase Paul reminds us that the gospel was committed to him, that he was separated unto it and he identified with it [Mu]. This phrase serves as a reminder that preaching the gospel to the Gentiles is Paul&rsquo;s particular call [Rom 1&ndash;8, p. 172] [BECNT]. Paul is not referring to something particular in his expounding the gospel, but rather that he knows it, espouses it wholeheartedly, and has made it his own [Mor]. It means the gospel as he habitually taught it [ICC1], the gospel that he preached [SSA], his personal way of proclaiming it [AB]. (Abernathy, SILESS)</p>'),
(14, 1, 45, 3, 15, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-21 19:34:32', '<p>ὀξεῖς &ndash; means &ldquo;to have a keen edge&rdquo; and hence &ldquo;sharp,&rdquo; but then more idiomatically it connotes something &ldquo;quick&rdquo; or &ldquo;swift&rdquo;</p>'),
(14, 1, 45, 3, 19, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-21 19:52:05', '<p>ἐν τῷ νόμῳ &ndash; &ldquo;in (the realm of) the law&rdquo; or &ldquo;[with]in the confines of the law,&rdquo; which conceptually means &ldquo;under the law&rdquo; &ndash; cf. 2:12</p>'),
