(14, 1, 54, 6, 1, 0, null, 99, '2022-04-26 18:25:40', '<p>&ldquo;Yoke of slavery&rdquo; is a term found in classical Greek writers.787 Jesus used &ldquo;yoke&rdquo; as a metaphor for being his disciple.788 Slavery was onerous and undesirable, but it was universal across the Roman Empire and indeed across most civilizations until fairly recent times. (Yarborough, PNT)</p>'),
(14, 1, 54, 6, 3, 1, null, 99, '2022-11-22 17:18:42', '<p>Compare κατ&rsquo; εὐσέβειαν in Tit 1:1</p> <p>&ldquo;κατά, &ldquo;according to,&rdquo; could indicate purpose or goal: the goal of the teaching is godliness (cf. BAGD 406&ndash;7). It could also describe correspondence or conformity: the teaching that conforms to godliness (cf. BAGD 407; M. J. Harris, NIDNTT 3:1200&ndash;1201).&rdquo; (Mounce, WBC)</p>'),
