(15, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Not a chapter heading of the verses that follow! That which is not the earth is the heavens at this point.', 99, '2022-10-14 14:37:05', '<p>See my notes on verse 2. In verse 2, the earth that would have not been created yet if verse 1 is a chapter heading, &ldquo;was&rdquo; and had adjectives describing it. It exists here in verse 2 before God said &ldquo;Let there be light.&rdquo;</p>'),
(15, 0, 1, 1, 2, 0, 'Spirit of God &ndash; God&rsquo;s spirit &ndash; emphasizing God Himself taking action.', 99, '2022-09-20 10:38:31', '<p><strong>Spirit of God</strong> &ndash; [My best understanding] God is a spirit-being. Referring to his spirit can be equal to us referring to our souls. The soul of Tim is Tim&rsquo;s self. &ldquo;Oh my soul, why are you sad?&rdquo; is me talking to myself. I think that by God saying it this way: &ldquo;the spirit of God&rdquo;, God was saying that he personally did this, not by commanding other beings to do it. God can and does take credit for the things he commands other spirit-beings to actually do, which is the right of a ruler. But I think this is making it clear that God Himself was going into action to straighten out the mess that other created spirit-beings had made of his creation. I don&rsquo;t think that this necessarily means that no part of the 6 days was delegated to his loyal spirit-beings, but that God was stepping in to a situation that He had largely left in the hands of his spirit-being sons of God.</p> <p>We know from Ephesians 1 that God&rsquo;s plan included a man, later named Jesus, who would eventually unite all families on earth and in heaven under one head, himself (and that the Body of Christ of this administration, &ldquo;Christians,&rdquo; were also in this plan). God had this plan in mind before &ldquo;the foundation of the earth&rdquo;. I think that phrase means that before the initial creation, God planned that a particular man, whom he would conceive in a woman, and who would be perfected through enduring sufferings, would eventually pay the price for all of humanity&rsquo;s sins (which sins had an astronomically high probability of happening due to free will which He was going to give spirit-beings and mankind). God would raise that man from the dead, and raise him up into the heavens to sit at His right hand over all of His creation.</p> <p>An integral part of God&rsquo;s plan, before mankind could be created, was to create various families of spirit-beings, whose normal abode is in heaven, and whose purpose in their service to God was to take care of the unseen/spiritual foundations of God&rsquo;s creation (the heavens), to maintain it in a stable state under His rulership, under His direction, in order for God&rsquo;s purposes to come to pass, including humans. John S does a great job of laying out how it is God&rsquo;s way to delegate responsibility to other beings and that He does not micro-manage everything they do. That is not love. How much the spirit-beings knew of this plan is not revealed here. Certainly more was revealed in the revelation of the sacred secret.</p> <p>Verse 2 shows how terribly unsucessful they were at their responsibilities (formless, empty, and with darkness...). Failing this badly must have intention to it. [Now, document that.] They were not doing it well enough to even keep earth capable of having the living things that God wanted to live on it, including humans. God&rsquo;s plans were in jeopardy. He had to step in in a big way to save His plans. God Himself took action, and John S&rsquo; has comments on this as well.</p> <p>[Hypothesis:]There are a lot of physical constants that physicists/comologists know exist, but they don&rsquo;t know why they work, they just do. They also know that if these were to change, even the slightest, then huge changes would happen to the universe. There are also things in &ldquo;space&rdquo; that they know about which could annihilate earth, but that there are a lot of fortunate happenstances that protect the earth. It can easily be seen that spirit-beings who are designed to care for the nest that the earth rests in (the heavens), could also affect changes that were not so good for the earth.</p> <p>Though &ldquo;formless&rdquo; is good, it could use other words like &ldquo;wasted&rdquo; or &ldquo;purposeless&rdquo;, or even including both tohu and bohu: &ldquo;an empty purposeless waste&rdquo;. I feel that &ldquo;formless&rdquo; gives the idea of etherial, or like a nebula, but it could also be be like a lot of mud, and water sliding around too which seems to fit the idea of darkness on the face of the deep and a lack of dry land. However, from what Arthur Custance says, the definitions seem to point at it being compared to a wilderness, or waste area, that cannot support life. Whether it became this way, or it is simply saying that at the time directly before God hovered over it, THE EARTH WAS (or BECAME...). Verse 1 is not a chapter heading because the earth exists and it is referred to as God&rsquo;s creation, so God had to have created it before verse 2, hence verse 1. This thing called earth not only was, but it has adjectives. It exists before God said: &ldquo;Let there be light.&rdquo;</p>'),
(15, 0, 1, 1, 3, 0, 'God is talking so that his inner Divine Council of Spirit-beings hear - see vs. 26.', 99, '2023-02-11 15:10:45', '<p>The way that God&rsquo;s spirit, that is God Himself, took action is by instructing his inner council of spirit-beings. It does not say here that God &ldquo;created&rdquo; light. Here, He told them to let it be. Somehow, spirit-beings were holding this light back. God said to let there be light. Now whether He acted to let it be or His spirit-beings acted to let it be at his command, or both, it does not say. More important is what this light is in comparison to Day 4 when the Sun, Moon, and stars were set in the heavens. This could be the usage of light as that which exposes the deeds, the works of those that it shines on, which in this case would have been the deeds of spirit-beings who were causing the conditions mentioned in verse 2. His next action was to separate the light from the darkness, which in this context means the critique of the works that were good from those which were evil, thus making a knowledge of good and evil within the spirit-realm.</p>'),
(15, 0, 1, 1, 6, 0, 'Removes some of the water from off the earth itself and puts it beyond the heaven that now has the stars and planets in it.', 99, '2023-02-11 02:43:32', '<p>This lends to the idea that the &ldquo;formlessness&rdquo; of the earth before day 1 was due to an overabundance of water on land of the earth. Probably not as bad as during Noah&rsquo;s flood but still a lot of muddiness all over the earth. Again God simply said to his inner-council of spirit-beings to let there be an expanse, but in this case it also adds that God did that exact thing in the verse following.</p>'),
(15, 0, 1, 1, 7, 0, 'Some water separated from the waters below the expanse called &ldquo;heaven&rdquo;. &ldquo;Expanse&rdquo; can be &ldquo;firmament&rdquo; too, or both &ldquo;firm expanse&rdquo;.', 99, '2022-09-15 16:05:56', null),
(15, 0, 1, 1, 8, 0, 'A second usage of the word for &ldquo;heavens&rdquo;.', 99, '2022-09-15 16:22:27', '<p>Only on this day, the result of things done was not called &ldquo;good&rdquo; like for the other days.</p>'),
(15, 0, 1, 1, 9, 0, 'There was a lack of &ldquo;dry land&rdquo; prior to this.', 99, '2023-02-11 03:08:23', '<p>Again, God said this to be heard by his inner-council, but it does not say who did it. Note that it does not say that there was no land but simply the land was not &ldquo;dry&rdquo; and then after gathering the waters into &ldquo;one place&rdquo;, which seems to be what we call &ldquo;the oceans&rdquo;, some dry (not wet) land appeared. God is preparing the earth for the creation of mankind, another being to be made in His image but whose bodies would be made out of the dust of the earth.</p>'),
(15, 0, 1, 1, 10, 0, 'A second usage of the word for &ldquo;earth&rdquo;.', 99, '2022-09-15 16:08:49', null),
(15, 0, 1, 1, 20, 0, 'A 3<sup>rd</sup> usage of &ldquo;heavens&rdquo; called the open heavens, where birds fly.', 99, '2022-09-15 16:10:33', null),
(15, 0, 1, 1, 26, 0, 'Us/Our: God and his Divine Council', 99, '2022-06-15 23:34:30', null),
(15, 0, 1, 2, 5, 0, 'What is &ldquo;plant of the field&rdquo;, &ldquo;or herb of the field&rdquo;? Maybe things planted by humans for their food.', 99, '2022-09-15 16:38:39', '<p>Humans were created after plants were &ldquo;Let there be...&rdquo;. So this is not trying to contradict that. It simply seems to be saying that there were no fields planted by humans for food or their other purposes. Rather, God made a garden for mankind. I don&rsquo;t think field meant everywhere except the garden, nor did it mean, open areas of land. It just means a place where plants are grown intentionally.</p>'),
(15, 0, 1, 3, 1, 0, 'The serpent is the spirit-being who came to be called the Devil. He leads with a question to get her talking.', 99, '2023-02-01 02:26:23', null),
(15, 0, 1, 3, 3, 0, 'She hasn&rsquo;t built the spoken word of God in her mind.', 99, '2023-02-01 02:30:06', null),
(15, 0, 1, 3, 4, 0, 'Total contradiction of what God had said &ndash; this is evil.', 99, '2023-02-01 02:24:50', null),
(15, 0, 1, 3, 5, 0, 'The Devil twists words. The words themselves are true in a sense, but that sense does not apply in this way.', 99, '2023-01-31 16:45:10', '<p>This is the Devil talking &ndash; he is already a liar &ndash; twisting words. These words are true in a sense, but not totally true. Eve and Adam already know good, in the sense that God has been good to them, and everything in their environment has been good. They know that one thing is forbidden and in that sense, it warned them of evil. What they don&rsquo;t have is a full knowledge of spiritual good and evil, which existed already on day 6. If it did not exist, then God would have actually placed a stumbling block in their path by naming the tree as He did. The Devil was doing what he does best: twisting words. By disobeying God, they would be thrust into the world of the knowledge of spiritual good and evil, something they were not equipped to handle.</p>'),
(15, 0, 1, 3, 6, 0, 'Eve knew what she needed to know. But she was deceived, and thought the tree would make her wise like God and his spirit-beings.', 99, '2023-01-31 16:22:31', '<p>This tree is not called the tree of the knowledge of good and evil because it would make a person &ldquo;wise&rdquo; about good and evil. No, it is called that by God because eating of it would put mankind in the arena of knowing and therefore the need to discern between spiritual good and spiritual evil, which they were not capable of doing correctly. That is why God did not want them to eat it. He just wanted them to obey his command about this. If it really passed all good accurate knowledge and wisdom, then God would have wanted them to eat of it. But after they ate, look at what they &ldquo;knew&rdquo;. That they were naked and that was something to hide. That is knowledge but it is tainted. That is why God asked Adam, &ldquo;Who told you that you were naked?&rdquo;</p>'),
(15, 0, 1, 3, 7, 0, 'The Devil opened their eyes. Expect what they &ldquo;know&rdquo; to be twisted.', 99, '2023-02-01 02:21:59', '<p>They &ldquo;knew&rdquo; that they were naked. God created them naked &ndash; it was good like everything else in their world. But then they &ldquo;knew&rdquo; it was something bad that they needed to hide. Their eyes were opened, but by whom, God or by the Devil? God asked &ldquo;Who told you that you were naked?&rdquo;, so it wasn&rsquo;t Him. God did not say, &ldquo;What made you aware that you were naked?&rdquo; either. He asked &ldquo;Who&hellip;?&rdquo;. It wasn&rsquo;t the tree that opened their eyes. It was what the Devil did in them when they gave him their obedience over God. The Devil told them that they were naked among other things I am sure.</p> <p>They became capable of being influenced by evil through an inner spiritual connection in their nature. It is probably a deficiency in their body/soul nature. It is not a direct control over them, but it is influential. This deficiency is called &ldquo;sin&rdquo; by the Bible, and is often called the sin-nature by expositors. The word for sin means &ldquo;sub-standard&rdquo;. After this happened, demons do not have to manifest themselves in the physical world to communicate with people, they can attempt to communicate via an inner connection &ndash; sin.</p> <p>Adam and Eve sinned by wanting to receive information that God had forbidden. They wanted information about spiritual things &ldquo;good and evil&rdquo; from a source that God had forbidden. They gave The Devil the right to do what he did to them. He had to come into concretion to tempt them before they obeyed him, but now he can work internally if they let him. Eve was deceived, thinking she was doing something good, but Adam disobeyed God knowing full well.</p> <p>People still have sin in their flesh-nature, even Christians, but Christians have an inner spiritual connection to God that is called the helper and the comforter, and the spirit of truth. That spirit is permanent because it is the guarantee of their salvation.</p>'),
(15, 0, 1, 3, 10, 0, 'Not just knowing they were naked, but full acceptance of it being bad, &ldquo;I was naked, and I hid myself.&rdquo;', 99, '2022-09-19 01:38:30', '<p>Remember, they were naked, but it was good because God created them that way. But the Devil planted the knowledge that their nakedness was bad in some way via an inner-connection &ndash; sin. They bought into it completely and became afraid of being naked in front of even God, who created them that way. This is not a discernment of good and evil, but knowledge from good and evil sources. It added knowledge from an evil perspective.</p>'),
(15, 0, 1, 3, 11, 0, 'God asked the right question. WHO told you that you were naked (in a bad way)? God did not. Nature did not.', 99, '2022-09-19 01:48:23', '<p>It was knowledge from an evil source that told them that they were naked &ldquo;oh how bad being naked is&rdquo;. That was what not eating from the tree of the knowledge of good and evil was supposed to protect them from &ndash; an inner connection to influence from an evil source. By obeying the Devil, they gave him some authority and he used it to establish an inner connection in them &ndash; sin. The authority fit the sin. They desired a non-God spiritual source of knowledge and wisdom about spiritual things &ndash; good and evil. He established exactly that in them &ndash; the sin nature.</p>'),
(15, 0, 1, 3, 16, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-02 21:27:54', '<p>First thing I notice is that God says &ldquo;I will...&rdquo; for the first part of this statement about the consequences. That makes it Him bringing this pain in childbirth upon her unless this is an idiom. Secondly, I don&rsquo;t see how one can distinguish the rest of what God said to her from the &ldquo;I will...&rdquo; of the first sentence. If it is not an idiom, then all of this is His Will, and He is admitting it. Now it is apparent that He would not have liked it to be this way, but after her sin, God&rsquo;s will has apparently changed if this is literal. He wills due to His justice that her pain be multiplied in child birth, He wills that her desire turn to her husband for things, and that she now be ruled by her husband. Every other way denies that God said &ldquo;I will...&rdquo;.</p> <p>If God did not will it, but it says that He willed it, then it must be a figure of speech of some kind. Maybe it is an &ldquo;idiom of permission&rdquo; that permits or allows the Devil&rsquo;s right to influence them internally, which might even effect a change in them physically in some ways too.</p> <p>I suppose people could argue that because He did not say &ldquo;&hellip;and I will that your desire will be...&rdquo;, that this differentiates the &ldquo;I will&rdquo; of the first sentence with the rest of what He said.</p> <p>Looks to me like we have to consider this all to be God&rsquo;s just will that includes the rights of his spirit-being sons as well as those of his human son and daughter.</p> <p>The Devil had only made statements and suggestions that the humans acted on in disobedience to God. He did bear false witness about God though, and he intentionally deceived Eve.</p>'),
(15, 0, 1, 3, 17, 0, 'Listened greater to his wife than God.', 99, '2023-01-31 15:58:42', null);
INSERT INTO `myrevdata` (`myrevid`, `testament`, `book`, `chapter`, `verse`, `highlight`, `marginnote`, `sqn`, `lastupdate`, `myrevnotes`) VALUES
(15, 0, 1, 3, 22, 0, 'Thrust into the arena of the knowledge of spiritual good and spiritual evil.', 99, '2023-01-31 16:10:58', '<p>God and his inner council have been dealing with the knowledge of spiritual good versus spiritual evil already or God would have had no need to make the rule to mankind to stay out of that arena on the same day that He created Adam (day 6). Demon spirit-beings twist knowledge about good and evil so that it is difficult for mankind to walk without God&rsquo;s clear words on it. This is not a good arena for Adam and Eve to have jumped into being guided by a demon. God did not want humans to be in it. But by sin they now have an inner connection to evil spiritual influences, and if they are going to manage to live inside of God&rsquo;s will, they will need knowledge from God and it is apparent that God gives it. For Adam and Eve, this is not the ability of discernment of spiritual good versus spiritual evil, but being now thrust into the arena of it without being capable of dealing with it. If they could, they would not have thought of their nakedness as bad. Who told them that?</p>'),
(15, 0, 1, 4, 7, 0, 'Spiritual battle: God said &ldquo;...you are to rule over it&rdquo; &ndash; he could rule over the demon who was wanting to dominate him but he did not.', 99, '2022-08-31 12:00:22', '<p>Man still has the dominion here unless he gives in to obey the demon. Adam&rsquo;s sin did not take away all dominion of mankind over what happens on earth. It is a war for dominion between man and demons. People have to stay on God&rsquo;s side by believing and obeying God in order to get his help to defeat the insurgency of the Devil and his crew against the rule of mankind over what happens on earth. But if people keep giving in, then Evil takes the dominion. Adam&rsquo;s sin brought about the sin-influenced-nature of mankind and the sentence of death (to remove that person from everlasting life in God&rsquo;s creation.)</p>'),
(15, 0, 1, 4, 8, 0, '&ldquo;Cain rose up against Abel&rdquo; &ndash; First act of a man elevating himself as judge, and executioner of a human being &ndash; ruling over Abel in obedience to &ldquo;Sin&rdquo;.', 99, '2022-09-02 10:33:47', '<p>Cain gave up his own authority to rule over things done on earth to the Devil by being obedient to him. The Devil in turn supported Cain&rsquo;s &ldquo;self-elevation&rdquo; and &ldquo;Cain rose up&rdquo; over Abel&rsquo;s life and existence, judged him, and killed him. God had told Cain that he &ldquo;is to rule over the sin-demon&rdquo; but he gave his obedience to the demon instead. This is how the Devil gets authority on earth. Cain knew full well what he was doing, and he gave over his obedience to the Devil.</p> <p>Romans 6:16 &ndash; Do you not know that if you offer yourselves as obedient slaves to anyone, you are slaves of the one you obey, whether of sin leading to death or of obedience leading to righteousness?</p> <p>REV Commentary of verse 4:7 &ndash; &ldquo;Cain ignored God&rsquo;s warning and turned to the Devil for support and became &ldquo;of that wicked one&rdquo; (1 John 3:12).&rdquo;</p> <p>In the spiritual battle we must recognize when a sin-demon is trying to trick us out of our authority over actions done on earth. This is our earth, we are the God-given rulers of earth, not the Devil, who influences us to give it to him by obedience to him.</p> <p>Hypothesis: Adam gave him <u>some</u> of his dominion by eating of the tree of the knowledge of good and evil. The transfer of authority is limited to the nature of the sin. He brought two things into the world: the sin-nature (sin-affected/influenced nature), and the sentence to death (death). Adam still had authority from God to rule animals, and plants, and the earth&rsquo;s resources but there would be a state of hostility, a power struggle between mankind and the Devil&rsquo;s crew. God did not imprison or kill the Devil or his loyal followers but he took away their authority and power so that they would be oppressed and humiliated and defeated all the days of their lives. So where do they get their power to affect earth? They get it from people, the rightful rulers, who obey them. They are empowered by the sin of people. This is how they get their authority, in pieces, by the individual sins of others. It is complicated, but true. Luke 4:6 &ndash; the Devil says that the authority was delivered to him, yes, but not all by one sin. It never attributes his almost complete control of the world to Adam only. But he works through the sin-affected-nature of mankind which is passed down to all of Adam&rsquo;s progeny, and he works through the fear of death to influence people even more. By those things, all men have sinned in some way, or ways. Though he was tempted in all ways like we are, Jesus did not sin at all. Even Adam and Eve were tempted by external forces (the manifestation of the Devil as a glorious son of God) before they sinned and afterward the sin-nature made them temptable internally. Jesus, not having that sin-nature, could also be tempted by external things. The sin-nature allows temptation to come internally.</p> <p>After Adam and Eve&rsquo;s sin of eating of the tree of the knowledge of good and evil the Devil was cursed. Here is the REV commentary on the first part of that curse:</p> <p>&ldquo;on your belly you will go.&rdquo; The serpent in the Genesis record is not a literal snake, it is the figure hypocatastasis for the Devil [see commentary on Gen. 3:1, and also see Appendix 14: &ldquo;Names of the Devil,&rdquo; under &ldquo;serpent&rdquo;]. In spite of that, however, God uses idioms that apply to a snake when talking to the Devil. Genesis 3:14 is a good example, because the idiom &ldquo;to crawl on your belly&rdquo; is an idiom for <strong>oppression and humiliation</strong>, and even today that kind of idiom is used (Ps. 44:25).</p> <p>&ldquo;you will eat dust.&rdquo; This idiom refers to being <strong>defeated; &ldquo;utter defeat.&rdquo;</strong> We can see it being used in Psalm 72:9. We still use the same idiom for being defeated today, although usually in the context of being a loser in some kind of race or contest. The Devil, that &ldquo;ancient serpent,&rdquo; will always be defeated. He wins minor skirmishes, but he has been defeated over and over for thousands of years now, and eventually will be totally defeated and destroyed.</p> <p>And yet, he holds sway over the whole world. Wow! Confessing our sins, and stopping ourselves from sinning now is a key to power in the spiritual battle. We also need to manifest holy spirit to receive information and powerful works to do by our Lord&rsquo;s power. By his grace, we can do more than we can by our own godliness.</p>'),
(15, 0, 1, 4, 15, 0, 'God was not commanding that murderers be executed at this time. After Noah&rsquo;s flood, he did.', 99, '2022-09-02 10:49:16', null),
(15, 0, 1, 14, 22, 1, null, 99, '2022-12-31 19:36:18', null),
(15, 0, 2, 1, 17, 0, 'The Hebrews did not lose their faith in Egypt. Genesis was not written in a vacuum of no word from God. Read before Genesis sometime.', 99, '2022-06-08 01:02:25', '<p>Killing babies is wrong. Stand up for God above the government and fear of death.</p>'),
(15, 0, 2, 1, 21, 0, 'God blessing them already.', 99, '2022-06-08 01:18:10', null),
(15, 0, 2, 2, 2, 0, 'See Hebr. 11. Believing revelation from God.', 99, '2022-06-08 01:09:28', null),
(15, 0, 2, 2, 3, 0, 'Intentional by revelation.', 99, '2022-06-08 01:11:00', null),
(15, 0, 2, 2, 9, 0, 'What a blessing God worked here. He knows how.', 99, '2022-06-08 01:19:24', null),
(15, 0, 2, 2, 23, 0, 'They cried out to God.', 99, '2022-06-08 01:20:49', null),
(15, 0, 2, 2, 24, 0, 'God heard.', 99, '2022-06-08 01:21:11', null),
(15, 0, 2, 2, 25, 0, 'God saw, and knew.', 99, '2022-06-08 01:21:26', null),
(15, 0, 2, 3, 6, 0, 'This meant a lot to Moses!', 99, '2022-06-08 01:16:18', '<p>He had heard about the God of Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob. His people talked about him. They weren&rsquo;t living in a Word vacuum when God gave Genesis to Moses.</p>'),
(15, 0, 2, 3, 7, 0, 'God called them MY people before he called them out of Egypt to be his holy nation.', 99, '2022-06-08 01:17:25', null),
(15, 0, 2, 24, 9, 0, 'Heaven', 99, '2022-08-06 00:44:05', null),
(15, 0, 5, 32, 1, 0, 'Prophetic warning to Israel (see the end of ch.31).', 99, '2022-09-04 00:06:54', null),
(15, 0, 5, 32, 5, 0, '&ldquo;They&rdquo; appears to be Israel in the future when/if they reject God.', 99, '2022-09-04 00:36:51', null),
(15, 0, 5, 32, 8, 0, 'Yahweh is the Most High above other &ldquo;gods&rdquo;. The inheritance was land. God, as the Most High, set the boundaries of the nations according to &ldquo;the number&rdquo; of the sons of God, other &ldquo;gods&rdquo; who were allowed to rule. See Romans 1- God gave those people over. Instead of destroying them, he gave them over to other &ldquo;gods&rdquo;.<br /> &nbsp;', 99, '2022-10-23 19:47:42', '<p>God owns the whole earth. Remember the old days. The inheritance was land. There was no land of Yahweh in this arrangement, <u>but He owns it all</u>. I believe this has some respect for the idiom of permission. God set the boundaries of the nations according to what &ldquo;sons of God&rdquo; (created spirit-beings &ndash; &ldquo;gods&rdquo; that the Most High is &ldquo;over&rdquo;) that they worshipped (when they should have been worshipping Yahweh). The nations were all idolaters. He had more in mind for his chosen people when He would call them out. See Romans 1- &ldquo;gave them over&rdquo;. Instead of destroying them, he gave them over to his enemy &ldquo;gods&rdquo;. <strong>&ldquo;number&rdquo;</strong> &ndash; possibly a numerous group like: Oh I want to be in that number when the saints come marching in.&rdquo; We see in Daniel how there were actual &ldquo;spirit&rdquo; princes of the territory who were involved in delaying the angel sent from God. These territorial spirit-being rulers are aligned with the Devil, not God. In God&rsquo;s absense, they rule the way they like.</p>'),
(15, 0, 5, 32, 10, 0, 'God called Abram (who worshipped the true God while in the land of his father who worshipped a different god or gods) away from his father&rsquo;s house and land to go to a land that God would show to him. He therefore had no inherited land immediately. But his descendents, Israel would get it.', 99, '2022-09-04 00:43:04', '<p>He would go to a land that God would show him. But he gained no inheritance there. God had plans though for Abraham&rsquo;s descendents, especially the promised One to Come, who would become a blessing to all nations. Jacob/Israel was in that plan.</p>'),
(15, 0, 5, 32, 12, 0, 'This was God&rsquo;s aim. The foreign gods took everyone&rsquo;s allegiance but God was making his own nation.', 99, '2022-09-04 00:45:09', null),
(15, 0, 5, 32, 13, 0, 'He made them very prosperous. Remember this is a prophetic warning. He would make them prosperous.', 99, '2022-09-04 00:51:03', null),
(15, 0, 5, 32, 15, 0, 'Still prophetic warning. They will grow fat and become gorged and they will forsake God and reject the Rock of his salvation (the Messiah).', 99, '2022-09-04 00:53:06', null),
(15, 0, 5, 32, 20, 0, 'Yahweh will respond after this future rejection of Him. Remember, like most prophecies, this was to warn them not to do this. If they heed the warning forever, then they will not get these consequences.', 99, '2022-09-04 01:24:22', null),
(15, 0, 5, 32, 26, 0, 'God will not fully annihilate them.', 99, '2022-09-04 00:59:05', null),
(15, 0, 5, 32, 30, 0, 'God gave them over into his enemies&rsquo; hands. See Romans 1.', 99, '2022-10-23 00:54:26', null),
(15, 0, 5, 32, 31, 0, '&ldquo;their&rdquo; &ndash; the other nations that will defeat the Israelites. Follow the &ldquo;their&rdquo; in the following verses. If God were <u>for</u> the people of Israel that are inhabiting his land at that time, the gods of the other nations would not stand a chance.', 99, '2022-10-23 01:05:27', null),
(15, 0, 5, 32, 32, 0, 'I think this is talking about the other nations&rsquo; from a spiritual perspective &ndash; ruled by demons.', 99, '2022-10-23 00:58:11', null),
(15, 0, 5, 32, 34, 0, 'Then this question by God!', 99, '2022-10-23 00:58:51', null),
(15, 0, 5, 32, 35, 0, 'The Day of God&rsquo;s vengeance against the nations and their people who have mistreated His people.', 99, '2022-10-23 01:00:51', null);
