(15, 0, 5, 32, 36, 0, 'But when they are so punished that their power is gone...', 99, '2022-09-04 01:00:48', null),
(15, 0, 5, 32, 37, 0, 'God will say to the nations who abused his people. See &ldquo;the rock&rdquo; is their gods.', 99, '2022-10-23 01:48:24', null),
(15, 0, 5, 32, 38, 0, 'The other &ldquo;gods&rdquo; are zilch compared to God.', 99, '2022-10-23 01:49:37', null),
(15, 0, 5, 32, 39, 0, 'God has no god. The gods that exist are nothing in comparison to Yahweh!', 99, '2022-10-23 01:53:04', null),
(15, 0, 5, 32, 40, 0, 'God swearing by himself. He will bring vengeance.', 99, '2022-10-23 01:54:50', null),
(15, 0, 9, 1, 4, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-12 00:01:15', '<p>If brought a sin offering, the priests got a piece of the meat, but you got to eat the rest of it.</p>'),
(15, 0, 9, 1, 5, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-12 00:03:21', '<p>Simply means that the reason was of a spiritual origin. God or God allowing it for some reason. It might be that God had a plan.</p>'),
(15, 0, 9, 1, 6, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-12 00:04:48', '<p>Maybe Elkanah could have done more to make order, but often these dual-wife situations are difficult.</p>'),
(15, 0, 9, 1, 8, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-12 00:06:53', '<p>Hannah, rolling her eyes, duh, of course not you clueless husband.</p>'),
(15, 0, 10, 7, 11, 0, '&ldquo;a house&rdquo; &ndash; meaning a dynasty', 99, '2022-12-04 19:39:40', '<p>This is the subject, David&rsquo;s God-made dynasty. It is not talking about a physical constructed house. This is the context of the following section of scripture, even when David goes into the house of God to praise and thank God for this awesome gift. He knows that if it is going to be &ldquo;forever&rdquo;, the Messiah, the promised seed in Genesis 3, the seed of Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, and the king that would come from Judah&rsquo;s line, has to be in that dynasty eventually, and ultimately. Therefore God promised David that the Messiah would come from his lineage, that is the most important part of God&rsquo;s promise about David&rsquo;s house, his dynasty, but it is also talking about the sons of David would be the rightful choices for the kingship of Israel from now on.</p>'),
(15, 0, 10, 7, 12, 0, 'your seed = Solomon and Messiah', 99, '2023-01-01 01:50:38', null),
(15, 0, 10, 7, 13, 0, 'In one sense Solomon built a house for God&rsquo;s name, but in two ways will also the Messiah &ndash; He will build a new temple in Zion and a house that will govern Israel and the whole world.', 99, '2022-12-04 19:47:06', '<p>It is true both of Solomon and the Messiah</p>'),
(15, 0, 10, 7, 14, 0, 'The Messiah will not commit iniquity, but all the other Davidic kings would do so in various ways.', 99, '2022-12-04 19:48:42', null),
(15, 0, 10, 7, 15, 0, 'The Davidic dynasty is by a covenant, which they eventually broke badly enough for God to end it. But God&rsquo;s promise remained intact for the Messiah per the next verse. See 2 Chronicles 6:16.', 99, '2022-12-04 20:10:47', '<p>See 2 Chronicles 6:14ff &ndash; and he said, &ldquo;O Yahweh, the God of Israel, there is no God like you in heaven or on earth, who keeps the covenant and covenant faithfulness with your servants who walk before you with all their heart 15You have kept what you spoke to your servant David my father. You spoke with your mouth and have fulfilled it with your hand, as it is this day.<br /> &nbsp; 16So now may Yahweh the God of Israel keep for your servant David my father what you have spoken to him, saying, &lsquo;You will not fail to have a man sit in my presence on the throne of Israel, <u>if only your sons guard their way, to walk in my Law as you have walked before me</u>.&rsquo;<br /> &nbsp;</p> <p>The Davidic covenant for the continuation of the sons of David to be king were still dependent on the original covenant to Israel, to walk in God&rsquo;s Law. It was not stated this way in 2 Samuel 7, but this is the correct understanding of how the covenants interrelate. However, the earlier covenants that include the Messiah were not under the later covenant that included the Law.</p>'),
