(15, 0, 20, 4, 25, 1, 'Eyelids are aimed by the head not the eyes.', 99, '2023-02-04 13:27:09', '<p>This is a Hebrew parallelism in meaning but the actions to get there are somewhat different. &ldquo;Focus your eyes in front of you,&rdquo; is parallel to &ldquo;let your eyelids look straight ahead of you.&rdquo; However, eyelids cannot be focused or directed independently from the head like the eyes can. Focus your eyes, and train your head which aims the eyelids. Both are about looking straight ahead which is an idiom meaning to do the will and law of God, without turning to the right or left, which is to do evil. There are lots of varying degrees of turning but only 1 straight ahead.</p>'),
