(15, 1, 45, 1, 17, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-26 00:06:37', '<p>Habakkuk is about faithfulness, but here it is about trust to the end of believing and confessing as in Rom. 10:9-10.</p>'),
(15, 1, 45, 1, 24, 0, 'Abandon God and He honors your free will choice and He abandons you.', 99, '2022-10-26 12:27:08', '<p>REV commentary is very helpful. The point is that when a person rejects God, and God leaves them alone, then they become subject to everything in the creation that is also against God without God&rsquo;s help. Worshiping these things that are not God, opens a person up to the deception and advances and detriments and even attacks of demons who take advantage of people. Even if the god-rejecters don&rsquo;t accept any thing as a god or as an idol, they still become subject to the effects of their sins against them and the eventual judgment of God against their works.</p> <p>Now, sin loves company. Sinning in one way leads to sinning in more ways. Corruption yields more corruption. It all affects a person negatively. This corruption also affects society. People who recognize the creator God &ndash; Yahweh &ndash; will also feel some of the affects of the corruption of their society by those who reject Him. Corrupt laws, corrupt TV, corrupt internet things, corrupt businesses, corrupt employers, corrupt lawyers, corrupt ministers, it all affects the blessings of God on the land. Our lives can be affected by it all. We should work at maintaining our holiness, our separation from the corruption. We need to pray to be blessed and protected from corruption and evil and such and operate manifestations of holy spirit to follow the Lord through the wilderness.</p>'),
(15, 1, 45, 7, 7, 0, 'His Word tells me what is right and wrong, yay! (Vs.8) But (dark music &ndash; da dat dat da) sin&hellip;', 99, '2022-06-08 00:47:54', '<p>Would not know what it is to covet&hellip; (not really, not for sure.)</p>'),
(15, 1, 45, 7, 8, 0, 'Sin-consciousness because the commandment makes them known. Ruining my life, my vitality, my vivaciousness.', 99, '2022-06-08 00:45:17', '<p>Opportunity &ndash; if never came to respect the commandment, then no sin-consciousness. With the law, we need to keep our God-given things like righteousness, joy, peace, etc. Keep moving ahead.</p>'),
(15, 1, 45, 7, 17, 0, 'I &ndash; the inner me. The me that will remain in the kingdom.', 99, '2022-06-08 00:50:07', null),
(15, 1, 45, 7, 20, 0, 'Its the sin-nature in my flesh, not the me that has Christ in me, the one who will live in the kingdom of the Messiah.', 99, '2022-06-08 00:22:46', null),
(15, 1, 45, 7, 24, 0, 'Look what he did anyways.', 99, '2022-06-08 00:24:24', '<p>Look what Paul accomplished working with Jesus and God. He kept at it even though he has the sin-nature.</p>'),
(15, 1, 45, 8, 14, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-14 22:44:03', null),
(15, 1, 45, 8, 15, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-14 22:44:07', null),
