(15, 1, 47, 12, 2, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-30 13:05:50', '<p>I don&rsquo;t see how the third heaven can be called paradise since paradise is on earth. This is clearly talking about heaven. Now, he could have been brought by revelation vision to a future heaven, or to a third level of heaven (above the open heaven that birds fly in, and above the firmament of heaven where the sun, moon, and stars are placed, to the place where God, Jesus, and the angels reside &ndash; the third heaven.</p> <p>In the body or out of the body &ndash; might refer to the body of Christ, in other words: Christian or not. Or it might refer to an actual taking to the third heaven if it was the one beyond the 2 other heavens that exist today. Certainly, if it was to the future 3<sup>rd</sup> heaven, then that would be &ldquo;out of the body&rdquo;, in other words, only via revelation, not an actual going there. God can give revelation that is similar to &ldquo;being there in actuality&rdquo;. For example, look at John&rsquo;s experience as he relates what he was shown and was told as written in Revelation.</p> <p>Now, theologians seem to agree that this was Paul talking about himself. I don&rsquo;t know how that is. It certainly does not look like that from a casual reader&rsquo;s point of view.</p>'),
(15, 1, 47, 12, 4, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-30 13:11:18', '<p>Again, this looks to the casual reader like Paul was referring to someone other than himself, but many commentators believe it was about Paul himself. I don&rsquo;t know how that is.</p>');
