(20, 0, 1, 2, 11, 0, null, 99, '2022-04-19 23:08:07', '<p>Pishon occurs only here in the bible.</p> <p>Havilah, as a place, also occurs in Genesis 25:18. Web references suggest it might be South of Cush, kind of in Ethiopia.</p> <p>There isn&#39;t enough data to suggest a strong correlation, especially considering the flood of Noah likely changed a lot of geography.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 2, 12, 0, null, 99, '2022-04-19 22:30:35', '<p>Resin is a semi clear substance that is gooey but becomes hard. It comes mostly from trees ( primarily pine) but also some plants. It can repel water and be used to seal boats. It can also be made into turpentine, has many uses and in hops, gives beer it&#39;s unique aroma and bitter taste. Incense was derived from plant resins.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 2, 13, 0, null, 99, '2022-04-19 22:51:58', '<p>Gihon Spring is on the east side of the City of David ( southern Jerusalem) and on the city side of the Kidron Valley.</p> <p>Cush is first mentioned as a place in Isaiah 11:11, 18:1, then Jeremiah 46.9, Ezekiel38:5, Nahum 3:9, and Zephaniah 3:10. Cush (and Put frequently referenced with it) are in Africa, cush borders the west side of the southern part of the Red Sea. (Put is west of Egypt.)</p> <p>Not sure if any correlation exists between these locations and what is given here.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 2, 14, 0, null, 99, '2022-04-19 23:12:34', '<p>Assyria is Northeast of... The &quot;sea&quot; of Galilee. Euphrates runs between the the land northeast of the Mediterranean sea to the Persian Gulf southeast of Babylon.</p> <p>Although we can&#39;t be sure of these place, I wonder why Godnames them, and has Moses write them as part of this book. Could He be giving some information as to the playing field where His story would take place?</p>'),
