INSERT INTO `myrevdata` (`myrevid`, `testament`, `book`, `chapter`, `verse`, `highlight`, `marginnote`, `sqn`, `lastupdate`, `myrevnotes`) VALUES
(20, 0, 1, 17, 23, 3, null, 99, '2022-08-25 04:25:13', '<p>What would this conversation been like? &quot;Hi Harry, I was talking to God. Anyway, bottom line is I&#39;m going to cut off your foreskin today. Your cool with that, aren&#39;t you?&quot;</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 17, 26, 0, null, 99, '2022-08-25 04:29:18', '<p>Ishmael was absolutely included in the covenant.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 18, 15, 0, null, 99, '2022-08-14 15:39:22', '<p>Note that Abraham laughed earlier. God pokes at Sarah for whatever was different between their 2 responses. It&#39;s a gentle nudge that would have helped her trust.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 20, 1, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-10 05:25:01', '<p>See <a href="http://www.dropbox.com/s/fasejlnb78yqv6s/2.2%20Patriarchs%20Abraham%20copy.jpg?dl=0">Satelte Bible Atlas Map 2-2</a></p> <p>Kadeshis in the lower left corner. The road to Shut is shown as their route to Egypt. Gerar is midway between their route and the Mediterranean Sea.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 20, 16, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-09 03:57:13', '<p>I don&#39;t know the value of 1000 pieces of silver, but if we used the value in the commentary of Acts 19:11, it would come to about $60,000.00.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 21, 20, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-09 07:47:35', '<p>The bow, could this relate to Sagittarius? I wonder if there was any activity in Sagittarius around this time? Also, does activity in Sagittarius point to descendants of Ishmael?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 21, 21, 2, null, 99, '2022-09-09 05:16:18', '<p>Try to add map with Paran.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 21, 31, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-09 07:20:15', '<p>Beer means well, and Sheba means oath or seven.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 22, 1, 5, null, 99, '2022-09-10 07:50:20', '<p>Commentary 3rd paragraph, 2nd to last sentence references Jonah 1:1, but I think the reference should include verse 2 also since it states what God wanted Jonah to do.</p> <p>Also, 4th paragraph references Genesis 22 but I think the reference should be limited to Genesis 22:1-18.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 22, 2, 5, null, 99, '2022-09-11 23:21:18', '<p><a href="http://www.dropbox.com/s/fasejlnb78yqv6s/2.2%20Patriarchs%20Abraham%20copy.jpg?dl=0">Satellite Bible Atlas Map 2-2</a> shows that Moriah is right around or at Jerusalem.</p> <p>*fix* The 3rd paragraph references chapter 22, but I think the reference should be limited to Genesis 22:1-18, same thing occurs in paragraph 11, and paragraph 12.</p> <p>Also, Probably for John- The 4th paragraph says Isaac carried the wood 3 days, but the way the record is written, Abraham splits the wood, they travel 3 days, then Abraham has the others with them wait with the donkey and he puts the wood on Isaac to carry.</p> <p>Als in paragraph 10, where it referencesHebrews 11, I think Hebrews 11:1-19 cover all the relevant verses, and then some.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 22, 17, 5, null, 99, '2022-09-12 01:15:52', '<p>Both the 1st and 3rd paragraphs have &quot; [For the figure...&quot; , but then mention the commentary for 2 different examples. I am wondering if the. 2 phrases could be condensed into1 followed by both commentary references?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 22, 21, 2, null, 99, '2022-09-12 01:23:55', '<p>See if there is a Map for this</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 23, 1, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-17 22:01:05', '<p>Sarah was 10 yrs younger than Abraham. Isaac was born when Abraham was 100, so Isaac would have been about 37 when Sarah died.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 23, 2, 2, null, 99, '2022-09-17 21:31:20', '<p>Hebron is between Jerusalem and Beer Sheba, west of the Dead Sea, about half way between the Dead Sea and the Mediterranean. satellite Bible Atlas Map 2-2 shows the location.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 23, 7, 4, null, 99, '2022-09-13 04:14:23', '<p>Sons of Heth are Hittites? (see paragraph 3-- having trouble with the connection)</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 23, 8, 2, null, 99, '2022-09-13 04:20:40', '<p>Is there lineage, or more info on Zohar or Ephron?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 23, 10, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-15 04:54:41', '<p>Heth was the firstborn son of Canaan. Hittites were listed as one of the nations In the land. See Genesis 15:18-21.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 23, 17, 2, null, 99, '2022-09-15 05:02:07', '<p>Add the map.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 23, 19, 2, null, 99, '2022-09-16 04:45:34', '<p>Refresh on map location.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 24, 4, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-18 00:41:39', '<p>My country is referring to Haran, north by Ur of the Chaldees. This is later validated in Genesis 25:20 where it references Paddan Aram which puts it in this General region.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 24, 60, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:30:21', null),
(20, 0, 1, 24, 62, 2, null, 99, '2022-09-17 21:11:11', '<p>See Satellite Bible Atlas Map 3-4, on the southern border of Canaan.</p> <p>Link the map.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 25, 9, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-17 22:38:52', '<p>The sons of Keturah are not mentioned as being there. Isaac would have been 75 yrs old, and Ishmael was older.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 25, 11, 2, null, 99, '2022-09-17 22:41:45', '<p>On the Southern border of Canaan, see Satellite Bible Atlas Map 3-4.</p> <p>Link map</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 25, 23, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:30:43', null),
(20, 0, 1, 25, 24, 5, null, 99, '2022-09-18 00:55:15', '<p>Emailed John on 9/17/22 that I think the word be should be removed.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 26, 6, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-18 20:07:36', '<p>The location of Gerar has a question mark in the Satellite Bible Atlas, but is shown between approximately 12 and 15 miles NW of Beer-sheba.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 26, 16, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-18 20:16:52', '<p>Seems similar to what Pharoah thought of the Israelites when they were slaves in Egypt.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 26, 17, 4, null, 99, '2022-09-18 20:20:55', '<p>See Genesis 26:6, marble the first reference is a region and this narrows it down?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 26, 26, 4, null, 99, '2022-09-18 22:42:34', '<p>See Genesis 21:2-32. This is such a parallel. If it&#39;s the same Abimelech he&#39;d have to be pretty old?</p>');
INSERT INTO `myrevdata` (`myrevid`, `testament`, `book`, `chapter`, `verse`, `highlight`, `marginnote`, `sqn`, `lastupdate`, `myrevnotes`) VALUES
(20, 0, 1, 26, 29, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-18 22:19:40', '<p>Hmmm... Nothing but good? What about the wells their men filled? Or the other well Isaac&#39;s men dug, and they took possession of?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 26, 30, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-18 22:20:57', '<p>Generous on Isaac&#39;s part.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 26, 31, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-18 22:22:15', '<p>I wonder what they swore specifically?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 26, 33, 4, null, 99, '2022-09-18 22:34:38', '<p>Is there any relation to this Beer-Sheba and the one Abraham</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 26, 35, 4, null, 99, '2022-09-18 22:53:22', '<p>Abraham bought the tomb for Sarah from Ephron the Httite in Genesis 23:10-16. Nothing more is said here. What is the significance?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 27, 3, 4, null, 99, '2022-09-18 22:55:55', '<p>I wonder if there was activity in Sagittarius around this time?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 27, 9, 4, null, 99, '2022-09-18 23:44:12', '<p>Seems like there was a sense of urgency here. Why two goats. Wouldn&#39;t one goat supply enough meat for an old man&#39;s stew? There are different kinds of goats etc but one web site suggested a 20 lb live goat would provide 5 lbs of edible meat. So how much would a &quot;good young goat&quot; weigh?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 27, 27, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:31:16', null),
(20, 0, 1, 27, 28, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:31:26', null),
(20, 0, 1, 27, 29, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:31:21', null),
(20, 0, 1, 27, 36, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-18 23:52:34', '<p>And he said-the he is Esau</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 27, 39, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:32:00', null),
(20, 0, 1, 27, 40, 1, null, 99, '2022-09-18 23:55:58', '<p>I wonder what the &quot;break lose&quot; refers to?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 27, 44, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-19 00:02:26', '<p>A few days... talk about an understatement. It would take at least a few days just to travel from Beer-Sheba to Haran. He ends up staying over 14 years.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 27, 46, 5, null, 99, '2022-09-19 00:06:24', '<p>The bottom reference sugests a range of verses, but the beginning and ending verse are the same.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 28, 18, 5, null, 99, '2022-09-22 04:31:08', '<p>The 1st and 5th paragraphs both reference all 4 of the standing stones Jacob set up- it seems like they could be modified to just be detailed once.</p> <p>Also, in the 2nd to last paragraph, where Joshua 11:9 was listed, I suspect 11:19 was intended.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 28, 19, 2, null, 99, '2022-09-22 04:36:28', '<p>The name Luz seems to have quite a few possible meanings. Not sure which applies.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 28, 22, 4, null, 99, '2022-09-22 04:41:36', '<p>The text doesn&#39;t mention an alter, but the commentary does. It also mentions sacrifice because of the alter, but with no alter mentioned, isn&#39;t the sacrifice suspect?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 29, 1, 4, null, 99, '2022-09-22 04:52:57', '<p>Children of the east seems to carry a definition that isn&#39;t clear. Some references suggest east of Palestine like the Arabs, others associate it with wisdom, like the astronomers, but they didn&#39;t really get wise till Daniel.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 29, 7, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-22 04:58:28', '<p>Didn&#39;t Jacob water them in Genesis 29:3 ?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 29, 10, 4, null, 99, '2022-09-22 04:56:48', '<p>Interesting- the repeat of mother&#39;s brother.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 29, 20, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-22 09:32:49', '<p>Serving 7 years for a bride... Is that what God will wait to see his Son have his bride? ( Perhaps 7,000 years? I.E., 2037ish?)</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 29, 32, 2, null, 99, '2022-09-28 05:01:48', '<p>Build a table listing every son, his mother, name meaning. Also copy it and put the copy near 31st 28 where the blessings are given and list each blessing.</p> <p>Reuben means: Behold A Son, Son Of Vision</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 29, 33, 0, null, 99, '2021-11-21 16:35:27', '<p>Simeon means hearing</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 29, 34, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-24 09:17:06', '<p>Levi means joiner.</p> <p>I wonder if there is any correlation to the constellation Cancer? (becauce of the pinchers?)</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 29, 35, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-24 09:30:53', '<p>Judah means praise.</p> <p>The blessing to Judah near Jacob&#39;s end of life is in Genesis 49:8-12 and shows Judah as the lion.</p> <p>I wonder if there is any correlation to the constellation Leo?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 30, 3, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-24 09:03:51', '<p>&quot;Bear on my knees&quot; - this is the only time this phrase appears in the bible,</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 30, 4, 5, null, 99, '2022-09-24 09:08:20', '<p>The last 2 references say &quot;went to her&quot; not &quot;went in to her&quot; maybe this should go to John?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 30, 6, 4, null, 99, '2022-09-25 08:32:12', '<p>I wonder if the commentary, where it references Benjamin, should reference Genesis 35:19 or that Rachel named him Benoni.</p> <p>Judged-I wonder if there is any correlation to the constellation Taurus? (The primary star Pleiades has to do with Judgement I think-- I should verify that)</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 30, 25, 4, null, 99, '2022-09-28 05:09:31', '<p>This is before the &quot;jubilee&quot; was given. I wonder if the timeline has any connection? According to the chronology chart, it was 7 years after Jacob married Rachel and Leah that Joseph was born.</p>');
INSERT INTO `myrevdata` (`myrevid`, `testament`, `book`, `chapter`, `verse`, `highlight`, `marginnote`, `sqn`, `lastupdate`, `myrevnotes`) VALUES
(20, 0, 1, 30, 35, 4, null, 99, '2022-09-28 05:30:26', '<p>The pronouns in verses 35 and 36 are confusing. Did Jacob or Laban remove them, and whose sons?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 30, 40, 4, null, 99, '2022-09-29 06:58:02', '<p>I am having a hard time envisioning this from how it is written.</p> <p>Would Jacob have gotten revelation to do these steps?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 31, 7, 4, null, 99, '2022-09-29 07:02:36', '<p>Did he change them 10 times? Or is that an exaggeration?</p> <p>1) serve an extra 7 years for Rachel.</p> <p>2)?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 31, 13, 5, null, 99, '2022-09-29 07:07:05', '<p>Since the commentary sentence starts with Jacob, it would be just as clear to have &quot;him&quot; instead of repeating his name.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 31, 21, 2, null, 99, '2022-09-29 07:14:28', '<p>Add map showing Gilead.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 31, 25, 4, null, 99, '2022-09-29 07:17:55', '<p>Is this saying they were both in the same mountain?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 31, 41, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-29 08:37:35', '<p>He repeats 10 times. See Genesis 31:7</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 31, 47, 2, null, 99, '2022-10-01 22:18:39', '<p>Link to Satellite Bible Atlas - Map 2-3</p> <p>Jegar Sahadutha means testimony or heap</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 31, 50, 4, null, 99, '2022-10-01 22:19:53', '<p>Is this a threat?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 31, 51, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-01 22:25:11', '<p>See Genesis 31:45, Jacob had set the standing stone, not Laban.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 31, 53, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-01 22:28:23', '<p>Isaac feared Yahweh, so Jacob swore to Yahweh.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 31, 55, 4, null, 99, '2022-10-01 22:31:33', '<p>When it says sons, I suspect it means grandsons. His daughters would include Rachel, Leah and his granddaughter Dinah along with any other granddaughters- but no others are mentioned.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 32, 2, 2, null, 99, '2022-10-01 22:34:33', '<p>See Satellite Bible Atlas - Map 2-3.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 32, 3, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-01 22:44:47', '<p>See Satellite Bible Atlas - Map 2-3, bottom right of the map.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 32, 9, 5, null, 99, '2022-10-01 22:54:50', '<p>The bottom of the 3rd paragraph mentions Jacob&#39;s limp, but that didn&#39;t happen until after meeting Esau, see Genesis 32:24-31.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 32, 16, 4, null, 99, '2022-10-01 23:44:44', '<p>See Satellite Bible Atlas - Map 2-3.</p> <p>The commentary description puts him close to Mahanaim, and the red arrow also shows Esau in that area, but I find that confusing. Even though Jacob&#39;s camps were likely slower than Esau&#39;s 400 men, Jacob should have been partway towards Esau, like I am thinking south of Mizpah where the Jabbok comes back together? See Genesis 32:21, but note Jabbok is in italics... Then the record of wrestling the angel in Genesis32:24-31 puts him at Peniel (Satellite Bible Atlas Penuel?) which is very close to Mahanaim.</p> <p>We&#39;re his concerns slowing him to where he was barely moving?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 32, 17, 5, null, 99, '2022-10-01 23:29:59', '<p>Where the commentary says &quot;...that and group...&quot;, it sounds awkward. Maybe &quot;...that the group..&quot;?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 32, 20, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-01 23:33:05', '<p>The commentary last sentence says &quot;lift up the fact&quot; instead of &quot;lift up the face&quot;.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 32, 22, 5, null, 99, '2022-10-02 00:02:17', '<p>In the 2nd reference, Genesis 30:9-12, should it go to verse 13 instead of 12 so we get the name of the 2nd son consistent with the first reference?</p> <p>See Satellite Bible Atlas - Map 3-3 for where the Jabbok is close to Penuel.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 32, 24, 5, null, 99, '2022-10-02 01:56:29', '<p>The wording in the last sentence of the commentary could be changed and provide a link to commentary on Genesis 32:28</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 33, 17, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-02 02:04:25', '<p>See Satellite Bible Atlas - Map 2-3, Sukkoth is called Succoth there and is about 5 miles west of Penuel. Succoth means booths.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 33, 18, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-02 02:07:44', '<p>See map from MyRRH Gen 33:17. Shechem is about 20 miles west of Succoth.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 33, 19, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-02 02:10:04', '<p>So, Israel owned a parcel of land in Canaan just outside Shechem.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 34, 2, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-02 02:14:56', '<p>Basically, this is pre-marital sex...</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 34, 7, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-02 02:16:27', '<p>Pre-marital sex was considered &quot;not OK&quot;.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 34, 30, 4, null, 99, '2022-10-02 05:35:50', '<p>Shechem and his father Hamor were Hivites per Genesis 34:2. Strange Hivites are not mentioned here, but Perizzites are? What is the relevance of Perizzites here?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 35, 1, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-02 05:41:40', '<p>See Satellite Bible Atlas - Map 2-3. Bethel is about 12 miles south of Shechem, still on the west side of the Jordan.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 35, 2, 4, null, 99, '2022-10-07 05:50:00', '<p>Change your clothing? I thought it was unusual to have more than one set of clothing. I wonder what the signif&igrave;ance is?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 35, 4, 4, null, 99, '2022-10-07 05:53:23', '<p>I wonder why the rings in their ears? He hadn&#39;t asked for those.</p> <p>And why hide them instead of destroy them?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 35, 6, 4, null, 99, '2022-10-07 05:55:54', '<p>I wonder why the name Luz was included, and even listed first here?</p>');
INSERT INTO `myrevdata` (`myrevid`, `testament`, `book`, `chapter`, `verse`, `highlight`, `marginnote`, `sqn`, `lastupdate`, `myrevnotes`) VALUES
(20, 0, 1, 35, 8, 4, null, 99, '2022-10-11 04:55:11', '<p>According to web search results, Allon Bacuth means Oak of Weeping. It doesn&#39;t appear anywhere else in the bible.</p> <p>This note seems strange here, but I imagine to the Israelites, it was note worthy. It makes me wonder if God had it put here to support the Deborah in Judges-they shared the name and oaks.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 35, 10, 1, null, 99, '2022-10-07 06:04:21', '<p>Jacob was first renamed Israel in Genesis 32:28.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 35, 11, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:33:20', null),
(20, 0, 1, 35, 12, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:33:24', null),
(20, 0, 1, 35, 15, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-08 06:46:52', '<p>Bethel means house of God.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 35, 16, 2, null, 99, '2022-10-08 06:49:20', '<p>See Satellite Bible Atlas - Map 2-3</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 35, 18, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-08 06:56:03', '<p>Benoni means &ldquo;son of my sorrow,&rdquo; but Jacob called him Benjamin, &ldquo;son of my right hand&rdquo;.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 35, 19, 2, null, 99, '2022-10-10 04:39:46', '<p>Note that there are 2 Bethlehems. One is South of Jerusalem, but this one is north of Jerusalem in Benjamin.</p> <p>See Satellite Bible Atlas - Map 2-3.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 35, 21, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-10 04:36:43', '<p>Eder is suggested to be Migdal Eder, Jerusalem per <a href="http://www.dropbox.com/s/btc7hffqmibszuq/2.3%20Jacob%20and%20Joseph%20with%20highlights.jpg?dl=0">Satellite Bible Atlas Map 2-3</a></p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 35, 22, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-10 04:48:26', '<p>Bilhah had been Rachel&#39;s slave. She had bore Dan and Naphtali.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 35, 23, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:33:40', null),
(20, 0, 1, 35, 24, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:33:37', null),
(20, 0, 1, 35, 25, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:33:42', null),
(20, 0, 1, 35, 26, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:33:45', null),
(20, 0, 1, 35, 27, 2, null, 99, '2022-10-10 04:53:39', '<p>It is interesting how the name bounces back and forth between Israel and Jacob.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 36, 2, 4, null, 99, '2022-10-13 09:02:49', '<p>In Genesis 36:2, it shows Ziben the Hivite, but in Genesis 36:20 it shows him as a son of Sier the Horite. How is this clarified?</p> <p>Oholibamah is listed as the daughter of Anah, the daughter of Zone in the Hivite here, but in</p> <p>here is different than the one in Genesis 36:20, and that Zibeon named his daughter after her uncle?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 36, 8, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-13 04:33:53', '<p>See Satellite Bible Atlas - Map 2-3, lower right, SE of the Dead Sea for Mount Seir.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 36, 10, 1, null, 99, '2022-10-13 08:38:59', '<p>Question: This section containing lineage info is formatted as Hebrew poetry. Should it be?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 36, 11, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:33:57', null),
(20, 0, 1, 36, 12, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:34:00', null),
(20, 0, 1, 36, 13, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:34:03', null),
(20, 0, 1, 36, 14, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:34:11', null),
(20, 0, 1, 36, 15, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:34:33', null),
(20, 0, 1, 36, 16, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:34:36', null),
(20, 0, 1, 36, 17, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:34:39', null),
(20, 0, 1, 36, 18, 1, null, 99, '2022-10-13 04:40:57', '<p>See verse 14, these are the same people, but it calls out that they are &ldquo;Chiefs&rdquo;</p> <p>There are a total of 14 chiefs.</p> <p>One is Amalek.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 36, 19, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:35:16', null),
(20, 0, 1, 36, 20, 4, null, 99, '2022-10-13 09:11:44', '<p>See Genesis 36:24, is Anah a son of Seir or a son of Zibeon or see Genesis 36:2, a daughter of Zibeon the Hivite?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 36, 21, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:36:36', null),
(20, 0, 1, 36, 22, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:36:38', null);
