(20, 0, 1, 36, 40, 1, null, 99, '2022-10-13 09:21:05', '<p>There are 11 chiefs here.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 36, 41, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:38:06', null),
(20, 0, 1, 36, 42, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:38:10', null),
(20, 0, 1, 36, 43, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:38:13', null),
(20, 0, 1, 37, 2, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-14 07:08:04', '<p>The sons would have been Dan and Naphtali (from Bilhah). and Had and Asher (from Zulpah).</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 37, 9, 2, null, 99, '2022-10-14 07:21:21', '<p>I keep a nting to see if thecontellations have specific parallels to each off the 12 sons of Israel. For example:</p> <p>Judah = Leo</p> <p>Joseph = Gemini ( because his portion went to Ephraim &amp; Manasseh).</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 37, 25, 2, null, 99, '2022-10-17 06:21:30', '<p>Add Satellite Bible Atlas map</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 37, 34, 5, null, 99, '2022-10-20 11:22:43', '<p>In the references in thec2nd to last paragraph, it references Exe 9:3, but there is not a reference to torn clothes there. Searching between 2 Kings and Esther, I found additional references in 2 Chr 23:13 and 2 Chr 34:19</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 37, 36, 5, null, 99, '2022-10-20 11:39:52', '<p>The punctuation in the last sentence of the first paragraph made it hard to read. Is the &quot;So&quot; after &quot;Midianites&quot; a new sentence? It is capitalized with no period before it.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 38, 5, 2, null, 99, '2022-10-20 11:45:10', '<p>Where is Chezib?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 38, 7, 3, null, 99, '2022-10-20 11:46:48', '<p>He was in Err (error?) LOL</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 38, 11, 4, null, 99, '2022-10-20 11:50:06', '<p>Her father&#39;s house- would that mean Judah, or the family she was born into?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 38, 21, 2, null, 99, '2022-10-21 05:49:18', '<p>Where is Enaim?</p>');
INSERT INTO `myrevdata` (`myrevid`, `testament`, `book`, `chapter`, `verse`, `highlight`, `marginnote`, `sqn`, `lastupdate`, `myrevnotes`) VALUES
(20, 0, 1, 38, 30, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-21 06:23:47', '<p>According to a Google search, Sarah means glowing, dawn, brilliance.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 41, 16, 4, null, 99, '2022-10-24 04:28:38', '<p>I wonder how Joseph could say it would be a favorable answer? Was he getting that revelation already?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 41, 44, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-26 06:38:53', '<p>The way this is phrased reminds me of Matthew 16:18.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 41, 45, 0, null, 99, '2022-11-29 06:01:44', '<p>God used this marriage to strengthen Joseph&rsquo;s new position as a national leader. The city of On was also known as Heliopolis, &ldquo;The City of the Sun.&rdquo; It was the center of worship of the sun god, Ra, and was located 10 miles northeast of modern Cairo. The priests of On were considered to be among the most intelligent and cultured persons in Egypt, and their erudition was second to none. The ancient historian Herodotus reported that &ldquo;the men of Heliopolis are said to be the most learned in records of the Egyptians&rdquo; (History 2:3, trans. by G. Macaulay). The high priest in On held the title of &ldquo;Greatest of Seers.&rdquo; When Joseph married into this family, he joined a social class befitting a national leader. Also implied in the marriage arrangement was Pharaoh&rsquo;s confidence that Joseph, too, was a &ldquo;seer,&rdquo; or prophet, of the highest caliber.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 42, 24, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-30 09:44:30', '<p>Simeon was Joseph&#39;s 2nd oldest brother by Leah.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 43, 6, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-31 06:50:31', '<p>Interesting that Israel is used instead of Jacob here.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 43, 29, 0, null, 99, '2022-11-02 04:24:27', '<p>Benjamin his brother, his mother&rsquo;s son, &lt;----he saw all his brothers as brothers, so &quot;his mother on&quot; is added to show the special relationship.</p> <p>and said, &ldquo;Is this your youngest brother, of whom you spoke to me?&rdquo; He said, &ldquo;God be gracious to you, my son.&quot;&lt;---it doesn&#39;t look like he gave any of them time to respond.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 43, 30, 5, null, 99, '2022-11-02 04:26:40', '<p>The REV translation for 1 Kings 3:26 doesn&#39;t match the commentary&#39;s wording.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 43, 32, 0, null, 99, '2022-11-02 04:30:02', '<p>Amazing, by having 3 serving areas, no one violated the rule, but to the brothers would likely have thought this leader was set apart because of his position.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 44, 5, 0, null, 99, '2022-11-02 04:36:09', '<p>Indeed divides? - I don&#39;t get any indication Joseph divined. Was this an added lie to further throw them off track?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 44, 15, 0, null, 99, '2022-11-02 04:39:37', '<p>More sneekiness Joseph!</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 45, 11, 4, null, 99, '2022-11-04 07:11:48', '<p>This may be what Joseph&#39;s dream in Genesis 37:5-10 was showing him. Was it a prophetic dream?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 45, 24, 4, null, 99, '2022-11-04 07:14:29', '<p>I wonder why the comment about not quarreling on the way is here?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 1, 0, null, 99, '2022-11-04 06:56:52', '<p>For all the hardship produced by famine, he still offered sacrifices-and this is still before the law would have commanded it! It shows his thankfulness to God. It could also be recognition that he saw God as his provision.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 2, 0, null, 99, '2022-11-04 06:58:01', '<p>God responded to Jacob&#39;s heart in offering his sacrifice.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 4, 4, null, 99, '2022-11-04 07:03:41', '<p>Joseph will close your eyes--does this mean he will be living with/near Joseph when he does? After missing him so long, I&#39;&#39;d imagine that would be a comfort.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 7, 0, null, 99, '2022-11-04 07:17:00', '<p>Daughters being plural refers to Jacob&#39;s daughters in law.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 9, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:39:59', null),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 10, 1, null, 99, '2022-11-04 07:31:44', '<p>Question: wouldn&#39;t pretty much all the sons wives been Canaanite women? (give or take the Hivites per Genesis 34:2, 34:29.) I wonder why that is called out here?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 11, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:40:04', null),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 12, 1, null, 99, '2022-11-04 07:35:58', '<p>Hezron leads to the line of David.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 13, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:40:09', null),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 14, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:40:12', null),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 15, 1, null, 99, '2022-11-04 07:45:35', '<p>Question: I wonder how the 33 are counted? If you count all the sons of Leah, and the names of their sons along with the 2 sons of Perez, Dinah and the Canaanite woman it comes to 33, but since the sons of Leah had children, it would seem there were other women not counted? She would the Canaanite woman and Dinah be counted, but no other women?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 16, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:40:19', null),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 17, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:42:03', null),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 18, 1, null, 99, '2022-11-04 07:51:02', '<p>Question: again with the count - the count of 16 lists all the names given which include 1 sister and 2 grandsons? Why would 1 sister be included, but not the wives?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 19, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:42:09', null),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 20, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:42:13', null),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 21, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:42:23', null);
INSERT INTO `myrevdata` (`myrevid`, `testament`, `book`, `chapter`, `verse`, `highlight`, `marginnote`, `sqn`, `lastupdate`, `myrevnotes`) VALUES
(20, 0, 1, 46, 22, 1, null, 99, '2022-11-04 07:54:53', '<p>Question: To get to this count of 14, we have the sons and their sons, but not even Asenath although she is named. Is this correct? What can be understood from this?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 23, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:42:29', null),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 24, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:42:32', null),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 25, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:42:35', null),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 26, 1, null, 99, '2022-11-29 06:16:17', '<p>More work for me: I&#39;ve counted 3 times, and keep getting 65. What am I missing?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 27, 1, null, 99, '2022-11-05 04:39:39', '<p>More work for me: To get from 66 to 70, which 4 are being added? If you say Joseph and his 2 sons, aren&#39;t we short another person?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 28, 0, null, 99, '2022-11-06 10:26:07', '<p>Goshen is on the east side of the Nile delta.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 46, 34, 4, null, 99, '2022-11-10 04:58:20', '<p>What does it mean, or what is the significance of &quot;...every shepherd is an abomination to the Egyptians.&quot;?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 48, 8, 0, null, 99, '2022-11-11 07:24:36', '<p>Rhetorical question as Jacob just claimed them as his in Genesis 48:5.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 48, 12, 4, null, 99, '2022-11-11 07:27:36', '<p>What is meant by between his knees in this passage?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 48, 15, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:43:08', null),
(20, 0, 1, 48, 16, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:43:10', null),
(20, 0, 1, 48, 19, 0, null, 99, '2022-11-13 06:25:25', '<p>The 2nd son will be greater- would Jesus see that he would be greater than Adam?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 48, 20, 1, null, 99, '2022-07-03 15:43:19', null),
(20, 0, 1, 48, 21, 0, null, 99, '2022-11-13 06:28:51', '<p>So this is how Joseph would know to tell the people to bring his bones back to Canaan.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 48, 22, 4, null, 99, '2022-11-13 07:02:56', '<p>I wonder what this portion is?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 2, 1, null, 99, '2022-09-18 01:41:53', null),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 3, 1, null, 99, '2022-09-18 01:42:00', null),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 4, 1, null, 99, '2022-09-18 01:42:07', null),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 5, 1, null, 99, '2022-09-18 01:42:15', null),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 6, 1, null, 99, '2022-11-21 08:45:05', '<p>Astronomical: Taurus is the closest I can see.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 7, 1, null, 99, '2022-11-13 07:14:52', '<p>Question: After Solomon, when the kingdom&#39;s were split, wasn&#39;t the split 10 tribes ( Which would have included Ephraim and Manassah) vs 2? Weren&#39;t the 2 Judah and Benjamin? Even though Simeon Was South of Judah, wouldn&#39;t it be counted as a northern tribe?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 8, 1, null, 99, '2022-11-17 04:53:34', '<p>Hand will be on the neck-- What does this mean?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 9, 1, null, 99, '2022-09-18 01:41:43', null),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 10, 1, null, 99, '2022-09-18 01:40:58', null),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 11, 1, null, 99, '2022-09-18 01:41:04', null),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 12, 1, null, 99, '2022-09-18 01:41:09', null),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 13, 1, null, 99, '2022-11-21 08:19:54', '<p>Astronomical: I wonder If Zebulun might be associated with Pisces?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 14, 1, null, 99, '2022-11-21 08:35:38', '<p>Astronomical : There are 2 stars near Cancer that are the northern and Southern donkeys.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 15, 1, null, 99, '2022-09-18 01:40:42', null);
INSERT INTO `myrevdata` (`myrevid`, `testament`, `book`, `chapter`, `verse`, `highlight`, `marginnote`, `sqn`, `lastupdate`, `myrevnotes`) VALUES
(20, 0, 1, 49, 16, 1, null, 99, '2022-11-21 08:57:16', '<p>Astronomical: could Dan be associated with Libra? Or, Sagittarius - Serpens is near it.</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 17, 1, null, 99, '2022-09-18 01:40:17', null),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 18, 1, null, 99, '2022-09-18 01:40:23', null),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 19, 1, null, 99, '2022-09-18 01:39:59', null),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 20, 1, null, 99, '2022-09-18 01:39:53', null),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 21, 1, null, 99, '2022-09-18 01:39:37', null),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 22, 1, null, 99, '2022-09-18 01:39:43', null),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 23, 1, null, 99, '2022-09-18 01:39:11', null),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 24, 1, null, 99, '2022-11-21 08:41:25', '<p>Astronomical: could Joseph be associated with Sagitarius?</p>'),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 25, 1, null, 99, '2022-09-18 01:39:22', null),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 26, 1, null, 99, '2022-09-18 01:39:04', null),
(20, 0, 1, 49, 27, 1, null, 99, '2022-09-18 01:38:43', null),
(20, 0, 1, 50, 10, 2, null, 99, '2022-11-21 09:14:58', '<p>Where is the threshing floor of Atad? AKA Abel Mizraim.</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 1, 2, 1, null, 99, '2022-11-29 06:27:43', '<p>The first 6 names are Leah&#39;s sons, then Rachel&#39;s son (and not counting Joseph because he was already in Egypt), but then it goes to Rachel&#39;s handmaid&#39;s sons an lastly Leah&#39;s handmaid&#39;s sons.</p> <p>The sequence is not the order they were born in per Genesis 29.</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 1, 3, 1, null, 99, '2022-09-18 01:45:06', null),
(20, 0, 2, 1, 4, 1, null, 99, '2022-09-18 01:45:14', null),
(20, 0, 2, 1, 9, 5, null, 99, '2022-11-29 06:34:39', '<p>In the commentary it says too might, but looking at the other versions referened, it looks like it should read as mighty.</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 1, 15, 0, null, 99, '2022-12-03 10:16:39', '<p>According to sheknows.com, the meaning of the name Shiphrah is: Handsome, trumpet, that does good.</p> <p>According to Wikopedia, the name of the second midwife, Puah, is a Canaanite name which means &quot;lass&quot; or &quot;little girl&quot;. Note that a son of Puah is listed as a judge in Judges 10:1-2, but I&#39;m not sure if it&#39;s referencing this Puah.</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 2, 15, 2, null, 99, '2022-12-09 04:24:59', '<p>Add a map of where Midian is.</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 2, 16, 4, null, 99, '2022-12-09 04:31:45', '<p>What kind of a priest was he? To Yahweh or false gods? Per Genesis 25:4 Midian was a descendant of Abraham through Keturah.</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 2, 21, 0, null, 99, '2022-12-11 21:35:30', '<p>According to an internet search, Zipporah comes from a root meaning bird.</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 3, 1, 2, null, 99, '2022-12-11 21:31:32', '<p>Add map of Horeb</p> <p>Here is the first time Horeb is mentioned.</p> <p>Reuel (per internet search) means friend to God, and Jethro means abundant.</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 3, 11, 5, null, 99, '2022-12-11 23:24:56', '<p>Bottom of 2nd paragraph where Exod 3 and 4 I referened, only Exod 3 is hyperlinked.</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 4, 24, 5, null, 99, '2022-12-12 01:08:28', '<p>At the bottom of the page is a footnote-a dimmed letter a referencing a work, but the a doesn&#39;t appear above.</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 4, 26, 4, null, 99, '2022-12-12 01:15:09', '<p>I still have trôble with this. Zipporah was a daughter of Jethro, a descendant of Ketura who was married to Abraham after the covenant, so they should all have known about circumcision. Why would this not have been taken care of as a normal course of living? She even knew how to do it. Was Moses the cause of the delay-being raised in Pharoah''s house for 40 years?</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 4, 27, 4, null, 99, '2022-12-12 01:18:37', '<p>Mountain of God always seems to be Horeb. Does this mean Zipporah was not so very far away from Jethro&#39;s hour when she went back?</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 4, 30, 4, null, 99, '2022-12-12 01:19:57', '<p>He did the signs- was the he Aaron or Moses?</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 6, 3, 4, null, 99, '2022-12-23 06:33:43', '<p>In Genesis 15:2-8, Abram had a conversation with Yahweh (in a vision) and called Yahweh, by his name more than once. How could Yahweh&#39;s name not be known to Abram (whose name was changed to Abraham in Genesis 17:5. It&#39;s the same person referred to here.) if he used it himself on his side of the conversation?</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 6, 7, 4, null, 99, '2022-12-23 06:39:50', '<p>&quot;and I will be to you a God, &quot; It seems like either the &quot;G&quot; should be lowercase, or the article &quot;a&quot; might not belong?</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 6, 14, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-13 05:28:09', null);
INSERT INTO `myrevdata` (`myrevid`, `testament`, `book`, `chapter`, `verse`, `highlight`, `marginnote`, `sqn`, `lastupdate`, `myrevnotes`) VALUES
(20, 0, 2, 6, 15, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-13 05:29:20', null),
(20, 0, 2, 6, 16, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-13 05:31:45', null),
(20, 0, 2, 6, 17, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-13 05:31:40', null),
(20, 0, 2, 6, 18, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-13 05:31:42', null),
(20, 0, 2, 6, 19, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-13 05:31:48', null),
(20, 0, 2, 6, 20, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-13 05:31:51', null),
(20, 0, 2, 6, 21, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-13 05:31:31', null),
(20, 0, 2, 6, 22, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-13 05:31:55', null),
(20, 0, 2, 6, 23, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-13 05:31:59', null),
(20, 0, 2, 6, 24, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-13 05:32:01', null),
(20, 0, 2, 6, 25, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-13 05:32:04', null),
(20, 0, 2, 6, 26, 2, null, 99, '2022-12-23 06:57:47', '<p>In Exodus 6:14-26 there are clues about validating the timeframe as to how long the Children of Israel were in Egypt. The genealogy also seems valuable to look at more.</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 6, 30, 4, null, 99, '2022-12-26 05:33:26', '<p>What is Moses&#39; point here? Is he suggesting his fellow Israelites won&#39;t listen to him because he seems like an outsider, and Pharaoh won&#39;t listen to him because he identifies with them?</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 7, 22, 4, null, 99, '2022-12-31 19:08:52', '<p>If Moses caused all the water to turn to blood, how could the magicians do it? It doesn&#39;t say he turned it back, or did he only do the river first, and they would have clean water in vessels to work with?</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 8, 7, 4, null, 99, '2022-12-26 07:14:45', '<p>So... Just more frogs? Like when Aaron stretched his hand a bunch came up, and when the magicians stretched their hands, more came out?</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 8, 22, 0, null, 99, '2022-12-26 07:28:42', '<p>Did the Hebrews experience frogs and lice?</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 9, 10, 0, null, 99, '2022-12-28 10:12:01', '<p>I wonder what animals of the Egyptians remained at that point?</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 9, 33, 4, null, 99, '2022-12-29 05:32:21', '<p>It reads like Moses came to Pharoah, and left him, in his city while the hail was coming down. How was Moses not injured? Also, where did the animals come from? I thought they were already killed in Exodus 9:1-7? Of course, that specified livestock. Could there be other animals that you would have in the field that are NOT livestock?</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 12, 18, 4, null, 99, '2023-01-09 07:16:38', '<p>I wonder how these 7 days point to Jesus?</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 12, 37, 2, null, 99, '2023-01-11 05:05:36', '<p>Look for map of Ramses to Sukkoth</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 12, 40, 5, null, 99, '2023-01-12 05:46:13', '<p>The 2nd bullet says Isaac was 60 when Jacob was born, however the previous bullet counts to Isaac&#39;s weaning. The 5 years from Isaac&#39;s birth to his weaning is getting counted twice.</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 12, 45, 0, null, 99, '2023-01-13 04:50:16', '<p>Naomi was Ruth&#39;s mother-in-law.</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 12, 46, 4, null, 99, '2023-01-13 04:52:36', '<p>I wonder what the significance is of not taking any of the meat out of the house.</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 12, 51, 4, null, 99, '2023-01-13 05:00:02', '<p>In Exodus 12:41-42, the armies of Yahweh lead the Children of Israel. Here it mentions their armies. I wonder what this looked like?</p>'),
(20, 0, 2, 13, 6, 4, null, 99, '2023-01-13 05:19:11', '<p>I wonder why this feast is 7 days- how does it point to Jesus?</p>'),
