(20, 0, 4, 25, 13, 0, null, 99, '2022-04-14 00:35:06', '<p>The sons of Zadok mentioned in Ezekiel 40:46 are in the lineage of Phinehas.</p>'),
(20, 0, 4, 28, 5, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-20 21:59:22', '<p>Note the grain offering- In Genesis 4:3 Cain offered a grain offering and it wasn&rsquo;t accepted; it was not identified as his &ldquo;best&rdquo;.</p>'),
(20, 0, 5, 5, 1, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-20 22:03:54', '<p>This point in Deuteronomy was 40 years after Moses first received the law in Sinai, and many of those people had passed away. The people needed to be reminded.</p>'),
(20, 0, 5, 9, 1, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>A comma would be appropriate after the word today. Israel didn&#39;t cross the Jordan for a couple months. The word today was used for emphasis.</p>'),
(20, 0, 5, 14, 21, 0, null, 99, '2022-03-27 19:36:08', '<p>See MyREV Commentary Exodus 23:19</p>'),
(20, 0, 6, 3, 10, 4, null, 99, '2022-01-16 16:17:21', '<p>I haven&#39;t been able to figure our where the Perizzites and Gergashites were located</p>'),
(20, 0, 6, 4, 1, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>In this chapter, the phrase &quot;cross over&quot; appears something like 12 times.</p>'),
(20, 0, 6, 4, 8, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>See also verse 20. There were these 12 stones in the water, in verse 20 they are in the camp on the west side in Gilgal.</p>'),
(20, 0, 6, 4, 9, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>The 12 stones placed in the river were Joshua&#39;s idea- it doesn&#39;t say God told him.</p>'),
(20, 0, 6, 4, 10, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>See Deuteronomy 32:44 and 47. There was a discussion between Joshua and Moses.</p>'),
(20, 0, 6, 4, 20, 0, null, 99, '2021-11-06 14:40:10', '<p>Gilgal is about 5 miles from the Jordan River.</p>'),
(20, 0, 6, 5, 2, 0, null, 99, '2021-10-07 00:54:08', '<p>A second time relates to the nation.</p>'),
(20, 0, 6, 9, 1, 0, null, 99, '2021-11-10 02:22:34', '<p>Canaan was a son of Ham.</p>'),
(20, 0, 6, 13, 14, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-16 16:18:35', '<p>13:14 and 13:33 both mention the tribe of Levi receiving no land inheritance</p>'),
(20, 0, 6, 13, 33, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-05 15:10:19', '<p>13:14 and 13:33 both mention the tribe of Levi receiving no land inheritance</p>'),
(20, 0, 6, 15, 1, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-06 00:06:08', '<p><a href="https://www.dropbox.com/s/t7lktq0rh3tjc3k/4.1%20Tribal%20Allotments%20-%20with%20highlights.jpg?dl=0" target="_blank">Satellite Bible Atlas Map 4.1 - with highlights</a></p>'),
(20, 0, 7, 10, 1, 4, null, 99, '2022-12-03 09:58:48', '<p>Is this Puah one of the 2 midwives mentioned in Exodus 1:15?</p>'),
(20, 0, 7, 19, 14, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-16 16:15:39', '<p>For map containing Gibeah, click below</p> <p><a href="https://ucb21a1af2462d8993eeb5dff489.previews.dropboxusercontent.com/p/thumb/ABTjQpoEnnEMURLukmVDAMWrhdCDKMfwZasfLHzeUR97eCZ3kDh3hU9uzoHN6aSygsnNyuJidztyW1GvTtifwubZhMi1nBwoNmXlOnaN-W7py_uuV1nDPSVpWPrEGBc5eKGCJIa2YLrkp0wvvTUcB2wqVyRvnZPhG5bAlNxFQg_aJDUwh6-hU_aZKhwOW2_JdL-djmOYmvbCUbeL2JEA-UpHjiDtdAjJEgHiMDishNDvI3H3Y_Q-2kET8hd9mFUc1LYpGqOxHeO_ILTthBrzrzBt216W-QCyUaO62-LEcUFFgC1xBYjAtAq00dmBMdu_XIz__008oCdCkZRKjSeULN9mk1TL1M34BzcE-lZDBX32ZA/p.jpeg?fv_content=true&size_mode=5" target="_blank">https://ucb21a1af2462d8993eeb5dff489.previews.dropboxusercontent.com/p/thumb/ABTjQpoEnnEMURLukmVDAMWrhdCDKMfwZasfLHzeUR97eCZ3kDh3hU9uzoHN6aSygsnNyuJidztyW1GvTtifwubZhMi1nBwoNmXlOnaN-W7py_uuV1nDPSVpWPrEGBc5eKGCJIa2YLrkp0wvvTUcB2wqVyRvnZPhG5bAlNxFQg_aJDUwh6-hU_aZKhwOW2_JdL-djmOYmvbCUbeL2JEA-UpHjiDtdAjJEgHiMDishNDvI3H3Y_Q-2kET8hd9mFUc1LYpGqOxHeO_ILTthBrzrzBt216W-QCyUaO62-LEcUFFgC1xBYjAtAq00dmBMdu_XIz__008oCdCkZRKjSeULN9mk1TL1M34BzcE-lZDBX32ZA/p.jpeg?fv_content=true&size_mode=5</a></p>'),
(20, 0, 9, 6, 17, 0, null, 99, null, '<p><span style="color:#27AE60;"><span style="background-color:#ECF0F1;">Gath is about 1/3 of the way down from the top of the Dead Sea, and close to the left side of the map. Ekron is north of Gath,</span></span></p> <p><img alt="Gath" height="1139" src="http://ucb21a1af2462d8993eeb5dff489.previews.dropboxusercontent.com/p/thumb/ABTjQpoEnnEMURLukmVDAMWrhdCDKMfwZasfLHzeUR97eCZ3kDh3hU9uzoHN6aSygsnNyuJidztyW1GvTtifwubZhMi1nBwoNmXlOnaN-W7py_uuV1nDPSVpWPrEGBc5eKGCJIa2YLrkp0wvvTUcB2wqVyRvnZPhG5bAlNxFQg_aJDUwh6-hU_aZKhwOW2_JdL-djmOYmvbCUbeL2JEA-UpHjiDtdAjJEgHiMDishNDvI3H3Y_Q-2kET8hd9mFUc1LYpGqOxHeO_ILTthBrzrzBt216W-QCyUaO62-LEcUFFgC1xBYjAtAq00dmBMdu_XIz__008oCdCkZRKjSeULN9mk1TL1M34BzcE-lZDBX32ZA/p.jpeg?fv_content=true&amp;size_mode=5" width="807" /></p>');
INSERT INTO `myrevdata` (`myrevid`, `testament`, `book`, `chapter`, `verse`, `highlight`, `marginnote`, `sqn`, `lastupdate`, `myrevnotes`) VALUES
(20, 0, 9, 13, 1, 0, null, 99, '2022-08-28 15:37:45', '<p>John taught on ch 13 and 14 on Sunday 8/28/22</p>'),
(20, 0, 9, 14, 18, 0, null, 99, '2022-08-28 15:42:51', '<p>This was kind of &quot;religious&quot;, instead of going with what he already had. This delayed getting his troops to the battle.</p>'),
(20, 0, 10, 22, 12, 0, null, 99, '2022-11-02 00:32:30', '<p>Darkness- the point being you can&#39;t see through it</p>'),
(20, 0, 10, 22, 26, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-20 21:55:42', '<p>See Psalm 18:25</p>'),
(20, 0, 11, 9, 4, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>David made mistakes, but repented.</p>'),
(20, 0, 11, 12, 11, 0, null, 99, '2022-08-23 23:59:10', '<p>A scorpion is a kind of whip with sharp things embedded in it.</p>'),
(20, 0, 14, 11, 6, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-06 00:16:35', '<p>See <a href="https://www.dropbox.com/s/sczxdh3zn2jtu3d/6.1%20Division%20of%20Kingdom.jpg?dl=0">Satellite Bible Atlas Map 6-1</a></p>'),
(20, 0, 14, 18, 1, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-26 01:27:40', '<p>Ungodly alliance</p>'),
(20, 0, 14, 18, 28, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-26 01:29:30', '<p>God&#39;s prophet said- don&#39;t go</p>'),
(20, 0, 14, 29, 1, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-20 22:27:06', '<p>Abijah means &quot;my father is Yahweh&quot;.</p> <p>Note: this Zechariah is not the same one that wrote the book &ndash; the timing is about 200 yrs off.</p>'),
(20, 0, 14, 29, 12, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-14 01:09:48', '<p>More work can be done, butvsone of these names are listed to validate that they were of the tribe of Levi.</p>'),
(20, 0, 14, 29, 21, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-14 01:11:34', '<p>This was not of the pattern of any of the specified offerings, but was a unique special offering.</p>'),
(20, 0, 14, 29, 34, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-14 01:17:50', '<p>It is not stated, but had to have been made known by revelation of some sort. In ch 30 There are specifics that deviate from the specifics of the Law also. God &#39;winked&#39; at the rules so he could accept these actions because of his mercy and because of the hearts of the people involved.</p>'),
(20, 0, 17, 4, 14, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>This time period was after Jeremia who prophesied that the Jews would suvive and there would be a future and redemption for them</p>'),
(20, 0, 17, 9, 21, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-20 22:12:09', '<p>Adar is 1 month before Nisan</p>'),
(20, 0, 18, 1, 17, 0, null, 99, '2021-11-24 01:12:50', '<p>Chaldeans were from Babylon</p>'),
(20, 0, 19, 1, 1, 0, null, 99, '2021-12-29 01:16:45', '<p>Benefits to Psalms</p> <p>1) Help with how to pray</p> <p>2</p> <p>3</p> <p>4</p> <p>5) Like Ephesians 4- help with godly behavior</p> <p>6) Express certainty of hope</p> <p>7) Sentiment and reflection</p> <p>8)</p>'),
(20, 0, 19, 3, 2, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>Selah is a musical term, and relates to suspension of music, or a pause.</p>'),
(20, 0, 19, 18, 25, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-20 21:56:11', '<p>See 2 Samuel 22:26</p>'),
(20, 0, 19, 19, 14, 0, null, 99, '2022-06-26 15:03:13', '<p>Meditation comes from the same Hebrew wordas used in Joshua 1:8, see commentary Joshua 1:8</p>'),
(20, 0, 19, 23, 1, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>Shepherds were regarded in Israel,</p>'),
(20, 0, 19, 23, 2, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>Sheep won&#39;t lay down unless they feel safe.</p>'),
(20, 0, 19, 23, 4, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>The rod was like a club, and was an offensive weapon.</p>'),
(20, 0, 19, 46, 1, 0, null, 99, '2022-05-22 16:32:42', '<p>According to Bullinger, this was likely written during the time of Hezekiah and the attacks from Sennecherib(sp? Fellowhip note)</p>'),
(20, 0, 19, 91, 1, 0, null, 99, '2021-10-03 14:58:28', '<p>Psalmist speaking</p>'),
(20, 0, 19, 91, 2, 0, null, 99, '2021-10-03 14:58:55', '<p>Messiah speaking</p>'),
(20, 0, 19, 91, 3, 0, null, 99, '2021-10-03 14:59:33', '<p>Back to Psalmist</p>'),
(20, 0, 19, 91, 11, 5, null, 99, '2022-10-29 01:26:23', '<p>The commentary mentions where Psa 91:11 is quoted on Matt and Luke, but in both cases the quote extends to Psa 91:12 also.</p>'),
(20, 0, 19, 91, 14, 0, null, 99, '2021-10-03 15:00:08', '<p>God speaking</p>'),
(20, 0, 23, 7, 12, 0, null, 99, '2021-12-15 01:17:50', '<p>Ahaz already gave the temple gold to Assyria</p>');
INSERT INTO `myrevdata` (`myrevid`, `testament`, `book`, `chapter`, `verse`, `highlight`, `marginnote`, `sqn`, `lastupdate`, `myrevnotes`) VALUES
(20, 0, 23, 7, 16, 0, null, 99, '2022-03-29 23:59:46', '<p>This would put it around 737 BC.</p>'),
(20, 0, 23, 40, 19, 0, null, 99, '2022-03-09 01:20:40', '<p>The silver chains were to keep the statue from falling over.</p>'),
(20, 0, 23, 40, 26, 0, null, 99, '2022-03-09 01:23:56', '<p>The stars were considered an army.</p>'),
(20, 0, 23, 41, 2, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-23 16:26:34', '<p>From the east- pagan rulers</p>'),
(20, 0, 23, 41, 7, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-23 16:25:22', '<p>But-- they are building idols</p>'),
(20, 0, 23, 41, 14, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-23 16:30:12', '<p>Worm- represents our weaknesses</p>'),
(20, 0, 23, 50, 7, 0, null, 11, '2021-11-07 05:48:41', '<p>Flint - Can&#39;t allow being pulled down--be resolute</p>'),
(20, 0, 23, 52, 13, 0, null, 12, null, '<p>This was likely after the Assyrian attack.</p>'),
(20, 0, 23, 60, 7, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-19 05:37:29', '<p>Not sure it&#39;s referencing the same one, but Nebaioth was the first born son of Ishmael.</p>'),
(20, 0, 23, 62, 4, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>&quot;Things to Come&quot; page 573 cites Peters as saying &quot;In the usage of the east when a king entered his capitol to rule therefrom, or a Prince ascended the throne, it was represented under the figure of a marriage, I.e. he was wedded, intimately and permanently united to the city, or throne, or people...&quot;</p>'),
(20, 0, 24, 31, 16, 0, null, 99, '2021-12-15 01:08:06', '<p>Israel and Judah</p>'),
(20, 0, 24, 34, 11, 0, null, 99, '2022-11-20 16:15:56', '<p>Doh!</p>'),
(20, 0, 24, 34, 16, 0, null, 99, '2022-11-20 16:16:47', '<p>Problem!</p>'),
(20, 0, 27, 7, 4, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-29 14:42:45', '<p>Reminds me of Facebook, or social media.</p>'),
(20, 0, 27, 7, 5, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-29 14:44:20', '<p>Reminds me of Apple, expensive enough to be devicive, not affordable for many people.</p>'),
(20, 0, 27, 7, 6, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-29 14:45:48', '<p>Dominion, reminds me of Google. Who has not heard of it, and how much does it wnow about people?</p>'),
(20, 0, 27, 7, 7, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-29 14:48:11', '<p>This one reminds me of Netflix, or streaming video services. How much have they changed the world? Perhaps it includes broadcast media at a broader level.</p>'),
(20, 0, 28, 6, 7, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-16 16:15:48', '<p>At fellowship, someone referenced 2 Kings ch 14-17</p>'),
(20, 0, 29, 1, 1, 0, null, 99, '2022-02-13 16:03:31', '<p>This book is predominately about end times prophecy</p>'),
(20, 0, 36, 3, 9, 0, null, 13, null, '<p>In &quot;Things to Come&quot; by J. Dwight Pentecost, page 490, item S he implies a single language referencing only this verse.</p>'),
(20, 0, 38, 5, 11, 0, null, 99, '2022-06-15 00:09:30', '<p>Shinar is in Babylon.</p>'),
(20, 0, 38, 14, 8, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-20 22:22:29', '<p>See John 7:38 &ndash; Jesus is the living water</p>'),
(20, 1, 40, 5, 3, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>Blessed-The Hebew word doesn&#39;t have a good English equivalent. It implies recognition that God is involved.</p>'),
(20, 1, 40, 5, 43, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-26 01:32:59', '<p>Jehosaphat should have not partnered with Ahab</p>'),
(20, 1, 40, 5, 44, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-26 01:34:57', '<p>Give enemies of God an opportunity to know God.</p>'),
(20, 1, 40, 7, 27, 0, null, 99, '2022-11-27 17:26:24', '<p>Note that the wind blowing and beating here is less intense than the words in Matt 7:25.</p>'),
(20, 1, 42, 3, 37, 0, null, 99, '2022-05-18 20:19:00', '<p>In Genesis 5, it&#39;s Kenan, not Cainan.</p>'),
(20, 1, 42, 3, 38, 0, null, 99, '2022-05-18 20:53:20', '<p>In Genesis 5:6, Enos is spelled Enosh.</p>'),
(20, 1, 42, 23, 26, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>This account jumps from Tuesday, immediately into Wednesday, with no information about the time between.</p>'),
(20, 1, 42, 23, 33, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>Malefactors = Greek kakourgos - evil worker (per Youngs concordance)</p>');
INSERT INTO `myrevdata` (`myrevid`, `testament`, `book`, `chapter`, `verse`, `highlight`, `marginnote`, `sqn`, `lastupdate`, `myrevnotes`) VALUES
(20, 1, 42, 23, 39, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>It was one malefactor (evil worker, evil doer) that rebuked the other malefactor.</p>'),
(20, 1, 42, 23, 40, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>Same condemnation - John 8:30 shows Jesus being accused of being a malefactor.</p>'),
(20, 1, 43, 4, 4, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-16 16:12:26', '<p>It was much more common for Jews to go east to the other side of the Jordan to travel between these points to avoid the Samaritans.</p>'),
(20, 1, 43, 4, 5, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-06 00:11:51', '<p>This would be near Shechem per text in Satellite Bible Atlas pg 24, referencing <a href="http://www.dropbox.com/s/btc7hffqmibszuq/2.3%20Jacob%20and%20Joseph%20with%20highlights.jpg?dl=0">Satellite Bible Atlas Map 2-3</a> blue route line</p>'),
(20, 1, 43, 4, 10, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-16 16:25:10', '<p>Jeremiah 2:13</p>'),
(20, 1, 43, 7, 1, 0, null, 99, '2022-08-30 23:54:38', '<p>Galilee means circle or circuit and covers the areas all around the lake.</p> <p>The Saducees were in control. Jsus healed a nan on the Sabbath, and then told him to pick up his bed which was work.</p>'),
(20, 1, 43, 7, 2, 0, null, 99, '2022-08-30 23:56:27', '<p>The trip from Galilee to Jerusalem was a 3 day trip, so many times, Jews might go only 1 time instead of the 3 times the law called for.</p>'),
(20, 1, 43, 7, 5, 0, null, 99, '2022-08-30 23:58:54', '<p>There would have been a personal sting for Jesus that his brothers didn&#39;t believe him.</p>'),
(20, 1, 43, 7, 12, 0, null, 99, '2022-08-31 00:05:07', '<p>See Proverbs 28:12.</p>'),
(20, 1, 43, 12, 27, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-18 15:08:05', '<p>This was on Sunday Nisan 11, his last words to people in the temple.</p>'),
(20, 1, 43, 12, 36, 0, null, 99, '2022-09-18 15:11:29', '<p>He was never in public in Jerusalem after this.</p>'),
(20, 1, 43, 20, 24, 0, null, 99, '2022-08-07 15:08:20', '<p>The name Thomas comes from a Hebrew word (or Aramaic) meaning twin or double. Didymus is from the Greek and also means twin.</p>'),
(20, 1, 44, 3, 6, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>Notes</p>'),
(20, 1, 44, 4, 36, 0, null, 99, '2022-04-26 18:02:24', '<p>Barnabas and John Mark were cousins from Cyprus.</p>'),
(20, 1, 44, 12, 19, 0, null, 99, '2022-04-20 00:20:17', '<p>There were 16 guards?</p>'),
(20, 1, 44, 13, 1, 0, null, 99, '2021-10-07 23:57:50', '<p>Written around 48-49 AD, consistent with the timing of the book of Galatians.</p>'),
(20, 1, 44, 15, 3, 0, null, 99, '2021-10-08 00:00:28', '<p>The councils 4 items are directed towards Gentile believers that came from an idolatrous past.</p>'),
(20, 1, 44, 16, 3, 0, null, 99, '2021-10-06 00:15:18', '<p>It&#39;s possible Paul had this done to protect Timothy, or possibly to avoid confrontation like they had on the first itinerary. It&#39;s also possible it would have aided in getting access.</p>'),
(20, 1, 44, 16, 9, 0, null, 99, '2022-04-19 23:48:58', '<p>The clothing a Macedonian man would wear was unique.</p>'),
(20, 1, 44, 16, 14, 0, null, 99, '2021-10-06 00:24:12', '<p>Lydia was a &quot;God-Fearer&quot;</p>'),
(20, 1, 44, 18, 25, 0, null, 99, '2021-10-13 00:06:08', '<p>Intensely eager = boiling over per Sue C 10/12/21</p>'),
(20, 1, 44, 18, 26, 0, null, 99, '2021-10-13 00:08:10', '<p>It was a risk to speak of Jesus in the synagogue. (ask Paul ☺)</p>'),
(20, 1, 45, 7, 17, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>This use of &quot;I&quot; relates to the inner self.</p>'),
(20, 1, 46, 1, 2, 0, null, 99, '2022-03-23 00:56:22', '<p>Showing people directing their prayer to Jesus.</p>'),
(20, 1, 46, 1, 12, 0, null, 99, '2021-11-07 16:30:34', '<p>Cephas is Peter&#39;s Hebrew name. That group of people would have had Me e ish backgrounds.</p> <p>Apollo was an orator.</p>'),
(20, 1, 46, 3, 9, 0, null, 99, '2021-11-17 01:38:10', '<p>We = Paul, Silas, Timothy, whoever is with him</p> <p>You = the Corinthian Church</p>'),
(20, 1, 46, 11, 20, 0, null, 99, '2022-04-10 15:28:37', '<p>For logistical reasons, it would have been an infrequent event.</p>'),
(20, 1, 46, 13, 10, 0, null, 99, '2022-06-01 00:46:43', '<p>Completeness likely refers to the eternal kingdom</p>'),
(20, 1, 46, 14, 18, 0, null, 99, '2022-06-01 00:23:32', '<p>You all= any of you</p>'),
(20, 1, 46, 14, 32, 0, null, 99, '2022-06-01 00:32:04', '<p>The person who does the prophesying chooses to do it and how.</p>');
INSERT INTO `myrevdata` (`myrevid`, `testament`, `book`, `chapter`, `verse`, `highlight`, `marginnote`, `sqn`, `lastupdate`, `myrevnotes`) VALUES
(20, 1, 48, 3, 8, 0, null, 99, '2021-11-21 17:59:53', '<p>Declared to Abraham ahead of time-- refers to Isaac being saved from being sacrificed.</p>'),
(20, 1, 48, 3, 17, 0, null, 99, '2022-03-08 21:49:08', '<p>The commentary for Exodus 12:40 suggests the slavery in Egypt lasted no more than 139 years.</p>'),
(20, 1, 48, 4, 22, 0, null, 99, '2021-10-10 15:16:56', '<p>This completely ignores the 6 sons with Ketura.</p>'),
(20, 1, 48, 4, 24, 0, null, 99, '2021-10-10 15:18:15', '<p>For Law, see Exodus. Chapters 20-23.</p>'),
(20, 1, 50, 1, 1, 0, null, 99, '2022-03-23 00:48:18', '<p>Philippi was established as a place for retired Roman soldiers. Their primary language would have been Latin. Later believers like Lydia came, and their language would have been Greek. Paul was multi-lingual and would have written in Greek.</p>'),
(20, 1, 50, 3, 2, 0, null, 99, '2022-03-23 00:05:20', '<p>Contains the picture of a viscous dog that would follow you, then attack you from the back.</p>'),
(20, 1, 50, 3, 3, 0, null, 99, '2022-03-23 00:06:29', '<p>Confidence in the flesh meaning that A person was born Jewish.</p>'),
(20, 1, 50, 3, 5, 0, null, 99, '2022-03-23 00:39:20', '<p>Paul spoke Hebrew (along with Greek), but speaking Hebrew kind of set him apart as being more sophisticated somehow. He points out that doesn&#39;t matter to him.</p>'),
(20, 1, 51, 1, 15, 0, null, 99, '2022-11-27 16:43:08', '<p>Think in terms of how wisdom is described in the old testament. Also note, the context is the resurrected and exhaulted Christ.</p>'),
(20, 1, 52, 5, 6, 0, null, 99, '2021-11-07 05:58:12', '<p>Consider how the adversary has us blaming each other for things he causes.</p>'),
(20, 1, 58, 4, 8, 0, null, 99, '2022-03-15 02:58:00', '<p>Joshua 23:14</p>'),
(20, 1, 58, 6, 20, 0, null, 99, '2022-04-06 22:58:41', '<p>See Genesis 14:17-24</p>'),
(20, 1, 58, 11, 22, 0, null, 99, '2022-05-17 00:00:39', '<p>Genesis 50:25-26</p>'),
(20, 1, 58, 11, 25, 0, null, 99, '2022-05-17 00:06:42', '<p>Exodus 2:11?</p>'),
(20, 1, 66, 6, 6, 3, null, 99, '2022-09-10 05:14:04', '<p>Prophets might not understand the words they are writing, and the words could apply to future events. At first when I read this, I didn&#39;t understand it. Then I realized it absolutely applies to our day and time. The oil probably does feel hurt when nutritionists call it fat.</p>'),
(20, 1, 66, 12, 16, 0, null, 99, '2022-06-15 00:26:07', '<p>The woman is Israel.</p>'),
(20, 1, 66, 13, 11, 0, null, 99, '2022-06-15 00:28:21', '<p>This is the False Prophet.</p>'),
(20, 4, 13, 1, 1, 0, null, 99, '2022-10-24 01:15:51', '<p>In the reference to Ecclesiastes2:14 at the end of the first paragraph, it suggets the text reads &quot;happening happens&quot; where it currently reads &quot;event happens&quot;.</p> <p>Also in the second to the last paragraph, where there I a hyperlink to the REV search tool, when I click it (using an android tablet) my REV crashes.</p>'),
