(27, 1, 58, 12, 1, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-17 12:11:46', '<p>Hebrews chapter 12 begins with referring to the cloud of witnesses from previous chapter. This includes the following people who had faith, believing, trust in God:</p> <ol> <li>Chapter 11, verse:</li> <li>verse 4, Abel (offered unto God a more excellent sacifice)</li> <li>verse 5, Enoch (was removed from pains of the enemy death &ndash; Enoch pleased God)</li> <li>verse 7, Noah (prepared an ark resulting in saving all living mankind who believed God)</li> <li>verse 8 and 17, Abraham (obeyed God &ndash; journeyed into a foreign country in search for God&rsquo;s Promised Land); (offered up Isaac as a sacrifice to God).</li> <li>verse 11, Sara (at very old age, conceived &amp; delivered a child [Isaac &ndash; who was in the Christ line])</li> <li>verse 20, Isaac (Isaac blessed Jacob and Esau concerning things to come in the future)</li> <li>verse 21, Jacob (when Jacob was on his death bed, blessed each of Joseph&rsquo;s sons</li> <li>verse 22, Joseph (when his end was near, prophesied the children of Israel&rsquo;s exodus out of Egypt to the Promised Land, and made arrangements for his own burial)</li> <li>verse 23 and 24 and 27 and 28 and 29, Moses (v. 23-Moses, at birth, was hid for 3 months to preserve his life for God); (v. 24-as a young man refused to be called Pharoah&rsquo;s daughter&rsquo;s son); (v. 27-Moses forsook Egypt and did not fear the king of Egypt); (v. 28- Moses kept the Passover &amp; sprinkling of blood on doorposts); (v. 29- Moses led people through Red Sea as on dry land); (v. 30-Moses led believers at walls of Jericho &ndash; marching around city for 7 days, then walls of Jericho fell).</li> <li>verse 31, Rahab (Rahab the prostitute peacefully hid God&rsquo;s spies in her house)</li> <li>verse 32, Gideon, Barak, Samson, Jepthah, David, Samuel, the Prophets (conquered kingdoms, enforced righteousness, obtained promises, shut the mouths of lions, quenched the power of fire, escaped edge of swords, from weakness were made strong, became strong in war, caused enemy armies to run away).</li> <li>verse 35, women (some women received back their dead by resurrection; others were tortured, not accepting release by captors &ndash; looking toward resurrection of sheep [just] in the future).</li> <li>verse 36 and 37, others (experienced mockings and floggings and being imprisoned, murdered, being destitute, afflicted and mistreated, wandered in deserts &amp; mountains without homes</li> <li>verse 39, these ALL (having trusted God did not yet receive God&rsquo;s redemption. are commended for their lives of believing God).</li> </ol>'),
