(41, 1, 42, 16, 8, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-06 21:51:23', '<p>I really think &ldquo;generation&rdquo; here should be &ldquo;lifetime&rdquo;. They are more prudent in their lifetime, than the sons of light. I don&rsquo;t know what it means to be prudent in ones generation. Does not make much sense.</p>'),
(41, 1, 42, 16, 9, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-06 21:53:38', '<p>I love what Alfred Plummer says in the ICC, &ldquo;The steward secured a home for a time; but a wise use of opportunities may secure a home for eternity.&rdquo;</p> <p><strong>unrighteous wealth</strong>: v. 11 shows that it is certainly possible to be faithful with unrighteous wealth (seen by the conditional &ldquo;if&rdquo;). Therefore, we should not understand it to mean &ldquo;sinful&rdquo; wealth, but rather &ldquo;temporal&rdquo; and &ldquo;fleeting&rdquo; wealth.</p>'),
(41, 1, 42, 16, 23, 4, null, 99, '2022-01-06 21:53:49', '<p>What is translated as &ldquo;the grave&rdquo; here is hades. However, we know from Revelation that Death and Hades (or the grave) are thrown into the lake of fire. Therefore, this parable does not make sense if we are to understand this torment as going on in the grave. But rather, this torment is describing the lake of fire, after the great judgement has occured (see v. 26).</p> <p>This is the only occurance in the entire NT or OT in which Hades is spoken of as a place of torment, and it is in a parable. So, we should not overide the hundreds of other verses that believe it to be the grave.</p>'),
(41, 1, 42, 16, 31, 1, null, 99, null, '<p>The main spiritual point is that there is no second chance of salvation after death.</p>'),
(41, 1, 42, 17, 19, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-06 21:54:30', '<p>&quot;Your trust has saved you.&quot; He was already physically cleansed before he displayed faith. Therefore this salvation that occurs here is not physical but eternal.</p> <p>Running to Jesus is all that matters, the 9 will look back on their life and say the greatest moment of my life was being healed, but the one will look back and say that the greatest moment of his life was meeting the one who could heal. FROM BIBLICAL STORY.ORG - BAYLIS</p> <p>Compare this with Luke 15, God desires the one who will repent, not the 99 who need no repentance!</p>'),
(41, 1, 42, 19, 11, 5, null, 99, '2022-01-06 21:54:41', '<p>Jesus departure, not his return, inaugurate his kingdom. However, the fullness of his kingdom will be realized when he returns.</p> <p>This parable clearly explains how Jesus is the Messiah, yet how this timeline will unfold.</p> <p>The &#39;authority over the cities&#39; is not given until the king returns.</p>'),
