(41, 1, 44, 2, 34, 4, null, 99, '2022-08-05 15:53:58', '<p>Somebody&rsquo;s response:</p> <p>According to those who teach that the soul REMAINS with the decaying body, this verse proves to THEM beyond any doubt that no man has ascended into heaven.</p> <p>But in truth, this verse is taken out of its CONTEXT. And when we read the context of this verse it is clearly seen that Peter is teaching the Jews that it was NOT David who ascended into heaven, but rather, it was our Messiah Jesus whom the Jews killed that God raised from the dead and who has now ascended into heaven.</p> <p>Peter makes it clear that the decayed body of David is still yet in the grave. So all this verse proves is that the dead BODIES are in the graves and NOT the SOUL and SPIRIT of those who were dwelling in the tabernacle of those physical mortal bodies. And this could be one of the reasons why the Jehovah&#39;s Witnesses TRY to prove that there is NO BODILY resurrection of Jesus or us. It is like the Roman Catholic Church that creates another man-made doctrine called baptizing babies to TRY and hide their error of a previous doctrine called the doctrine of original sin. One false doctrine leads to another false doctrine.</p>'),
