(41, 1, 54, 5, 3, 1, null, 99, '2022-11-07 02:34:08', '<p>1 Timothy 5:3 states, &ldquo;Honor widows who are real widows.&rdquo; &ldquo;Honor&rdquo; in this verse refers to financial support, as is evident in the contrast in v. 4 regarding widows who have children or grandchildren who can support them (cf. vv. 8 and 16, regarding the obligation to provide financial support to one&rsquo;s widowed relatives) and the statement in v. 5 that by &ldquo;real widows&rdquo; Paul refers to widows who are &ldquo;left all alone.&rdquo; In Paul&rsquo;s day, most women were dependent on their families for financial support. Widows without supporting relatives lacked means of financial support in a way that widowers did not. Consequently Paul made these provision for widows and not for widowers, who could work outside the home and as a group did not have nearly the need for support as widows. (From Philip Payne)</p>'),
