(49, 0, 23, 9, 6, 2, null, 99, '2022-04-15 10:58:31', '<p>The Hebrew word translated &ldquo;age&rdquo; (or &ldquo;everlasting&rdquo; in most Bibles), is `ad (#05703 עַד), and refers to something that lasts a long time or forever, or something that endures for an age or ages, and that can be of the past or future. Thus, when Habakkuk 3:6 speaks of the mountains that will be shattered at some point in the future, they are called &ldquo;the ancient mountains&rdquo; in some translations (cp. NAB; NET), or by hyperbole, &ldquo;the everlasting mountains&rdquo; (cp. KJV).</p>');
