(49, 1, 46, 15, 33, 5, null, 99, '2022-02-14 13:51:04', '<p>In biblical times &ldquo;bad company&rdquo; referred to being with worthless or evil people. Today the &ldquo;company&rdquo; we keep can also include the television and movies we watch, the video games we play, etc., as well as the worthless, ungodly, or evil people we spend time with</p>'),
(49, 1, 47, 1, 23, 0, null, 99, '2022-02-15 05:35:45', '<p>All of us should strive to live such godly lives that our lives can be called upon as a witness for Christ.</p>'),
(49, 1, 47, 2, 14, 2, null, 99, '2022-02-15 05:46:57', '<p>We Christians are not to water down our witness so that we do not offend the unsaved by our smell of death. In fact, the very next verse (2 Cor. 2:17), speaks of those who water down the Word, ostensibly to be accepted by others. Christians smell like death to unbelievers. Hopefully, some of them will recognize that the death they smell is their own, and come to Christ for salvation so they can live forever.</p>'),
(49, 1, 47, 2, 15, 2, null, 99, '2022-02-15 05:39:49', null),
(49, 1, 47, 2, 16, 2, null, 99, '2022-02-15 05:40:02', null),
(49, 1, 47, 4, 16, 2, null, 99, '2022-02-15 14:56:38', '<p>Given those things, Paul was not discouraged. His outward body was getting weaker, but his inner self, his mind, was being renewed day after day, and the renewing of the mind 2 Corinthians 4:16 is similar to the renewing of the mind mentioned in Romans 12:2, which uses the same Greek root word (except Romans uses a noun and Corinthians uses a verb). Paul is encouraged and excited about life and what the Lord is doing in him and in the world, and his &ldquo;inner self&rdquo; was being renewed by that.</p>'),
(49, 1, 47, 5, 4, 1, null, 99, '2022-02-15 16:55:45', null),
(49, 1, 47, 5, 10, 1, null, 99, '2022-02-15 14:58:12', null),
(49, 1, 47, 5, 14, 2, null, 99, '2022-02-15 14:59:08', null),
(49, 1, 47, 5, 15, 2, null, 99, '2022-02-15 14:59:10', null),
(49, 1, 47, 5, 21, 1, null, 99, '2022-02-16 13:49:14', '<p>Sin offering</p>'),
(49, 1, 47, 6, 1, 0, 'Test', 99, '2022-02-17 13:39:42', '<p>The heart is deceitful above all things, and it is exceedingly corrupt&rdquo; (Jer. 17:9)</p>'),
(49, 1, 47, 6, 12, 2, null, 99, '2022-02-17 13:47:21', null),
(49, 1, 47, 7, 1, 1, null, 99, '2022-02-17 15:05:24', null),
(49, 1, 47, 9, 6, 3, null, 99, '2022-02-17 15:07:41', null),
(49, 1, 47, 9, 7, 4, null, 99, '2022-02-17 15:07:51', null),
(49, 1, 47, 9, 10, 2, null, 99, '2022-02-17 15:09:33', null),
(49, 1, 47, 9, 11, 2, null, 99, '2022-02-17 15:09:44', null),
(49, 1, 48, 2, 19, 2, null, 99, '2022-02-20 03:48:13', null),
(49, 1, 48, 4, 5, 4, null, 99, '2022-02-21 02:58:09', null),
(49, 1, 48, 5, 10, 4, null, 99, '2022-02-21 07:30:46', null),
(49, 1, 48, 5, 13, 1, null, 99, '2022-02-21 07:37:01', '<p>We are to love our fellow Christians, and that love is expressed in many different, but visible, ways. If we are focused on &ldquo;one another,&rdquo; that is, on building up the Christian community, we will find life to be much more rewarding than if we are just concerned about ourselves. For example, the specific command to &ldquo;love one another&rdquo; occurs 13 times in the New Testament.</p>'),
(49, 1, 48, 5, 19, 1, null, 99, '2022-02-21 07:46:34', null),
(49, 1, 48, 5, 20, 1, null, 99, '2022-02-21 07:47:49', null),
(49, 1, 48, 5, 21, 2, null, 99, '2022-02-21 07:52:43', '<p>The evidence in this verse will show that it is speaking about having an inheritance in the Kingdom (rewards), not about being saved and being in the Kingdom.</p>'),
(49, 1, 48, 5, 22, 2, null, 99, '2022-02-21 08:01:09', null),
(49, 1, 48, 5, 23, 2, null, 99, '2022-02-21 08:03:37', '<p>True self-control comes from a combination of free-will decisions and the new nature inside that is trying to reproduce itself in outward man. It is, after all, a &ldquo;fruit of the spirit,&rdquo; not a &ldquo;fruit of the will.&rdquo; A commitment to self-control without being motivated by love for others feeds prideful ambition and self-glorification. Christians are not to live like unbelievers who indulge the flesh (Eph. 2:3). Christians are to control themselves (1 Cor. 9:24-27</p>'),
(49, 1, 48, 5, 25, 4, null, 99, '2022-02-21 08:04:37', null),
(49, 1, 48, 6, 6, 0, null, 99, '2022-02-21 08:16:46', '<p>Lenski translates the verse: &ldquo;Moreover, let him who is being instructed in the Word be partaker with the one instructing him in all good things.&rdquo;</p>');
INSERT INTO `myrevdata` (`myrevid`, `testament`, `book`, `chapter`, `verse`, `highlight`, `marginnote`, `sqn`, `lastupdate`, `myrevnotes`) VALUES
(49, 1, 48, 6, 15, 2, null, 99, '2022-02-21 08:22:04', null),
(49, 1, 48, 6, 16, 3, null, 99, '2022-02-21 08:24:27', null),
(49, 1, 49, 1, 1, 0, null, 99, '2022-02-21 15:12:22', '<p>Furthermore, there is a lot about God, Jesus, and spiritual matters, including who we are and what we have in Christ, that cannot be fully understood on a purely intellectual level; they have to be experienced to be fully understood.</p>'),
(49, 1, 49, 1, 3, 2, null, 99, '2022-02-21 17:05:20', null),
(49, 1, 49, 1, 4, 4, null, 99, '2022-02-21 17:16:15', '<p>In other words, before the foundation of the world God planned to have a &ldquo;Christian Church,&rdquo; &ldquo;the Body of Christ,&rdquo; and planned that those people who joined the Church would be saved.</p>'),
(49, 1, 49, 1, 7, 1, null, 99, '2022-02-21 17:26:15', '<p>It took an immense amount of grace for God to do what He did for us&mdash;including have His Son die for us&mdash;when we did so little for Him and deserved so little.</p>'),
(49, 1, 49, 1, 8, 1, 'Grace, wisdom, and insight', 99, '2022-02-21 17:29:03', '<p>God lavished His grace upon us, and when He did, His grace was accompanied by wisdom and insight. In other words, the believer does not have just grace, but the wisdom and insight (or understanding) that comes with the grace. Of course the wisdom and insight are not automatic, the believer has to exercise it and grow in it.</p>'),
(49, 1, 49, 1, 11, 3, null, 99, '2022-02-21 17:56:37', '<p>God planned for the Church, the Body of Christ, before the foundation of the world. This is not &ldquo;predestination,&rdquo; even though many versions use that word.</p>'),
(49, 1, 49, 1, 12, 1, 'Commentary!', 99, '2022-02-21 18:00:10', null),
(49, 1, 49, 1, 13, 1, null, 99, '2022-02-21 18:13:00', '<p>you also.&rdquo; The Good News came to the Jews first, then later to the Gentiles. The addition of this phrase, &ldquo;you also,&rdquo; shows that the majority of Paul&rsquo;s audience was Gentile.</p>'),
(49, 1, 49, 1, 18, 2, null, 99, '2022-02-26 01:24:26', '<p>The Christian&rsquo;s hope is the anchor of their soul (Heb. 6:19), so it is vital that Christians not be unclear about what their hope is. It involves having new bodies like Christ&rsquo;s body, living in the Kingdom of Christ here on a newly regenerated earth, and enjoying the rewards that one has earned for obedience to God.</p>'),
(49, 1, 49, 2, 4, 2, null, 99, '2022-02-22 16:57:50', null),
(49, 1, 49, 2, 5, 4, null, 99, '2022-02-22 16:57:59', null),
(49, 1, 49, 3, 6, 1, null, 99, '2022-02-23 13:53:57', '<p>The point Scripture is making is that now, in union with Christ Jesus, Jews and Gentiles are the same. This was a new revelation and part of the Administration of the Sacred Secret. The Old Testament had foretold that the Gentiles would be blessed by the Messiah (Ps. 102:15; Isa. 2:2-4; 19:23-25; 42:6; 49:6; 51:4-5; 56:3-7; 60:3; 66:18-21; Ezek. 39:21, 27; Micah 4:2; Hag. 2:7; Zech. 8:22), but it never said that the Gentiles would be &ldquo;fellow-heirs&rdquo; and &ldquo;fellow-partakers of the promise.&rdquo;</p>'),
(49, 1, 49, 3, 8, 4, null, 99, '2022-02-23 13:58:05', null),
(49, 1, 49, 3, 9, 4, null, 99, '2022-02-23 14:14:26', null),
(49, 1, 49, 3, 16, 1, null, 99, '2022-02-23 14:20:34', null),
(49, 1, 49, 3, 17, 1, null, 99, '2022-02-23 14:26:32', '<p>The idea conveyed by rhizoō (rooted) is that of being given a source of life-sustaining nourishment and strength. Like a tree that buries its roots deep into the earth to draw necessary nutrients and to provide it with support to remain upright during storms and wind, believers have their source of life-giving nutrients and strength &ldquo;in love.&rdquo;</p> <p>The word themelioō (grounded) in the passive sense means &ldquo;to be provided with a foundation&rdquo; (Theological Dictionary of the New Testament) and it is used to describe the way that believers are like a house that has been built upon a sure foundation&mdash;immovable and unshakeable. Moreover, this idea is depicted in the Gospel of Matthew where themelioō is used to describe the house of the wise person which &ldquo;did not fall because it had been founded [themelioō] on the rock&rdquo; (Matt. 7:25; cp. Luke 6:48).</p>'),
(49, 1, 49, 3, 18, 2, null, 99, '2022-02-13 17:47:37', '<p>Four dimensions</p>'),
(49, 1, 49, 3, 19, 3, null, 99, '2022-02-23 14:27:27', null),
(49, 1, 49, 3, 20, 1, null, 99, '2022-02-23 14:27:35', null),
(49, 1, 49, 4, 3, 2, null, 99, '2022-02-23 15:02:37', '<p>God has given us a list around which Christians should certainly attempt to unify: the &ldquo;seven ones&rdquo; of Ephesians 4:4-6: one body, one spirit, one hope, one Lord, one Faith, one baptism, one God.</p>'),
(49, 1, 49, 4, 9, 1, 'Commentary', 99, '2022-02-23 16:30:56', null),
(49, 1, 49, 4, 10, 1, null, 99, '2022-02-23 16:31:02', null),
(49, 1, 49, 4, 13, 1, 'Commentary', 99, '2022-02-23 16:37:33', null),
(49, 1, 49, 4, 15, 2, null, 99, '2022-02-23 16:40:20', '<p>To &ldquo;grow up&rdquo; into Christ requires mental and spiritual growth, which takes time and effort. It is a process, not an event. Every Christian has &ldquo;baggage,&rdquo; weaknesses, and blind spots that keep them from fully utilizing their ministry and being like Christ. On the Day of Judgment, Jesus Christ will not expect us to be perfect, but he will expect that we have not been content to live with our faults and excuses, but have made a sincere effort to try to live like he did and do our best to be approved by God (2 Tim. 2:15)</p>'),
(49, 1, 49, 4, 16, 2, null, 99, '2022-02-23 16:40:52', null),
(49, 1, 49, 4, 19, 1, null, 99, '2022-02-24 00:49:39', '<p>to engage in.&rdquo; This phrase is translated from the Greek prepositional phrase eis ergasia (#1519 ἐις; #2039έργασία), which literally means &ldquo;for engagement in some activity or behavior with sustained interest&rdquo; (BDAG Greek-English lexicon). Ergasiais often translated as &ldquo;practice&rdquo; (NAB, NET, CSB, ESV) because that brings out the meaning of sustained involvement in the activity and shows that it is not just a one-time occurrence.</p>'),
(49, 1, 49, 4, 27, 1, null, 99, '2022-02-24 01:03:30', null),
(49, 1, 49, 4, 29, 1, null, 99, '2022-02-24 01:14:41', '<p>We are not to speak just to justify ourselves, but the standard we use is, &ldquo;Does it benefit the hearer in some way?&rdquo; What we say is to be helpful in building the other person up.</p>');
