(53, 0, 1, 1, 2, 0, '<span style="font-size:medium"><span new="" roman="" style="font-family:" times=""><span style="color:#000000"><span style="font-style:normal"><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal"><span style="font-weight:400"><span style="white-space:normal"><span style="background-color:#cccccc"><span style="text-decoration-thickness:initial"><span style="text-decoration-style:initial"><span style="text-decoration-color:initial"><span style="font-size:13.5pt">But the earth became...', 99, '2022-09-21 01:24:58', '<p>[EXB] The [or&hellip;the] earth &middot;had no form and was empty [or was a formless void]. Darkness covered the &middot;ocean [deep], and &middot;God&rsquo;s Spirit [or a mighty wind] was &middot;moving [hovering] over the water.</p> <p><a href="https://custance.org/Library/WFANDV/intro.html">https://custance.org/Library/WFANDV/intro.html</a> <span style="font-size:medium"><span new="" roman="" style="font-family:" times=""><span style="color:#000000"><span style="font-style:normal"><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal"><span style="font-weight:400"><span style="white-space:normal"><span style="background-color:#cccccc"><span style="text-decoration-thickness:initial"><span style="text-decoration-style:initial"><span style="text-decoration-color:initial"><span style="font-size:13.5pt">there is, on the basis of the evidence, far more reason</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> <span style="font-size:medium"><span new="" roman="" style="font-family:" times=""><span style="color:#000000"><span style="font-style:normal"><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal"><span style="font-weight:400"><span style="white-space:normal"><span style="background-color:#cccccc"><span style="text-decoration-thickness:initial"><span style="text-decoration-style:initial"><span style="text-decoration-color:initial"><span style="font-size:13.5pt">to translate Gen. 1.2 as &quot;But the earth had become a ruin and a deso</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style="font-size:medium"><span new="" roman="" style="font-family:" times=""><span style="color:#000000"><span style="font-style:normal"><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal"><span style="font-weight:400"><span style="white-space:normal"><span style="background-color:#cccccc"><span style="text-decoration-thickness:initial"><span style="text-decoration-style:initial"><span style="text-decoration-color:initial"><span style="font-size:13.5pt">lation...&quot; than there is for any of the conventional translations in</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> <span style="font-size:medium"><span new="" roman="" style="font-family:" times=""><span style="color:#000000"><span style="font-style:normal"><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal"><span style="font-weight:400"><span style="white-space:normal"><span style="background-color:#cccccc"><span style="text-decoration-thickness:initial"><span style="text-decoration-style:initial"><span style="text-decoration-color:initial"><span style="font-size:13.5pt">our modern versions.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>'),
(53, 0, 1, 1, 27, 0, '<a data-hlite="0" id="hl_53|0|1|1|27" onclick="showhilightdiv(''53|0|1|1|27'', ''/Gen/1/27/0'');" title="Clear">So God created mankind in His own image. In the image of God He created them. Male and female He created them.</a>', 99, '2022-10-26 20:10:00', '<p><a data-hlite="0" id="hl_53|0|1|1|27" onclick="showhilightdiv(''53|0|1|1|27'', ''/Gen/1/27/0'');" title="Clear">God created+He created+He created &gt; mankind+</a><a data-hlite="0" onclick="showhilightdiv(''53|0|1|1|27'', ''/Gen/1/27/0'');" title="Clear">them+Male and female+</a><a data-hlite="0" id="hl_53|0|1|1|27" onclick="showhilightdiv(''53|0|1|1|27'', ''/Gen/1/27/0'');" title="Clear">them</a> <a data-hlite="0" onclick="showhilightdiv(''53|0|1|1|27'', ''/Gen/1/27/0'');" title="Clear">&gt; in His own image + In the image of God</a></p>'),
(53, 0, 1, 5, 2, 0, 'Adam= &ldquo;red earth&quot;', 99, '2022-07-24 21:49:11', null),
(53, 0, 1, 9, 6, 0, '<a data-hlite="0" id="hl_53|0|1|9|6" onclick="showhilightdiv(''53|0|1|9|6'', ''/Gen/9/6/0'');" title="Clear">Whoever sheds the blood of mankind, by mankind is his blood to be shed, for God made mankind in His own image.</a>', 99, '2022-10-26 19:58:10', null),
(53, 0, 1, 14, 13, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-07 18:59:29', '<p>&ldquo;Hebrew&rdquo; 1<sup>st</sup> use in the Bible. &ldquo;Hebrew&rdquo; noun <em>&#39;eber</em> meaning: one who passed over, passer over, one who transits, one who looks at something from both sides. Etymology: From the verb <em>&#39;abar</em> meaning to pass over, to cross over (a river, border, obstacle or terrain). The derived noun <em>&#39;eber</em> describes who ended up on the other side or in the region beyond. Abraham crossed the Euphrates River. Joshua crossed the Jordan River.</p> <p>Josh 3:1And Joshua rose up early in the morning, and they moved from Shittim and came to the Jordan, he and all the children of Israel. They camped there before they crossed over the Jordan.</p>'),
(53, 0, 1, 24, 63, 0, '<h3>Frank Licary&rsquo;s Notes on Genesis 24:63</h3> <img alt="" src="https://www.revisedenglishversion.com/i/redx.png" /><br /> Isaac went out to meditae in the field at the evening.', 99, '2022-06-26 15:30:14', null),
(53, 0, 1, 27, 1, 0, null, 99, '2021-11-02 18:28:34', '<p>Context Gen 26:44 and they became a bitterness of spirit to Isaac and to Rebekah.</p> <p>&ldquo;a bitterness of spirit&rdquo; is the use of &ldquo;spirit&rdquo; (Hebrew: ruach) that refers to acts of the mind, thoughts, attitudes and emotions. Esau&rsquo;s Hittite wives caused hostile, bitter thoughts and bad attitudes toward Isaac and Rebekah.</p>');
