(53, 0, 13, 4, 9, 0, 'Jabez means &ldquo;much distress, hardship, grief, sorrow, pain&rdquo;<br /> Jabez was more honorable than his brothers; but his mother named him Jabez, saying, &ldquo;Because I gave birth to him in much distress, hardship, grief, sorrow, pain.&rdquo;', 99, '2022-11-18 17:40:21', null),
(53, 0, 13, 4, 10, 0, 'Jabez cried out to the God of Israel, saying, &ldquo;Oh that You would indeed bless me and enlarge my property border, and that Your hand would be with me, and You would keep me from evil so that it does not hurt me!&rdquo; And God granted his request.<br /> &nbsp;', 99, '2022-11-18 17:48:51', '<p>Simple prayer. SIB KIS = See it big, keep it simple.</p> <p>1 Chronicles 4:10 Jabez cried out to the God of Israel, saying, &ldquo;Oh that You would indeed bless me and enlarge my property border, and that Your hand would be with me, and You would keep me from evil so that it does not hurt me!&rdquo; And God granted his request.</p> <p>SELAH</p>'),
(53, 0, 18, 28, 1, 0, '<sup>12<a id="c28_v12"></a></sup><a href="https://www.revisedenglishversion.com/Job/chapter28/12" ondblclick="event.stopPropagation();event.preventDefault();" target="_self" title="Click for Commentary">&ldquo;But where can wisdom be found? Where is the place <em>to find</em> understanding?</a>', 99, '2022-11-27 16:14:19', null),
(53, 0, 18, 28, 21, 0, 'Wisdom is personified as a woman here in Job and in Proverbs, the Hebrew word for &ldquo;wisdom&rdquo; is feminine.', 99, '2022-11-27 16:16:36', null),
(53, 0, 19, 2, 7, 0, 'Yahweh said to me [the Messiah], &ldquo;You are My son; today I have become your Father.', 99, '2022-11-02 22:50:32', '<p>In Psalm 2:7, the Messiah is called the &ldquo;Son&rdquo; when he comes into his kingdom, that is, when he takes his full authority in the household of God and takes over the actual rulership of the world. So the Messiah becoming the &ldquo;Son&rdquo; is not at his conception or birth, but at a much later (and still future) time. Thus in Psalm 2:7, the word &ldquo;Son&rdquo; is describing the relationship that the Messiah has with the Father as a fully developed Son, participating in ruling the house.</p>'),
(53, 0, 19, 4, 4, 0, 'Eph 4:26 Be ye angry, and sin not: let not the sun go down upon your wrath.<br /> Lev 19:18 You must not take vengeance, nor hold a grudge against the children of your people, but you must love your neighbor as yourself. I am Yahweh.', 99, '2022-07-17 10:16:37', null),
(53, 0, 19, 5, 6, 0, 'lies= slander Ps 140:3 <a href="https://www.revisedenglishversion.com/Psalms/chapter140/3" ondblclick="event.stopPropagation();event.preventDefault();" target="_blank" title="Click for Commentary">They have sharpened their tongue like a serpent; a viper&rsquo;s poison is under their lips. Selah.</a>', 99, '2022-07-20 20:19:22', '<p>Rom 3:10-18 10 just as it is written, THERE IS NONE RIGHTEOUS, NO, NOT ONE.<br /> 11THERE IS NONE WHO UNDERSTANDS, THERE IS NONE WHO SEEKS FOR GOD. 12 THEY HAVE ALL TURNED ASIDE; TOGETHER THEY HAVE BECOME WORTHLESS. THERE IS NONE WHO IS KIND, NO, NOT SO MUCH AS ONE. [Ps 14:1-3; 53:1-3; Ecc 7:20]<br /> 13 THEIR THROAT IS AN OPEN TOMB. WITH THEIR TONGUES THEY KEEP DECEIVING. THE POISON OF ASPS IS UNDER THEIR LIPS. [Ps 5:9]<br /> 14 THEIR MOUTH IS FULL OF CURSING AND BITTERNESS. [Ps 10:7]<br /> 15 THEIR FEET ARE SWIFT TO SHED BLOOD.<br /> 16 DESTRUCTION AND MISERY ARE IN THEIR WAYS,<br /> 17 AND THE WAY OF PEACE THEY HAVE NOT KNOWN. [ Is 59:7-8]<br /> 18 THERE IS NO FEAR OF GOD BEFORE THEIR EYES. [Ps 36:1]</p>'),
(53, 0, 19, 8, 5, 0, 'lower than angels', 99, '2022-11-26 12:43:47', '<p>7You made him lower than the angels for a little while. You crowned him with glory and honor, and set himf over the works of your hands.</p>'),
(53, 0, 19, 19, 4, 0, 'Rom 10:18 But I say, &ldquo;Did they not hear?&rdquo; Indeed, they have: THEIR VOICE WENT OUT TO ALL THE EARTH, AND THEIR WORDS TO THE ENDS OF THE INHABITED WORLD.', 99, '2022-10-13 08:45:17', '<p>Rom 10:18 NIV: But I ask: Did they not hear? Of course they did: &ldquo;Their voice has gone out into all the earth, their words to the ends of the world.&rdquo; [from Ps 19:4]</p> <p>Rom 1:19-20 because what can be known about God is visible to them, for God has made it visible to them. For since the creation of the world His invisible attributes&mdash;His eternal power and divine nature&mdash;are clearly seen, because they are understood through what He has made, so they are without excuse.</p>'),
(53, 0, 19, 33, 1, 0, 'Exult: be extremely joyful, rejoice, leap for joy', 99, '2022-12-03 15:00:23', null),
(53, 0, 19, 45, 6, 0, '<a data-hlite="0" id="hl_53|1|58|1|8" onclick="showhilightdiv(''53|1|58|1|8'', ''/Heb/1/8/0'');" title="Clear"><strong>Your throne is Ruler for ages and ages, the scepter of uprightness is the scepter of your kingdom.</strong></a>', 99, '2022-11-02 22:37:35', '<p>&ldquo;GOD&rdquo; was a descriptive title applied to a range of authorities, including God, angels, demons, pagan gods, great people, rulers, and people acting with God&rsquo;s authority&mdash;all of those were referred to as &ldquo;GOD.&rdquo; For example, Jesus pointed out that people to whom the Word of God came were called &ldquo;gods&rdquo; (John 10:34-35)</p>'),
(53, 0, 19, 58, 1, 0, '<a data-hlite="0" id="hl_53|0|19|58|1" onclick="showhilightdiv(''53|0|19|58|1'', ''/Ps/58/1/0'');" title="Clear">Do you rulers truly speak righteously? Do you children of men</a> <a data-hlite="0" onclick="showhilightdiv(''53|0|19|58|1'', ''/Ps/58/1/0'');" title="Clear">judge uprightly?</a>', 99, '2022-11-30 17:08:01', '<p>Do you rulers truly speak righteously?<br /> Do you children of men judge uprightly?<br /> NO! In your heart you commit injustices.<br /> You deal out violence with your hands to the land.<br /> The wicked turn aside from the womb. They wander off from the time of their birth, speaking lies.<br /> Their poison is like the poison of a serpent; like a deaf cobra that closes its ear, which does not listen to the voice of snake charmers, who are clever chanters of spells.<br /> Oh God, break their teeth in their mouth.<br /> Oh Yahweh, break out the young lion&rsquo;s fangs.<br /> Let them vanish like water run-off this drains into thirsty ground.<br /> Let their arrows be blunt, pointless, useless shafts.<br /> Let them be like a snail that melts into slime in the sun.<br /> Let them be like a woman&#39;s miscarriage that never sees the sun.<br /> God will sweep them away like a whirlwind, faster than a pot heats over burning thorns.<br /> The righteous will rejoice when they see God&rsquo;s vengeance.<br /> They will wash their feet in the blood of the wicked.<br /> So the people will say, &ldquo;Surely there is a reward for the righteous. Surely there is a God Who judges the earth.&rdquo;<br /> -Psalm 58:1-11</p>'),
(53, 0, 19, 58, 7, 0, '<br /> Let them vanish like water that runs off, drains into thirsty ground. When he aims his arrows, let them be blunt, pointless, useless shafts.', 99, '2022-11-30 16:58:27', null),
