(53, 1, 42, 4, 18, 0, 'LXX Is 61:1-2a The Spirit of the Lord Yahweh is upon me, because Yahweh has anointed me to bring good news to the suffering and afflicted. He has sent me to comfort the brokenhearted, to announce liberty to captives, to open the eyes of the blind, <a data-hlite="0" id="hl_53|0|23|61|2" onclick="showhilightdiv(''53|0|23|61|2'', ''/Isa/61/2/0'');" title="Clear">to proclaim the year of Yahweh&rsquo;s favor.</a>', 99, '2022-12-05 19:32:19', '<p>Jesus also refers to Is 35:4b He [God&rsquo;s Messiah] will come and save you. 5Then the eyes of the blind will be opened and the ears of the deaf will be unstopped. 6Then the lame man will leap like a deer and the tongue of the mute will sing, for waters will break out in the wilderness, and streams in the desert.</p> <p>Mt 11:5 the blind receive their sight, and the lame walk, the people with skin diseasesa are cleansed, and the deaf hear, and the dead are raised, and the poor have good news proclaimed to them.</p>'),
(53, 1, 42, 5, 2, 0, '&ldquo;nets&rdquo; plural vss 2,4,5,6', 99, '2022-10-12 11:14:28', '<p>Lk 5:2, 4, 5, 6 nets (diktya, plural)</p> <p>Jn 21:6, 8, 11 net (diktyon , singular)</p>'),
(53, 1, 42, 5, 7, 0, 'They waved to their partners in the other boat to come help them. They filled both boats, nearly swamping them with the catch.', 99, '2022-10-12 10:37:13', '<p>MSG Lk 5:4-7 Simon said, &ldquo;Master, we&rsquo;ve been fishing hard all night and haven&rsquo;t caught even a minnow. But if you say so, I&rsquo;ll let out the nets.&rdquo; It was no sooner said than done&mdash;a huge haul of fish, straining the nets past capacity. They waved to their partners in the other boat to come help them. They filled both boats, nearly swamping them with the catch.</p>'),
