(53, 1, 45, 12, 19, 0, '<strong>Vengeance is Mine, I will repay [Deut 32:35-36, 43]</strong>', 99, '2022-11-02 20:51:14', '<p>Deut 32:35 <strong>Vengeance is Mine and payback...</strong> the day of their calamity is at hand and the things that are prepared for them are coming swiftly. 36a <strong>Yahweh will vindicate</strong> His people&hellip; 43b...<strong>He will avenge</strong> the blood of His servants. <strong>He will return vengeance</strong> on His adversaries. <strong>He will repay</strong> those who hate Him...</p>'),
(53, 1, 46, 1, 2, 0, 'call on the name of = praying to Jesus; 1st used Genesis 12:8 called on the name of Yahweh.', 99, '2022-03-23 00:58:15', null),
(53, 1, 46, 1, 19, 0, 'Is 29:14 therefore, behold, I am going to do wonders among this people, wonder upon wonder, and the wisdom of their wise men will perish, and the understanding of their prudent men will be hidden.', 99, '2022-11-29 17:21:26', null),
(53, 1, 46, 8, 5, 3, null, 99, '2022-02-02 11:52:59', null),
(53, 1, 46, 8, 6, 3, null, 99, '2022-02-02 11:52:29', null),
(53, 1, 46, 10, 32, 0, 'Give none offence, neither to the Jews, nor to the Gentiles, nor to the church of God:', 99, '2022-08-26 08:09:36', null),
(53, 1, 46, 14, 34, 0, '*There is also a text-critical point, but not one that is as easy to prove. The facts (a) that vv. 34–35 are transposed after v. 36 in some text traditions and (b) that these verses are not missing', 99, '2022-03-06 05:53:15', '<p>*There is also a text-critical point, but not one that is as easy to prove. The facts (a) that vv. 34&ndash;35 are transposed after v. 36 in some text traditions and (b) that these verses are not missing from any manuscript suggest together that vv. 34&ndash;35 could have been a large marginal addition from Paul&rsquo;s hand. That suggestion reinforces the interpretation of this as a relative prohibition: Paul did not intend to make a blanket statement about women&rsquo;s conduct in all cases but to give an application of the principle of orderly worship to a specific problem that the Corinthians were dealing with.</p>'),
(53, 1, 47, 4, 2, 0, '<a data-hlite="0" id="hl_53|1|47|4|2" title="Clear">we have renounced the hidden things of shame, not walking in craftiness, nor watering-down the word of God,</a>', 99, '2022-12-13 15:04:38', null),
(53, 1, 47, 4, 3, 0, 'But if our gospel be hid, it is hid to them that are lost:', 99, '2022-12-13 15:11:15', null),
(53, 1, 48, 1, 10, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>Gal 1:13 &quot;my former way of life in Judaism, how intensely I was persecuting the church of God and was trying to destroy it.&quot; Paul tried to please Jew leaders by fanatically persecuting Christians.</p> <p>2Tim 2:15 Be diligent to present [paristēmi, stand before] yourself approved before God, a worker who does not need to be ashamed, rightly handling the word of truth.</p> <p>Romans 14:18 For whoever serves Christ in this way is pleasing to God and approved by men.</p> <p>2 Corinthians 10:18 For it is not the one who recommends himself who is approved, but the one whom the Lord recommends.</p> <p>1 Thessalonians 2:4 but just as we have been approved by God to be entrusted with the gospel, so we speak, not to please man, but God Who tests our hearts.</p> <p>Hebrews 11:2 For by it [faith] the men of the past were approved by God.</p> <p>Hebrews 11:5 By faith [trust] Enoch was moved so that he would not see death, and he could not be found, because God moved him, for before he was moved he obtained the testimony that he pleased God.</p>'),
(53, 1, 48, 1, 12, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>see entire commentary! All revelation will either come to a person externally or it will be internal, given directly to the person&rsquo;s mind. Revelation from God or the Lord Jesus can come to us in many ways. Bible examples of how God has communicated a message of knowledge or wisdom include Him speaking audibly, sending an angel, sending a prophet, having Balaam&rsquo;s donkey talk, putting dew on a fleece, writing on a wall, giving visions, and in dreams.</p>'),
(53, 1, 48, 1, 23, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>Acts 9:1 Now Saul, still breathing out threats and murder against the disciples of the Lord, went to the high priest 2 and asked him for letters to the synagogues of Damascus, that if he found anyone belonging to the Way, whether men or women, he could bring them bound to Jerusalem.</p> <p>Acts 9:4 and he fell to the ground and heard a voice saying to him, &ldquo;Saul, Saul, why are you persecuting me?&rdquo;</p> <p>Acts 22:7 And I fell to the ground, and heard a voice saying to me, &quot;Saul, Saul, why do you persecute me?&quot;</p> <p>Acts 26:14 And when we had all fallen to the ground, I heard a voice saying to me in the Hebrew language, &quot;Saul, Saul, why do you persecute me? It is hard on you to be kicking against the goads.&quot;</p> <p>Acts 9:10 Now there was a certain disciple at Damascus, named Ananias, and in a vision the Lord said to him, &ldquo;Ananias.&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;See, I am here, Lord.&rdquo;</p> <p>Acts 9:13 But Ananias answered, &ldquo;Lord, I have heard from many about this man, how much evil he has done to your holy ones at Jerusalem,&quot;</p> <p>Acts 9:17 And Ananias departed and went into the house, and laying his hands on him said, &ldquo;Brother Saul, the Lord has sent me&mdash;Jesus, who appeared to you on the road by which you came&mdash;so that you can receive your sight and be filled with holy spirit.&rdquo;</p>'),
(53, 1, 48, 6, 14, 0, 'KJV But God forbid that I should glory, save in the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ, by whom the world is crucified unto me, and I unto the world.', 99, '2022-10-27 21:59:56', null),
(53, 1, 49, 4, 26, 0, 'Ps 4:4 <a data-hlite="0" id="hl_53|0|19|4|4" title="Clear">be angry, but do not sin. Speak in your heart on your bed,<br /> and keep silent. Selah.</a><br /> <a data-hlite="0" title="Clear">Stand in awe, and sin not: commune with your own heart upon your bed, and be still. Selah.</a><br /> Lev 19:18 You must not take vengeance, nor hold a grudge against the children of your people, but you must love your neighbor as yourself. I am Yahweh.<br /> Ps 4:8', 99, '2022-07-17 10:30:12', '<p>Ps 4:8 I will both lay me down in peace and sleep: for only You, Yahweh, make me dwell in safety.</p>'),
(53, 1, 50, 3, 10, 0, '2 Tim 2:3 Share with me in suffering hardship, as a good soldier of Christ Jesus.', 99, '2022-03-23 00:42:31', null),
(53, 1, 50, 3, 14, 0, 'upward calling Rom 12:2 reneweding mind = anakainos nous = newing-up in quality mind', 99, '2022-03-23 00:53:55', null),
(53, 1, 51, 1, 13, 0, 'God rescued us', 99, '2022-11-29 18:25:46', null),
(53, 1, 51, 1, 15, 0, 'He= Christ Jesus; image= icon, imprint, embossment', 99, '2022-11-29 18:19:55', null),
(53, 1, 51, 1, 16, 0, 'all within a certain category; God created the positions of authority needed to run the Church of God.', 99, '2022-11-29 18:24:28', null),
(53, 1, 51, 1, 17, 0, '<strong>Christ holds highest rank</strong>', 99, '2022-11-29 18:27:28', null),
(53, 1, 51, 1, 18, 0, 'the Body of Christ', 99, '2022-11-29 18:29:01', null),
(53, 1, 52, 4, 14, 0, '2Cor4:14 <a data-hlite="0" id="hl_53|1|47|4|14" title="Clear">knowing that the One Who raised the Lord Jesus will raise us up also <em>to be</em> with Jesus, and will bring us [fallen asleep] along with you [alive], into his [Jesus&rsquo;] presence.</a>', 99, '2022-12-10 14:03:57', null),
(53, 1, 52, 5, 17, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-16 14:59:11', '<p>Pray without giving up; Pray without ceasing; Pray unceasingly;</p>'),
(53, 1, 52, 5, 18, 0, null, 99, '2022-01-16 15:05:35', '<p>Rejoice continually; pray without giving-up; give thanks in all circumstances; for this is God&#39;s will for you in union with Christ Jesus.</p> <p>-1Thess5:16-18</p>'),
(53, 1, 54, 4, 15, 0, '<h3>Keep meditating on these things.</h3> <img alt="" src="https://www.revisedenglishversion.com/i/redx.png" /><br /> Keep meditating on these things. Be <em>devoted</em> to them so that your progress is obvious to all.', 99, '2022-06-26 15:27:48', null),
(53, 1, 55, 2, 10, 0, '2 Tim 2:3 Share with me in suffering hardship, as a good soldier of Christ Jesus.', 99, '2022-03-23 00:43:16', null),
(53, 1, 55, 3, 16, 0, 'All scripture is God-breathed and profitable for&hellip; instruction in right-living.', 99, '2022-10-31 15:18:25', null),
(53, 1, 55, 3, 17, 0, 'so that the person who belongs to God [of God] can be complete, completely equiped [artios, exartizo] for every good work.', 99, '2022-10-31 15:53:57', '<p>artios (only use) = thorough, complete, capable, proficient, able to meet all demands, entirely suited, completely ready</p> <p>exartizo (2x, here &amp; Act 21.5) = finished, completely complete, fully equipped, completely furnished</p> <p>2 Tim 2:15 so that the man of God may be proficient (exērtismenos, perf pass ptcp nom sg masc), fully equipped (exērtismenos, perf pass ptcp nom sg masc) for every good work.</p> <p>Acts 21:5 When our days there were ended (exartisai | ἐξαρτίσαι | aor act inf ), we departed and went on our journey, and they all, with wives and children, accompanied us until we were outside the city. Then kneeling down on the beach, we prayed</p>'),
(53, 1, 55, 4, 18, 0, null, 99, '2022-02-02 01:55:15', '<p>Nero had Paul excecuted by beheading. Nero executed thousands of Christians.</p>');
INSERT INTO `myrevdata` (`myrevid`, `testament`, `book`, `chapter`, `verse`, `highlight`, `marginnote`, `sqn`, `lastupdate`, `myrevnotes`) VALUES
(53, 1, 58, 1, 1, 0, 'God gives progressive revelation, bit by bit, over time.', 99, '2022-11-02 18:01:12', null),
(53, 1, 58, 1, 3, 0, 'Jesus Christ <a data-hlite="0" id="hl_53|1|58|1|3" onclick="showhilightdiv(''53|1|58|1|3'', ''/Heb/1/3/0'');" title="Clear">is the reflection of God&rsquo;s glory [the image of God] and the exact representation of God&rsquo;s imprint [character] and is upholding all things by God&rsquo;s powerful word. After he had accomplished <em>the</em> cleansing for sins, he sat down on the right hand of the Majesty on high</a>', 99, '2022-11-03 01:35:52', null),
(53, 1, 58, 1, 5, 0, '<strong>You are My Son today, I became your Father [when I raised you from the dead]a.</strong> And again, <strong>I will be to him a Father and he will be to Me a Son [when I conceived him]b</strong>?', 99, '2022-11-03 01:44:43', '<p>a Ps 2:7 I will proclaim the decree of Yahweh. He said to me, &ldquo;You are My son, today I have become your father.</p> <p>Rom 1:4 Jesus Christ was appointed the Son-of-God-with-power by his resurrection from the dead according to the Spirit of Holiness [God]&mdash;Jesus Christ our Lord&mdash;</p> <p>b 2Sam 7:14 I will be his father and he will be My son, whom, if he commits iniquity, I will discipline him with the rod of men and with blows from the sons of men,</p>'),
(53, 1, 58, 1, 6, 0, '[AMP] Moreover, when God brings the firstborn Son again into the habitable world, God says, Let all the angels of God worship Jesus.<br /> When God <strong>again</strong> brings the firstborn into the inhabited world [Jesus&rsquo; 2<sup>nd</sup> coming], God says, <strong>And let all the angels of God pay him [Jesus Christ] homage [bow down and worship]</strong>. <em>Paul changed OT meaning to reveal the sacred secret.</em>', 99, '2023-01-22 05:30:47', '<p>Ps 97:7 Let all who serve carved images be put to shame. Those who boast in their idols <strong>bow down to Him [Yahweh], all you gods [more powereful than mere angels]!</strong></p> <p>Deut 32:43 Rejoice, O heavens [faithful spirit beings/angels] together with Him [Yahweh]; <strong>bow down to Him [Yahweh], all you sons of God [angels],</strong> for He [Yahweh] will avenge the blood of His servants. He [Yahweh] will return vengeance on His adversaries. He [Yahweh] will repay those who hate Him and will make atonement for His land and for His people.</p>'),
(53, 1, 58, 1, 7, 0, 'AMP: And concerning the angels it says, &ldquo;Who makes His angel messengers spirits and His ministering servants flames of fire [to do His bidding].&rdquo; CEV: And when God speaks about the angels, He says, &ldquo;I change My angels into wind and My servants into flaming fire.&rdquo; ICB: This is what God said about the angels: &ldquo;God makes His angels become like winds. He makes His servants become like flames of fire.&rdquo;', 99, '2023-01-22 04:39:29', '<p>Psalm 104:3 He lays the beams of His chambers on the waters; He makes the clouds His chariot; He rides on the wings of spirits [ruach]; 4 God makes spirits His messengers, flaming fires His ministers [servants] = <strong><em>God is demoting angels/spirits lower than Jesus Christ and elevating the Body of Christ saints (the sacred secret hid in OT, revealed in Heb 1:7).</em></strong></p> <p>In Ezekiel God&rsquo;s chariot is moved by cherubims [spirits] with wings.</p>'),
(53, 1, 58, 1, 8, 0, '<a data-hlite="0" id="hl_53|1|58|1|8" onclick="showhilightdiv(''53|1|58|1|8'', ''/Heb/1/8/0'');" title="Clear"><strong>Your throne is Ruler for ages and ages, and the scepter of uprightness is the scepter of your kingdom.</strong></a>', 99, '2022-11-02 22:37:47', '<p>&ldquo;GOD&rdquo; was a descriptive title applied to a range of authorities, including God, angels, demons, pagan gods, great people, rulers, and people acting with God&rsquo;s authority&mdash;all of those were referred to as &ldquo;GOD.&rdquo; For example, Jesus pointed out that people to whom the Word of God came were called &ldquo;gods&rdquo; (John 10:34-35)</p>'),
(53, 1, 58, 1, 10, 0, null, 99, '2022-11-02 22:59:55', '<p>Ps 2:7 &ldquo;Son&rdquo; is describing the relationship that the Messiah has with the Father as a fully developed Son, participating in ruling the house. Psalm 2:7 is used other ways in the NT: making Jesus the &ldquo;Son&rdquo; at his baptism when he receives God&rsquo;s holy spirit; Acts 13:33 quotes Ps 2:7 making Jesus the &ldquo;Son&rdquo; when God raised him from the dead and he began a whole new relationship with the Father; Heb 1:5 quotes Ps 2:7 in the ascension (cp. Heb. 1:3) Jesus became the &ldquo;Son&rdquo; when he sat down at God&rsquo;s right hand and began another new relationship with the Father. So we see that Psalm 2:7 is used differently in the New Testament than in the Old Testament, but each time it is quoted, the context makes clear what God is trying to communicate.</p>'),
(53, 1, 58, 1, 12, 0, null, 99, '2022-11-02 23:08:27', '<p><em>A Prayer of the afflicted</em> <em>when he is powerless and he pours out his complaint before Yahweh.</em></p> <p>Ps 102:25 Of old You [my God] established the earth. And the heavens are the work of Your hands. 26 They will perish, but You will endure. Yes, all of them will wear out like a garment. You will change them like clothing, and they will pass on. 27 But You are the same. And Your years will not come to an end.</p>'),
(53, 1, 58, 1, 13, 0, null, 99, '2022-11-02 23:10:35', '<p>Ps 110:1 Yahweh&rsquo;s declaration to my lord, &ldquo;Sit at My right hand until I make your enemies a footstool for your feet.&rdquo;</p>'),
(53, 1, 58, 1, 14, 0, '[Angels serve God for the sake of Christians]', 99, '2022-11-02 23:12:05', null),
(53, 1, 58, 2, 6, 0, null, 99, '2022-11-26 13:28:22', '<p>Heb 2:6-9 But someone has said: &ldquo;What is man that You are mindful of him, or the son of man that You take care of him? You made him a little lower than angels; <em>yet</em> You crowned him with glory and honour, and set him over the works of Your hands. You have put all things in subjection under his feet.&rdquo; You subjected all things under his feet&rdquo; [Ps 8:4-6]. For in the subjecting all things to him, He [God] left nothing not-subject to him. But now we do not yet see all things having been subjected to him.</p> <p>But we see Jesus&mdash;made lower than the angels for a short time so that by God&rsquo;s grace he might taste death for everyone&mdash;crowned with glory and honor because he suffered death.</p>'),
(53, 1, 58, 2, 9, 0, null, 99, '2022-11-26 13:31:28', '<p>PHILLIPS But we see Jesus, after being made temporarily inferior to the angels (and so subject to pain and death), in order that he should, in God&rsquo;s grace, taste death for every man, now crowned with glory and honor. It was right and proper that in bringing many sons to glory, God (from Whom and by Whom everything exists) should make the leader of their salvation a perfect leader through the fact that he suffered. For the one who makes men holy and the men who are made holy share a common humanity. So that he is not ashamed to call them his brothers, for he says: &lsquo;I will declare Your name to my brethren; in the midst of the congregation I will sing praise to You&rsquo;.</p>'),
