(53, 1, 62, 1, 10, 0, 'end chap 1 after 1Jn 1:1-2', 99, '2022-10-19 00:31:37', '<p>1Jn1:9-10 9 &amp; 1Jn2:1-2</p> <p>If we confess our sins, he is faithful and righteous to forgive us our sins and to cleanse us from all unrighteousness.<br /> If we say that we have not sinned, we make him a liar and his word is not in us. My little children, I write these things to you so that you will not sin. And if anyone sins, we have an advocate who pleads our case to the Father&mdash;Jesus Christ,a the Righteous One. And he is the atoning sacrifice for our sins, and not for ours only, but also for the whole world.</p>'),
(53, 1, 62, 4, 4, 0, '<span style="font-size: 1.2em;">2 King 6:16 &ldquo;Do not be afraid, for those [angel armies] who are with us are more than those who are with them.&rdquo;</span>', 99, '2022-08-24 12:02:27', '<p>2 Kings 6:<br /> 15 And when the servant of the man of God had risen early and gone out, behold, an army with horses and chariots was surrounding the city. So his servant said to him, &ldquo;Alas, my lord! What are we to do?&rdquo;<br /> 16 But he answered, <strong>&ldquo;Do not be afraid, for those [angel armies] who are with us are more than those [humans] who are with them.&rdquo;</strong><br /> 17 <strong>Elisha prayed and said, &ldquo;O Yahweh, please open his eyes so that he can see.&rdquo; So Yahweh opened the eyes of the young man and he saw, and behold, the mountain was full of horses and chariots of fire surrounding Elisha.</strong></p>'),
