(63, 1, 40, 5, 9, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>&ldquo;Blessed are the peacemakers, for they will be called sons of God.&rdquo; This clearly refers to the future because the peacemakers on the earth today are often scoffed at and discounted as cowards and compromisers. This is the case whether the conflicts are inter-family, inter-racial, or international. Nevertheless, the Lord recognizes their efforts and they will be called &ldquo;the sons of God&rdquo; in the Kingdom, where they will live forever. That peacemakers would have everlasting life was stated in the Old Testament. Psalm 37:37 (NIV84) says, &ldquo;there is a future for the man of peace.&rdquo;</p>'),
(63, 1, 40, 5, 10, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>&ldquo;Blessed are those who have been persecuted because of their righteousness, for theirs is the Kingdom of Heaven.&rdquo; Many of the people who have been persecuted died in the persecution, but they are promised &ldquo;the Kingdom of Heaven,&rdquo; i.e., everlasting life in Christ&rsquo;s wonderful future kingdom on earth. In this context, &ldquo;righteousness&rdquo; in the phrase &ldquo;because of their righteousness&rdquo; refers to both a believer&rsquo;s righteous standing in the sight of God and the righteous acts that they do. The primary emphasis of &ldquo;righteousness&rdquo; in this verse is &ldquo;righteous acts,&rdquo; because it is the righteous acts of godly people that draws the attention of ungodly people and incites them to persecute the godly. Thus, in that sense this verse is very similar to 2 Timothy 3:12, that everyone who lives a godly life will be persecuted. Also, however, on a spiritual level, the Devil and his people cannot be at peace with people who have a right standing in the sight of God (are spiritually &ldquo;righteous&rdquo;) and so persecute them for that reason also. Many verses show that those people who endure persecution will be blessed for their stand for the Lord (cp. 1 Pet. 4:12-16; Rev. 2:10;</p> <p>[For more on &ldquo;righteousness&rdquo; having the meaning of doing what is right or just (&ldquo;justice&rdquo;), see commentary on Matt. 5:6. For more on the meaning of &ldquo;righteousness&rdquo; and that word family, see commentary on Rom. 3:22. For more on Christ&rsquo;s future Millennial Kingdom on earth, see Appendix 3, &ldquo;Christ&rsquo;s Future Kingdom on Earth&rdquo;].</p>'),
(63, 1, 44, 18, 1, 1, null, 99, null, null),
(63, 1, 44, 18, 2, 4, null, 99, null, '<p>I love this bible aid</p>'),
