(126, 1, 49, 1, 4, 3, null, 99, null, null),
(128, 1, 46, 6, 9, 0, null, 99, null, '<p>Regarding malakoi and arsenokoites. As myself a homosexual, I cannot identify myself with your commentaries. A malakos is pejorative about a person not fitting into the norm of how a male should be or act. It does not necessarily mean homosexuality, it is to be considered something like &ldquo;a sissy, or sissy boy&rdquo;. It does more reflect the patriarcal view of male dominance. It also likens malakoi with women. A woman is in like manner inferior to the male in many cultures even today. As to the sexual act, the belief in ancient times was that it is the man that solely procreates, the woman is but his field to plow his seed in. So, if he plows his seed into another male, that means he uses the male as a woman for his own pleasure. Again if you say that malakos is a boy, or young man that is kept as a sex slave for his owner to do with what he pleases, it does not mean it is volutary on the malakos side, as the so called malakos might be heterosexual, but has no choice but to comply or be punished. Hence, if you want to make malakos into a homosexual in your translation, maybe you should add something like &ldquo;willing or consenting&rdquo; to the word homosexual, or use the same type of metafor and translate with a pejorative word, like &ldquo;poof&rdquo;, &ldquo;sissy&rdquo; etc, which in my opinion would be even better. In that way it consolidates the patriarcal view of both ancient and today&rsquo;s world.</p> <p>As to the arsenokoites, that is a reference to the Torah, a man sleeping with a man as with a woman, and has nothing whatsoever to do with homosexuality. Even straight men engage in same sex activities, have always done so and will always do so. For some men it does not matter who the recepient is. Their main interest is just to sexually relieve themselves, whether it be of sadistic nature or convenience. They do not consider themselves homosexual nor act in any effeminate way, nor are they perverted &ndash; they might have families and kids of their own. Again this patriarcal view of male dominance &ndash; a man can do what he wants being the dominant. Hence for arsenokoites, do not interpret into it what it is not, rather render it for what it is. Arsenokoites is a man that sleeps with another man as with a woman, or a male that has intercourse with another man or with other men, whether it be voluntary, dominant, sadistic, convenient or any other way and only serves as a way to release sexual tension.</p>'),
