(149, 1, 49, 4, 15, 0, '<a href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Ephesians%204:14-16&amp;version=KJ21">KJ21</a><br /> but speaking the truth in love, may grow up into Him in all things, who is the Head, even Christ,<br /> <a href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Ephesians%204:14-16&amp;version=ASV">ASV</a><br /> but speaking truth in love, may grow up in all things into him, who is the head, <em>even</em> Christ;', 99, '2023-01-21 09:54:35', '<p>&ldquo;we are to grow up.&rdquo; The &ldquo;we&rdquo; is collective, that is, the Church is to grow up into Christ, but that <span style="background-color:#f1c40f;">growth is done individually.</span> Each individual is to speak the truth in love and grow up in every way into Christ. The directive given to Christians to &ldquo;grow up&rdquo; places a responsibility on each Christian that will differ from person to person and should not be ignored.</p> <p><span style="background-color:#f1c40f;">To &ldquo;grow up&rdquo; into Christ requires mental and spiritual growth, which takes time and effort. It is a process, not an event.</span> Every Christian has &ldquo;baggage,&rdquo; weaknesses, and blind spots that keep them from fully utilizing their ministry and being like Christ. On the Day of Judgment, Jesus Christ will not expect us to be perfect, but he will expect that we have not been content to live with our faults and excuses, but have made a sincere effort to try to live like he did and do our best to be approved by God (2 Tim. 2:15).</p> <p><span style="background-color:#f1c40f;">The Bible tells us to examine ourselves</span> (1 Cor. 11:28; 2 Cor. 13:5; Gal. 6:4). That means that we should be asking ourselves questions such as &ldquo;What is my ministry? Am I fulfilling it? Is anything holding me back from being like Christ? What am I not doing I should be doing and what am I doing I should not be doing?&rdquo; Do I need help, and if so, where should I get that help?&rdquo;</p> <p>Judgment Day is no joke, and although making any changes or adjustments to our lives may be uncomfortable in the immediate present, those changes will produce &ldquo;the peaceable fruit of righteousness&rdquo; in this life (Heb. 12:11), and great joy in the next.</p> <p>&ldquo;into him.&rdquo; The Greek, eis auton, &ldquo;into him,&rdquo; refers to our relationship with Jesus. We are to grow up in every way in our relation to Christ.</p>'),
(150, 0, 19, 110, 5, 4, null, 99, '2021-11-06 14:36:25', '<p>It&#39;s Yahweh at the right hand of Yahshua. There is a temporary switch of power and thrones. This prophetic event is yet to happen in the future.</p> <p>Verse 1 states that Yahshua is sitting at the right hand of Yahweh&#39;s throne.</p> <p>Verse 5 states that Yahshua will be sitting on his Fathers throne. And his Father Yahweh will be temporarily sitting on the right hand of his Son&#39;s throne.</p>'),
