(215, 0, 1, 4, 22, 0, 'Bronze Age (3,300 - 1,200 BC)<br /> <br /> Iron Age (1,200 - 500 BC)', 99, '2022-07-09 12:56:27', '<p>Around 3500 BC the first signs of bronze usage by the ancient Sumerians started to appear in the Tigris Euphrates valley in Western Asia.</p> <p><a href="http://www.makin-metals.com/about/history-of-bronze-infographic/">http://www.makin-metals.com/about/history-of-bronze-infographic/</a></p> <p>The earliest known iron artefacts are nine small beads securely dated to circa 3200 BC, from two burials in Gerzeh, northern Egypt.</p> <p>https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0305440313002057#:~:text=The%20earliest%20known%20iron%20artefacts,before%20rolling%20them%20into%20tubes.</p>');
