(226, 1, 43, 12, 1, 0, 'Jn 12:1-11', 99, '2022-04-02 04:00:13', '<p>Jn 12:1-8 is John&rsquo;s version of the narrative in Matt and Mk. John has a few differences, but not contradictions. For example:</p> <ol> <li>In Mt and Mk Mary pours oil on Jesus head; here she pours the oil on his feet. But Mt 26:12, Jesus says she poured oil on his body. If Mary used the entire pint, it would easily have run down from his head to his feet, covering his whole body.</li> <li>Some commentators think that Mary in Mt and Mk is Mary Magdalene and therefore, the Mary in John cannot be the same because she was Martha and Lazarus sister. But she is not identified as &ldquo;Magdalene&rdquo; in Mt and Mk</li> <li>John adds the plot to kill Lazarus which is not recorded in Mt or Mk.</li> </ol> <p>Apparently, Lazarus had become somewhat of a celebrity because many of the common Jews came to see him as well. But the Jewish leaders wanted to kill him as well as Jesus because he caused many to believe in Jesus.</p>'),
