(270, 0, 1, 11, 9, 0, 'How were spirit beings involved? &ndash; Deut. 32:8', 99, '2022-08-19 18:43:03', '<p>&ldquo;sons of God.&rdquo; The Masoretic Hebrew text reads &ldquo;sons of Israel,&rdquo; but the Septuagint reads &ldquo;sons of God,&rdquo; and there is evidence from the Qumran Scrolls that that is the correct reading (cp. Peter Craigie, NICOT: The Book of Deuteronomy). What Deuteronomy 32:8 seems to be saying is that when the nations formed, their boundaries were determined by God, the different nations were somehow kept separate by the spiritual powers associated with them.</p>'),
(270, 1, 66, 22, 1, 0, 'Does one throne mean God and the Lamb are one person?', 99, '2022-08-19 18:09:59', '<p>The Lamb shares the throne of God because God has granted this to the Lamb: &ldquo;he shall rule&hellip;even as I myself have received power from my Father (Rev. 2:27, 3:21, cf. Matt. 28:18). As a parallel, the LORD God put both David and Solomon on His (God&rsquo;s) throne. &ldquo;Then Solomon sat on the throne of the LORD as king in place of David his father&rdquo; (1 Chron. 29:23). But neither David nor Solomon were God just because they were granted by God to rule as God&rsquo;s representatives on God&rsquo;s throne. As God&rsquo;s chosen, anointed kings, David and Solomon were granted to sit on God&rsquo;s throne. So is the risen Jesus Christ.</p>'),
(270, 1, 66, 22, 3, 0, 'Does one throne mean God and the Lamb are one person?', 99, '2022-08-19 18:09:17', '<p>The Lamb shares the throne of God because God has granted this to the Lamb: &ldquo;he shall rule&hellip;even as I myself have received power from my Father (Rev. 2:27, 3:21, cf. Matt. 28:18). As a parallel, the LORD God put both David and Solomon on His (God&rsquo;s) throne. &ldquo;Then Solomon sat on the throne of the LORD as king in place of David his father&rdquo; (1 Chron. 29:23). But neither David nor Solomon were God just because they were granted by God to rule as God&rsquo;s representatives on God&rsquo;s throne. As God&rsquo;s chosen, anointed kings, David and Solomon were granted to sit on God&rsquo;s throne. So is the risen Jesus Christ.</p>'),
(277, 0, 1, 4, 7, 0, null, 99, '2022-07-21 13:41:25', '<p>sin: (see JS comm) here using the Hebrew masculine noun for &ldquo;sin&rdquo;; portrayed as a &ldquo;male animal&rdquo; a &ldquo;crouching demon&rdquo; Everett Fox</p>'),
(285, 1, 56, 1, 3, 0, '&ldquo;God our Savior&rdquo; &ndash; meaning?', 99, '2022-08-16 13:47:14', '<p>This contradicts what I know, mainly, Jesus is not God. What is the explanation? And several other places in Titus also.</p>'),
