(297, 1, 46, 1, 22, 5, 'For the religious seek after signs i.e. a move of the Holy Spirit and the non saved seek head knowledge.', 99, '2022-12-06 14:51:32', '<p>Do the ones who have chosen Christ need Him to continually prove Himself to them? Why do they always want to see signs and miracles? God used them long ago to validate His sons authenticity and the apostles who were speaking a new truth that no one had heard before. In this day and age we have the truth and the message of good news easily and readily available to us. We grew up hearing about it. And some of us chose to believe. So why do we keep wanting signs and miracles and abundant riches? For what purpose? To what end? If it&#39;s for the unsaved to see the power of God? Shouldn&#39;t our life style be enough evidence of the power of God? The transformation that we undergo when we chose Christ? Shouldn&#39;t our lives be a sign and a wonder and a miracle of Christs power within us? Or are we so weak and doubt the power of God at work in us that we have to look for outside proof of the power of God and His son who works mightily in us every day &ndash; when we let him. We need to rethink our wants and desires. Are they in alignment with our Fathers wants and desires? Or do they go against or negate the work of Christ within us?</p>'),
