(342, 0, 2, 4, 16, 4, 'You will be God to him', 99, '2023-01-21 12:18:52', '<p>In Exodus 22:28 &ldquo;gods&rdquo; refers to human judges and the judges were called &ldquo;gods&rdquo; in Psalm 82:6-7. Moses was designated as God in relationship to Aaron (Ex. 4:16) and also to Pharaoh (Ex. 7:1). Jesus answered the Jews who sought to stone him for blasphemy, &ldquo;Is it not written in your law, &lsquo;I said, You are gods?&rsquo; If he called them gods, to whom the word of God came, and the Scriptures cannot be broken do you say of him whom the Father sanctified and sent into the world, &lsquo;You blaspheme&rsquo; because I said, &lsquo;I am the Son of God&rsquo;&rdquo;? (John 10:34-36).</p> <p>&mdash; The Tyranny of the Trinity: The Orthodox Cover-Up by P.R. Lackey</p>'),
(342, 0, 2, 7, 1, 4, 'Made you a god to...', 99, '2023-01-21 12:20:56', '<p>In Exodus 22:28 &ldquo;gods&rdquo; refers to human judges and the judges were called &ldquo;gods&rdquo; in Psalm 82:6-7. Moses was designated as God in relationship to Aaron (Ex. 4:16) and also to Pharaoh (Ex. 7:1). Jesus answered the Jews who sought to stone him for blasphemy, &ldquo;Is it not written in your law, &lsquo;I said, You are gods?&rsquo; If he called them gods, to whom the word of God came, and the Scriptures cannot be broken do you say of him whom the Father sanctified and sent into the world, &lsquo;You blaspheme&rsquo; because I said, &lsquo;I am the Son of God&rsquo;&rdquo;? (John 10:34-36).</p> <p>&mdash; The Tyranny of the Trinity: The Orthodox Cover-Up by P.R. Lackey</p>'),
(342, 0, 2, 32, 4, 1, null, 99, '2023-02-09 11:53:57', '<p>&ldquo;Jesus Is Still on Trial</p> <p>Dear reader, how badly do you really want to belong to the &ldquo;Mystery Trinity Club&rdquo;? Again, in the past dissenters were put to death&mdash;but today they just keep silent. Well, dear brethren and Trinity doubters, if you don&rsquo;t stand for something, you&rsquo;ll fall for anything. And far too many of my brethren have. Indeed, for fear of condemnation, they have far too long denied Jesus Christ as the Son of God as an appeasement, to be accepted and/or belong. Make no mistake, dear brethren; regrettably, after 1700 years, Jesus Christ is still on trial! Just how far have we advanced from the third, fourth and fifth centuries and the medieval epoch? It appears that theologically on this issue, we haven&rsquo;t advanced at all! Today, it is not politically correct to stand up for God in our schools and public venues, and Christians are outraged at this secular injustice. Those of us who acknowledge Jesus Christ as the Son of God are treated equally unjustly by our houses/institutions of worship and brethren. What a sad commentary. Perhaps our houses of worship should remove the &ldquo;beam&rdquo; from their own eyes.</p> <p>How Did You Come by Your Beliefs?</p> <p>&ldquo;Many come into adulthood having accepted without question what they heard, read or were taught in Sunday school. They have been unwilling to challenge what all their peers have also accepted without question. Strangely, these same people will often vigorously defend their beliefs with absolutely no need to examine why they believe what they do&mdash;or to consider how they came to such beliefs. Human nature wants to follow the crowd. And this has been the case with virtually every one of the popular church teachings, traditions and practices found in orthodox Christianity, which have been taken almost entirely from paganism, false customs and human reasoning. This is why the masses have followed a god that was conceived and developed entirely outside the pages of the Bible.&rdquo;64&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; The Tyranny of the Trinity: The Orthodox Cover-Up by P.R. Lackey</p> <p>I think of Linda Realty&rsquo;s comment to me:</p> <p>&quot;The book of John makes it perfectly clear that the Word was Jesus (v. 14 &ldquo;He was made flesh and dwelt among us and his own did not receive him&rdquo;)&mdash;verse 1 tells us he was with God and he was God. (That&rsquo;s very clear.) Verse 3 tells us he created EVERYTHING that was created and nothing was created that he didn&rsquo;t create. That&rsquo;s clear. Jesus made everything.&quot;</p> <p>Jesus is their Golden Calf<br /> &nbsp;</p>'),
