(342, 0, 13, 10, 14, 4, 'God killed Saul', 99, '2022-12-12 13:28:24', '<p>He did not seek guidance from the Lord. Therefore the Lord put him to death and turned the kingdom over to David the son of Jesse. ESV</p> <p><br /> The Bible says that God killed Saul even though Saul clearly committed suicide</p> <p>Therefore he slew him.--God acts through the instrumentality of His creatures. In this case He employed the Philistines, and the suicidal hand of Saul himself; just as He employed the Assyrian conquerors of a later age to be the scourge of guilty peoples (Isaiah 10:5-15), and raised up Cyrus to be His servant, who should fulfil all His pleasure (Isaiah 44:28; Isaiah 45:1-13). . . .</p> <p>So the LORD put him to death<br /> וַיְמִיתֵ֑הוּ (way&middot;m&icirc;&middot;ṯ&ecirc;&middot;hū)<br /> Conjunctive waw | Verb - Hifil - Consecutive imperfect - third person masculine singular | third person masculine singular<br /> Strong&#39;s 4191: To die, to kill</p>'),
(342, 0, 13, 29, 20, 1, 'Davis is worshipped', 99, '2022-12-27 15:26:45', '<p>God had a unique, virginally conceived Son, the Messiah, and God&rsquo;s spirit is the Spirit of God, His divine presence and power active in the world to enlighten and save. But God never spoke to His own Spirit and the Spirit never sent greetings, was never worshipped nor prayed to.<br /> Both the Father and the Son are addressed in prayer and both are worshipped, Jesus as the Messiah and the Father as the one true God. The biblical word &ldquo;worship&rdquo; is an &ldquo;elastic&rdquo; term with a meaning different from our English word &ldquo;worship.&rdquo; David was &ldquo;worshipped&rdquo; alongside the One God (1Chron. 29:20) and the saints are going to be &ldquo;worshipped&rdquo; by their former persecutors (Rev. 3:9). The Hebrew and Greek words for &ldquo;worship&rdquo; apply both to God and to persons who are not the One God, but superior human agents of the One God.</p> <p>October 1999 issue of Focus on the Kingdom</p>'),
(342, 0, 14, 13, 8, 1, 'Kingdom of Yahweh', 99, '2022-12-07 18:46:21', '<p>And now you are saying to strengthen yourselves before the kingdom of YHWH in the hand of the sons of David, and you [are] a numerous multitude, and calves of gold [are] with you that Jeroboam has made for you for gods.(Literal standard version)</p> <p>&ldquo;It is important to be reminded that David&rsquo;s rule over Israel is called the Kingdom of God. The Kingdom, it should be noted, is not a kingdom in the hearts of David&rsquo;s sons. It is in their hands, under their control, as they govern as Yahweh&rsquo;s vice-regents.&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; Our Fathers Who Aren&#39;t in Heaven by Anthony Buzzard<br /> &nbsp;</p>'),
