(342, 0, 19, 82, 6, 1, 'Ye are gods', 99, '2022-12-27 18:43:19', '<p>&ldquo;&ldquo;I said, &lsquo;You are gods, sons of the Most High, all of you; nevertheless, like men you shall die, and fall like any prince (sar, ruler).&rsquo;&rdquo; Jesus quoted this verse in John 10:34. The point is that the word &ldquo;god&rdquo; is sometimes used in the OT with reference to a person of authority such as a ruler or king and does not imply that that person is divine.&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; The Only True God: A Study of Biblical Monotheism by Eric H.H. Chang, Bentley C.F. Chan<br /> &nbsp;</p>'),
