(342, 0, 23, 29, 13, 1, '&quot;tradition learned by rote&quot;', 99, '2023-02-03 13:36:15', '<p>&ldquo;Then the Lord said, &lsquo;Because these people draw near with their words and honor Me with their lip service, but they remove their hearts far from Me, and their reverence for Me consists of tradition learned by rote&rdquo; (Isaiah 29:11-13).</p>'),
(342, 0, 23, 40, 18, 1, 'Who would you compare Yahweh to?', 99, '2022-11-25 20:24:21', '<p>&ldquo;To this question trinitarians reply boldly, &ldquo;Jesus, God the Son&rdquo;. They do well to consider the First Commandment carefully, and remember that Jesus himself firmly endorsed the proclamation in Deuteronomy 6: 4: &ldquo;Hear O Israel, the LORD (Yahweh) our God, the LORD is one!&rdquo;&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; The Only True God: A Study of Biblical Monotheism by Eric H.H. Chang, Bentley C.F. Chan<br /> &nbsp;</p>'),
(342, 0, 23, 40, 25, 4, null, 99, '2023-02-04 17:49:20', null),
(342, 0, 23, 45, 5, 1, 'There is one God', 99, '2023-01-04 13:42:33', '<p>Can you believe what Calvin writes:</p> <p>&ldquo;He whose divinity Isaiah repeatedly proves from the creation of the world, is none other than the Son of God.&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; Institutes of the Christian Religion by John Calvin</p> <p>&ldquo;The emphatic assertions of God in the Bible, that He is one single Person claiming the unique position of Deity, constantly rule out all contrary views which might make Him more than One: &ldquo;I am the LORD and there is no other; there is no God besides Me&rdquo; (Isa. 45:5). &ldquo;You alone are God&rdquo; (Isa. 37:16; Ps. 86:10). &ldquo;I am the Lord, and there is no other&rdquo; (Isa. 45:6). &ldquo;I, the LORD, besides whom there is no other God. There is no just and saving God but Me&rdquo; (Isa. 45:21). &ldquo;You are the only true God&rdquo; (John 17:3). The Bible exhausts language in its effort to inform the reader that there is one single God and that He is a single divine individual.&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; Jesus Was Not a Trinitarian by Anthony Buzzard<br /> &nbsp;</p>'),
