(342, 0, 23, 53, 10, 0, 'Jesus&rsquo; seed', 99, '2022-11-19 20:34:00', '<p>&ldquo;Verse 8 asks, &ldquo;... And who can speak of his descendants?...&rdquo; What we see here is that Jesus would die without ever having any children. In the Hebrew culture, this was considered a curse. Jesus died with no one to carry on his lineage. But look at verse 10: &ldquo;... He will see his offspring....&rdquo; What &ldquo;offspring&rdquo;? The &ldquo;children God has given him,&rdquo; the &ldquo;many sons in glory.&rdquo; Does this not specifically relate to Christ being called a &ldquo;seed&rdquo; in Genesis 3: 15? Yes, he is the seed that will bear much fruit after his kind. &ldquo;... We know that when he appears, we shall be like him...&rdquo; (1 John 3: 2). Praise God!&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; One God &amp; One Lord: Reconsidering the Cornerstone of the Christian Faith by John W. Schoenheit, Mark H. Graeser, et al.<br /> &nbsp;</p>'),
