(342, 1, 40, 19, 28, 1, 'Jesus, God&rsquo;s vice-regent', 99, '2022-12-29 13:29:50', '<p>&ldquo;The Pauline teaching is that Jesus is the man who fulfilled the destiny originally assigned to Adam, that of ruling the world as the One God&rsquo;s vice-regent. This is the overarching point of New Testament Christianity, promising to other human beings the prospect of following Jesus, the pioneer human being, to glory as rulers of the future Kingdom on earth (Matt. 19:28; 1 Cor. 6:2; Rev. 2:26; 3:21, etc.).&rdquo;</p> <p>This is the theme of the much neglected Christian Gospel of the Kingdom of God, preached as the central saving message by Jesus, and by Paul following the orders of Jesus in the Great Commission (Luke 4:43; 8:1; Acts 19:8; 20:24-25; 28:23, 31, etc.)</p> <p>&mdash; Jesus Was Not a Trinitarian by Anthony Buzzard</p>'),
(342, 1, 40, 22, 18, 1, null, 99, '2022-12-27 10:07:53', null),
