(342, 1, 42, 1, 33, 1, 'Messiah will Rule the Earth', 99, '2022-12-27 13:32:43', '<p>Many Old Testament Scriptures indicate that the Messiah will rule the earth (cp. Ps. 2:8-12; 72:1-17; 110:1-5; Isa. 9:6-7; 11:1-5, 10; 42:1-7; 49:5-7; 55:1-5; Ezek. 37:24-28; Dan. 2:35, 44; and see also Rev. 21-22).<br /> from the commentary at Daniel 7:13</p>'),
(342, 1, 42, 1, 35, 1, 'For that reason', 99, '2023-01-14 13:17:06', '<p>&ldquo;For Gabriel, Jesus is conceived and begotten and comes into existence in Mary&rsquo;s womb by a miracle of God&rsquo;s power. Jesus is not an &lsquo;eternally begotten&rdquo; (whatever that means!) Son of God, who passes from one form of life into another. Gabriel states in verse 35, &ldquo;therefore [dio kai&ndash;i.e. &ldquo;for this reason&rdquo;, because of God&rsquo;s creative act within Mary&rsquo;s womb] &hellip;that Holy One who is to be born will be called the Son of God&rdquo; (by the way, the NIV Bible waters down the Greek considerably!). Roman Catholic scholar, Raymond Brown, commenting on the &ldquo;therefore&rdquo; in Luke 1:35, states, &ldquo;of the nine times dio kai occurs in the New Testament&hellip; it involves a certain causality&hellip; this has embarrassed many orthodox theologians since in preexistence Christology a conception by the holy spirit in Mary&rsquo;s womb does not bring about the existence of God&rsquo;s Son. Luke is seemingly unaware of such a [preexistent] Christology; conception is causally related to divine Sonship for him.&rdquo; (The Birth of the Messiah, 1977) In other words, for Luke and Gabriel, God&rsquo;s creative act in Mary&rsquo;s womb begets (brings into existence) Jesus as God&rsquo;s Son. There is no hint of any suggestion at all that there was an incarnation where a pre-existing spirit being transformed himself and became a human baby. Jesus is a true man and came into existence by the creative power of God just as Adam did (Luke 1:23, 38). There is only one true God and He is the Father of Jesus Christ.&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; Twenty Biblical Reasons Why the Doctrine of the Trinity is Unbiblical by Chuck LaMattina</p> <p>The Greatest Career Opportunity<br /> of All Time &mdash; for You!<br /> Stop and listen! We have some spectacularly good news for you and your family. Some time in the future, Jesus of Nazareth is going to become the world&rsquo;s<br /> first successful super-ruler. He will totally reorganize human society, and produce the peace on earth which we all long for. Under Jesus&rsquo; government, the Kingdom of God, who is the Father of Jesus (Luke 1:35), there will be no more wars, no more famine; no more murder, rape or theft; no more alcoholism and depression; no more divorce, no more poverty, no more child abuse. Does this sound too good to be true? God, the Creator of all things, has personally promised that a Golden Age for all mankind will come. He has been promising it since He first placed man on our earth. The arrival of that era of glorious peace and prosperity is guaranteed.<br /> What you have just been told is the heart of the Christian Gospel. Very probably you have not heard it before. You have heard a &ldquo;reduced&rdquo; Gospel about &ldquo;going to heaven when you die.&rdquo; Nearly 2,000 years ago, Jesus came to announce the dramatically important good news concerning the future divine government on earth. He is coming back to take up his office as world super-ruler &mdash; and he is now recruiting men and women to assist him in the administration of his coming Kingdom. He wants you to be a ruler in that Kingdom. He wants us to train now under his supervision for royal office in that coming Kingdom (Matt. 19:28; 1 Cor. 6:2; Dan. 7:18, 22, 27; Rev. 2:26-27; 3:21; 5:10; Ps. 37:11, 29: &ldquo;inherit the earth and live in it forever,&rdquo; and many passages).<br /> What a tragedy if you were to allow this greatest of all career opportunities to pass you by. You can so easily neglect the information you have just been given. But don&rsquo;t do it. Do yourself and your family a favor. Check up on the facts. We might just have given you a major piece of Truth you have never heard!<br /> Act now! Find out more about the Christian Gospel/Good News. Peace is coming. And you can help to bring it about.</p> <p>Focus on the Kingdom, December 2014</p>'),
