(342, 1, 42, 2, 8, 1, 'Shepherds', 99, '2022-12-04 14:30:59', '<p>I decided to re-read the Christmas story once again this morning and I am always amazed that God reveals such awesome truth to people that are basically the nobodies of the world. Mary, who was just some insignificant young girl to those around her, probably playing with dolls, and in another case fishermen, who were basically the blue-collar workers of their day, the type that would be riding around in the back of a pickup truck today, and in this case, shepherds who were actually living outside with their sheep. I&#39;m sure that the last thing on their minds when they clocked in for work that night was that an Angel of God was going to appear to them.</p> <p>I&#39;ve noticed that God often does things suddenly and unexpectedly.</p> <p>And there were shepherds in the same area, living out in the fields and keeping watch over their flock at night. And an angel of the Lord suddenly stood before them and the glory of the Lord shone around them, and they were frightened with great fear. And the angel said to them, &ldquo;Do not be afraid, for listen, I bring you good news that will cause great joy, which will be for all the people.</p> <p>For to you was born this day in the city of David the Savior, who is the Messiah and Lord.</p> <p>Luke 2:8-11 (Revised English Version)</p> <p>As far as the nobodies of the world go, I can&rsquo;t help but think about what the Apostle Paul once wrote to the church in Corinth:</p> <p>Brothers and sisters, think of what you were when you were called. Not many of you were wise by human standards; not many were influential; not many were of noble birth. But God chose the foolish things of the world to shame the wise; God chose the weak things of the world to shame the strong. God chose the lowly things of this world and the despised things&mdash;and the things that are not&mdash;to nullify the things that are, so that no one may boast before him. It is because of him that you are in Christ Jesus, who has become for us wisdom from God&mdash;that is, our righteousness, holiness and redemption. Therefore, as it is written: &ldquo;Let the one who boasts boast in the Lord.&rdquo;</p> <p>1 Corinthians 1:26-31 (New International Version)</p> <p>So there it is, God deliberately chooses the nobodies of the world so that they will not boast about themselves, but instead they will boast about the God who has chosen them for such awesome revelations!</p>'),
