(342, 1, 43, 8, 58, 1, 'I AM!', 99, '2023-01-24 11:44:17', '<p>Did Jesus just say he was God as the Trinitarians would have us believe?</p> <p>Look how misleading some of the translations are.</p> <p>&ldquo;I tell you in solemn truth,&rdquo; returned Jesus, &ldquo;before there was an Abraham, I AM!&rdquo;PHILLIPS</p> <p>&ldquo;Where Jesus states that &ldquo;I am he [the Messiah] before Abraham came to be,&rdquo; or as it reads equally well in the Greek &ldquo;before Abraham comes to be.&rdquo; If so translated (the Greek is ambiguous) Jesus makes the claim to be prior to Abraham in the resurrection. If Jesus means before Abraham&rsquo;s birth he is the Messiah, this would be very similar to the text in Rev. 13:8 that Jesus was crucified before the foundation of the world, that is, in God&rsquo;s foreordained purpose (see 1 Pet. 1:20). Jesus is indeed prior to Abraham in the resurrection. Job expected to come into existence again in the resurrection (Job 14:14: &ldquo;If a man dies will he live again? I will wait until I begin to exist again,&rdquo;&rdquo;</p> <p>&ldquo;John&rsquo;s gospel has been used to force the rest of the Bible, against the grain of the Scripture taken as a whole, into the later theology of the church councils. John 8:58, for example, has been used to promote the idea, absent from the rest of the New Testament, that Jesus is equal in every sense with God and preexisted as the &ldquo;eternal God the Son.&rdquo;&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; Jesus Was Not a Trinitarian by Anthony Buzzard</p> <p>&ldquo;When Jesus stated &ldquo;I AM,&rdquo; he never alleged he was claiming to be God as so many gleefully attest! No, he stated Abraham was happy to see &ldquo;His DAY&rdquo; and was glad. God, sanctioned Abraham a revelation of the day of the Lord&mdash;the day when Christ would rule in the New Jerusalem on earth. Moreover, when Jesus stated he was before Abraham, he was avowing that he was predestined, and foreordained just as Christians&mdash;the elect, and the church which coexisted in the mind, plan and purpose of God from the beginning!&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; The Tyranny of the Trinity: The Orthodox Cover-Up by P.R. Lackey</p>'),
(342, 1, 43, 9, 9, 1, 'Ego Eimi', 99, '2022-12-10 14:51:18', '<p>The blind man said I AM just as Jesus had said about himself. I don&#39;t see anyone saying that the blind man is God though.</p>'),
