(342, 1, 44, 4, 24, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-19 14:06:43', '<p>&ldquo;Dear brethren, if Peter and John, two of Jesus&rsquo; closest disciples, knew who he was, and made a specific, clear distinction between Jesus and God, why is it not okay for myself and brethren of like-mind to believe the same? I might also add that they appeared to know who created the universe. Moreover, in this prayer to the LORD God, John and Peter knowingly acknowledged that God spoke by the Holy Spirit through David&rsquo;s mouth. Were they referring to a third Person, as opposed to God&rsquo;s own holy spirit&ndash;&ldquo;operational presence, and life force.&rdquo;&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; The Tyranny of the Trinity: The Orthodox Cover-Up by P.R. Lackey</p>'),
