(342, 1, 46, 1, 3, 1, null, 99, '2022-12-11 22:16:58', '<p>&ldquo;Paul is not referring to God as two different persons who each have their own title, but rather he is making a distinction between God (called here the Father) and Jesus (called here the Lord). In this statement only the Father is God.&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; &quot;Sleight Of Mind&quot; - Volume One - The Myth Of The Christian Trinity by Steven Blake<br /> &nbsp;</p>'),
(342, 1, 46, 3, 23, 1, null, 99, '2022-12-11 22:16:00', '<p>&ldquo;&ldquo;Ye are Christ&rsquo;s&rdquo; does not mean that we are Christ, but rather that we belong to Christ. Likewise, &ldquo;Christ is God&rsquo;s&rdquo; does not mean that Christ is God, but rather that Christ belongs to God.&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; &quot;Sleight Of Mind&quot; - Volume One - The Myth Of The Christian Trinity by Steven Blake<br /> &nbsp;</p>'),
(342, 1, 46, 8, 4, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-26 16:39:39', null),
(342, 1, 46, 8, 6, 4, 'For Us', 99, '2023-01-01 12:35:04', '<p>Notice process for us meaning the believers that he was with.</p>'),
(342, 1, 46, 8, 7, 4, null, 99, '2023-01-26 16:40:05', null),
(342, 1, 46, 11, 3, 1, null, 99, '2022-12-11 22:23:32', '<p>&ldquo;Here Paul clarifies that &ldquo;God&rdquo; and &ldquo;Christ&rdquo; are not different titles for the same person, but titles for two different persons-one who is God, and one who is not God.&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; &quot;Sleight Of Mind&quot; - Volume One - The Myth Of The Christian Trinity by Steven Blake<br /> &nbsp;</p>'),
(342, 1, 46, 11, 30, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-23 15:42:09', null),
(342, 1, 46, 15, 2, 1, 'Employ the brains God gave us', 99, '2023-01-27 16:10:04', '<p>&ldquo;When people don&rsquo;t employ the brains God gave them, they can all too easily be led into subscribing to what someone else deems as truth. They cease to be free agents of God and become property of a biased man-made theology. Jesus is very specific in Scripture regarding truth, and our responsibility to seek it out.&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; The Tyranny of the Trinity: The Orthodox Cover-Up by P.R. Lackey</p>'),
(342, 1, 46, 15, 6, 1, 'Dead Christians', 99, '2023-01-27 14:19:11', '<p>The Apostle Paul clearly believed that Christians that had died were dead.</p> <p>see 1 Corinthians 15:51-52</p>'),
