(342, 1, 54, 2, 4, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-08 03:14:10', '<p>&ldquo;There are many laypersons who protest that no one can really know the truth, but they did not arrive at this conclusion by studying the Holy Bible, becausein addition to the aforementioned Scriptures, 1 Timothy 2:3-5 states: &ldquo;&hellip;God our Savior, who wants all men to be saved and to come to a knowledge of the truth. For there is one God and one mediator between God and men, the man Christ Jesus, who gave himself as a ransom for all men&mdash;the testimony given in its proper time.&rdquo;&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; The Tyranny of the Trinity: The Orthodox Cover-Up by P.R. Lackey</p>'),
(342, 1, 54, 2, 5, 1, null, 99, '2022-11-22 15:54:47', null),
(342, 1, 54, 3, 16, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-04 18:22:23', '<p>&ldquo;Another example of a text which was altered is 1 Timothy 3:16. This verse reads in the KJV: &ldquo;God was manifested in the flesh.&rdquo; Modern versions have corrected the word &ldquo;God&rdquo; to &ldquo;He who.&rdquo; The alteration of an original &ldquo;He who&rdquo; (in Greek Oj) was very sneakily accomplished when some scribes changed the O (omicron) into a q (theta) giving qj (theta sigma). The reading THS was an abbreviated form of the Greek word theos, God. All that had to be done was to draw a little line across the middle of the O to produce the Greek letter theta (q). Then the text was made to sound Trinitarian and to support the Incarnation: &ldquo;God was manifested in the flesh.&rdquo; &ldquo;He who&rdquo; (Oj) was made to read &ldquo;God&rdquo; (qj).&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; Jesus Was Not a Trinitarian by Anthony Buzzard</p>'),
