(342, 1, 55, 4, 3, 1, 'End Time Delusion', 99, '2022-12-10 15:15:56', '<p>&ldquo;When it comes to popular prophetic theories, is it possible a large portion of Christianity is now in the midst of another outage&mdash;a truth outage?&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; End Time Delusions by Steve Wohlberg</p> <p>Delusion (noun):<br /> &nbsp;1. A misleading of the mind.<br /> 2. False belief; a fixed misconception.<br /> 3. Something which one accepts as true or real but which is actually false or unreal. Webster&rsquo;s New Collegiate Dictionary<br /> G. &amp; C. Merriam Co. (1953)</p> <p>myths</p> <p>μύθους (mythous)</p> <p>An idle tale, fable, fanciful story. Perhaps from the same as mueo; a tale, i.e. Fiction</p>'),
