(342, 1, 58, 1, 8, 0, 'O God', 99, '2023-02-08 15:16:01', '<p>Most Trinitarians say that God is the speaker in Psalm 45:6, and the verse should be translated as, &ldquo;Your throne, O God, is forever and ever.&rdquo; In doing that they assert that God (assumed to be the Father) is addressing the Messiah and referring to him as &ldquo;God&rdquo; (assumed to be &ldquo;God the Son&rdquo;). But that interpretation does not fit the theology of the Old Testament or the Bible as a whole, and it does not fit the internal evidence in the psalm itself.</p> <p>commentary at Psalm 45</p>'),
