(342, 1, 62, 2, 18, 1, 'Antichrist', 99, '2022-12-29 23:31:15', '<p>&ldquo;The word &ldquo;antichrist,&rdquo; or &ldquo;antichrists,&rdquo; is found only five times in Scripture, and all of these references are in two small books right before the Book of Revelation. The two little books are 1st and 2nd John. The exact verses are 1 John 2:18, 22; 4:3; and 2 John 7.&rdquo;</p> <p>1 John 2:18&mdash;The early Christians had heard that antichrist<br /> &nbsp;was coming.<br /> 1 John 2:18&mdash;Even now there are many antichrists.<br /> 1 John 2:18&mdash;This is evidence that the last time has come.<br /> 1 John 2:19&mdash;These many antichrists &ldquo;went out from us.&rdquo;<br /> 1 John 2:22&mdash;Anyone who denies the Father and the Son is antichrist.<br /> 1 John 2:26&mdash;These antichrists are trying to seduce us away<br /> &nbsp;from Jesus Christ.<br /> 1 John 4:3&mdash;There is a spirit of antichrist.<br /> 1 John 4:3&mdash;The spirit of antichrist denies Jesus Christ has come in the flesh.<br /> 1 John 4:3&mdash;The spirit of antichrist is already in the world.<br /> 1 John 4:4&mdash;True Christians must overcome every form of antichrist.<br /> 1 John 4:6&mdash;The spirit of antichrist is the spirit of error.<br /> 2 John 7&mdash;There are many deceivers and antichrists in the world.<br /> 2 John 9&mdash;To overcome these antichrists, Christians must<br /> abide in the doctrine of Christ.</p> <p>In reality, they all refer to seductive and deceiving elements which are here now and which true Christians must face and overcome.</p> <p>&mdash; End Time Delusions by Steve Wohlberg<br /> &nbsp;</p>'),
(342, 1, 62, 2, 22, 1, null, 99, '2022-12-29 23:25:39', null),
(342, 1, 62, 2, 26, 1, null, 99, '2022-12-29 23:25:42', null),
(342, 1, 62, 2, 28, 1, null, 99, '2023-02-10 23:14:07', '<p>&ldquo;&ldquo;The righteous &lsquo;will be like him when he appears,&rsquo; at his coming, and we shall see Christ &lsquo;as he is&rsquo; (1 John 2:28; 3:2). John would be speaking out of order by looking forward to seeing Christ &lsquo;as he is&rsquo; when he returns yet future, if the righteous dead will have known him in heaven long before his future coming. The saints will be like Christ only when they acquire glorious bodies &lsquo;at the last trump&rsquo; on Resurrection Day (Phil. 3:20-21; 1 Cor. 15:50-55). All who have not thus become &lsquo;like Christ&rsquo; will not attain to the Kingdom (see v. 50). Therefore, nobody could possibly have entered heaven at the time of death but must await entrance into the kingdom yet future when Christ appears on that glorious Day. The popular view of death, judgment, reward and resurrection appears to be hopelessly confused when compared with the lucid texts of Scripture.&rdquo;&mdash;Stan Paher, Focus on the Kingdom, January 2011&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; The Tyranny of the Trinity: The Orthodox Cover-Up by P.R. Lackey</p>'),
(342, 1, 62, 4, 1, 1, null, 99, '2022-12-15 16:42:04', null),
(342, 1, 62, 4, 2, 1, null, 99, '2022-12-15 16:42:36', null),
(342, 1, 62, 4, 3, 1, null, 99, '2022-12-15 16:42:38', null),
(342, 1, 62, 4, 15, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-07 15:00:26', '<p>&ldquo;I confess Jesus to be the Son of God and not the One True God, so why am I being condemned and chastised by my Trinitarian brethren?&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; The Tyranny of the Trinity: The Orthodox Cover-Up by P.R. Lackey<br /> &nbsp;</p>');
INSERT INTO `myrevdata` (`myrevid`, `testament`, `book`, `chapter`, `verse`, `highlight`, `marginnote`, `sqn`, `lastupdate`, `myrevnotes`) VALUES
(342, 1, 62, 5, 7, 3, null, 99, '2023-01-04 18:17:06', null),
(342, 1, 62, 5, 8, 3, 'A forgery', 99, '2023-01-04 18:18:21', '<p>For there are three that bear record in Heaven: the Father, the Word, and the Holy Ghost; and these three are one.</p> <p><br /> &ldquo;The King James Version of the Bible contains a passage in 1 John 5:7 which is now universally recognized as a forgery. It was added to the manuscripts as a Trinitarian proof text and was included almost as an accident in the Authorized Version of 1611. The notes in any modern study Bible will provide the reader with the necessary information about its absence from the original. Bruce Metzger concluded, &ldquo;That these words are spurious and have no right to stand in the New Testament is certain.&rdquo; Another example of a text which was altered is 1 Timothy 3:16. This verse reads in the KJV: &ldquo;God was manifested in the flesh.&rdquo; Modern versions have corrected the word &ldquo;God&rdquo; to &ldquo;He who.&rdquo;&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; Jesus Was Not a Trinitarian by Anthony Buzzard</p>'),
(342, 1, 62, 5, 10, 4, null, 99, '2023-02-05 13:50:43', '<p>&ldquo;Unlike the majority of our clergy who teach that God is a mystery, I believe our God is a knowable God, and it was never His intention to withhold what was necessary for our salvation. If God is a mystery, then we must be reduced to guesswork to gain any knowledge of the one true God. Contrary to what they teach, God is a knowable God and has revealed to us everything we need to know about Him. Be not misled: God made known to us exactly &ldquo;WHO&rdquo; he is and WHO Jesus is. Anyone who tells you otherwise is a liar, because God says they are!&rdquo;</p> <p>The clergy are meant to be our guides and the ones to shepherd us through the truths of Scripture. Why would anyone claiming to be a Christian and to love Jesus Christ feel entitled to call God a liar?</p> <p>&mdash; The Tyranny of the Trinity: The Orthodox Cover-Up by P.R. Lackey<br /> &nbsp;</p>'),
(342, 1, 62, 5, 11, 1, null, 99, '2022-12-13 14:27:40', null),
(342, 1, 62, 5, 12, 1, null, 99, '2022-12-13 14:27:38', null),
(342, 1, 62, 5, 13, 1, null, 99, '2022-12-13 14:27:56', null),
(342, 1, 62, 5, 20, 1, 'The True God', 99, '2023-01-05 12:33:02', '<p>&ldquo;1 John 5:20 (&ldquo; And we are in Him who is true, in His Son Jesus Christ. This is the true God and eternal life&rdquo;) is held by some commentators to be an indication that Jesus is God. Since this would overthrow the unitarian creed of Jesus, many other commentators, both evangelicals and liberals, recognize the reference to &ldquo;the true God&rdquo; as a title for the Father of Jesus. The verse is then an echo of John 17:3 where Jesus carefully distinguishes the &ldquo;only true God&rdquo; (the Father) from himself the Messiah. In 1 John 5:20 we are in Him who is true by being in His Son Jesus Christ. It is the Father who is this one true God, as Jesus had said in John 17:3.&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; Jesus Was Not a Trinitarian by Anthony Buzzard<br /> &nbsp;</p>'),
(342, 1, 65, 1, 7, 1, 'Fire', 99, '2022-12-31 13:58:32', '<p>&ldquo;This is a highly instructive verse in regard to the nature of future punishment, which is not unending torture as taught by some systems. The fire which destroyed Sodom and Gomorrah is not still burning! Nevertheless it was &ldquo;eternal fire.&rdquo; &ldquo;Eternal&rdquo; here as elsewhere means &ldquo;to do with the Age to Come&rdquo; (aionios, as in &ldquo;eternal&rdquo; life = the life of the Age to Come based on Dan. 12:2). The nature of that fire is elsewhere defined as destructive and consuming (cp. Ps. 37:20; Obadiah 16; Mal. 4:3). Its effects are irreversible and the fire is inextinguishable in the sense that nothing will prevent it bringing about its totally consuming effects.&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; The One God, the Father, One Man Messiah Translation: New Testament with Commentary by Anthony Buzzard<br /> &nbsp;</p>'),
(342, 1, 65, 1, 14, 1, null, 99, '2022-12-31 13:40:08', null),
(342, 1, 65, 1, 15, 1, null, 99, '2022-12-31 13:40:10', null),
(342, 1, 65, 1, 24, 1, null, 99, '2022-12-31 13:41:58', null),
(342, 1, 65, 1, 25, 1, null, 99, '2022-12-31 13:42:00', null),
(342, 1, 66, 1, 1, 0, null, 99, '2023-01-11 00:13:51', '<p>&ldquo;The book of Revelation portrays not the Lamb of God coming to take away the sins of the world but the Lion of Judah coming to judge the world.&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; The Tyranny of the Trinity: The Orthodox Cover-Up by P.R. Lackey<br /> &nbsp;</p>'),
(342, 1, 66, 1, 5, 1, null, 99, '2022-11-25 13:14:08', null),
(342, 1, 66, 1, 17, 1, 'The first and the last', 99, '2023-02-03 13:26:52', '<p>God is also said to be the first and the last in Isaiah. But He is careful to say that he is the only God there too.</p> <p>Isaiah 44:6, 8: &ldquo;Thus says the Lord, the King of Israel and his redeemer, the Lord of hosts; &lsquo;I am the first and I am the last, and there is no God besides Me&hellip;Do not tremble and do not be afraid; have I not long since announced it to you and declared it? And you are my witnesses. Is there any God besides Me, or is there any other rock? I know of none.&rdquo;</p>'),
(342, 1, 66, 2, 18, 1, 'The Son of God, not God the Son', 99, '2023-01-10 17:36:46', '<p>The Son of God is described in heaven with God the Father. Please note that he is not called God the Son!</p>'),
(342, 1, 66, 3, 9, 1, 'We are worshipped', 99, '2022-12-27 15:27:48', '<p>God had a unique, virginally conceived Son, the Messiah, and God&rsquo;s spirit is the Spirit of God, His divine presence and power active in the world to enlighten and save. But God never spoke to His own Spirit and the Spirit never sent greetings, was never worshipped nor prayed to.<br /> Both the Father and the Son are addressed in prayer and both are worshipped, Jesus as the Messiah and the Father as the one true God. The biblical word &ldquo;worship&rdquo; is an &ldquo;elastic&rdquo; term with a meaning different from our English word &ldquo;worship.&rdquo; David was &ldquo;worshipped&rdquo; alongside the One God (1Chron. 29:20) and the saints are going to be &ldquo;worshipped&rdquo; by their former persecutors (Rev. 3:9). The Hebrew and Greek words for &ldquo;worship&rdquo; apply both to God and to persons who are not the One God, but superior human agents of the One God.</p> <p>October 1999 issue of Focus on the Kingdom</p>'),
(342, 1, 66, 5, 10, 4, null, 99, '2023-01-28 16:17:27', null),
(342, 1, 66, 5, 13, 1, null, 99, '2023-02-07 11:39:46', null),
(342, 1, 66, 5, 14, 1, 'Jesus worshipped', 99, '2023-02-07 12:38:12', '<p>It is clear why people fell down and worshiped Jesus while he walked the earth and performed great miracles: people loved him and respected him greatly. It is also clear why we are to worship him now&mdash;he has earned our love and our highest reverence. He died to set us free, and God has honored him by seating him at His own right hand above all other powers and authorities. Just because we worship God and worship Jesus, does that mean they are the same or receive the same worship? No, it does not. We reserve a special place in our hearts for God, for Jesus, and frankly, for those other people who deserve our &ldquo;worship&rdquo; in the biblical sense of the word.<br /> From the commentary at Matt 4:10</p>'),
(342, 1, 66, 12, 9, 4, 'The Trinitarian Deception', 99, '2023-01-15 13:42:22', '<p>&ldquo;In the skewed logic of trinitarianism, God the Son is really two incompatible opposites thrown together into a bipolar Jesus who is both mortal and immortal, both man and God, and therefore both mortal man and immortal God. Anyone who can believe this twisted and contradictory doctrine will not find it hard to believe any error that comes along his way. It must have taken an impressive power of persuasion to pull off this deception, not just on a few individuals but on great multitudes throughout church history. This causes one to wonder if the persuasiveness of the deception comes from some supernatural force. We are reminded of the words in Revelation: &ldquo;that ancient serpent, who is called the devil and Satan, the deceiver of the whole world&rdquo; (Rev. 12:9). What it means is that no one, no matter how intelligent or educated, can escape from the paralyzing grip of spiritual deception. Spiritual perception, on the other hand, involves &ldquo;having the eyes of your hearts enlightened&rdquo; by God (Eph. 1:18), enabling the heart to see the liberating light of His truth. The second person of the Trinity&mdash;the one who supposedly died on the cross&mdash;clearly cannot be God who in Scripture is most definitely immortal. That being the case, who exactly is this God called the second person of the Trinity? And who have trinitarians been worshipping ever since their dogma became the official doctrine of the church in the fourth century? This question is becoming ever more frightening.&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; The Only Perfect Man: The Glory of God in the Face of Jesus Christ by Eric H.H. Chang, Bentley C.F. Chan</p>'),
(342, 1, 66, 17, 5, 1, 'Mystery', 99, '2022-11-30 14:05:15', '<p>&ldquo;The last book in the New Testament is titled &ldquo;Revelation&rdquo;. As you might guess, it purports to present information about the future, as revealed to mankind by God. The seventeenth chapter speaks of a &ldquo;great harlot: Babylon&rdquo;, commonly understood to be a metaphor for the location of the origination of all Satanically-orchestrated false religious teachings and beliefs. The meaning of the prophecy has been the source of endless speculation and difference of opinion. As yet, no single interpretation prevails, but many believe that the harlot spoken of here symbolizes false Christianity-a world-wide counterfeit of true, Bible-based, Christianity-designed by Satan to deceive those seeking to follow Jesus, the anointed King who Biblical prophecy tells us that God would raise up, empower and send to represent Himself and to rescue mankind from the penalty of their rebellion.&rdquo;</p> <p>&ldquo;Revelation tells us that the Harlot will be recognizable by a certain word written on her forehead. Care to hazard a wild guess as to what that word might be? (No cheating, now) . . . Give up? Here, let me quote the verse for you: &ldquo;And upon her forehead was a name written: &lsquo;Mystery&rsquo;&hellip;&ldquo;-Re 17: 5.&rdquo;</p> <p>Non-Trinitarian Christianity objects to the Doctrine of the Trinity upon the basis of its confusing, illogical, self-contradictory and irrational composition. Trinitarian Christianity attempts to dismiss these objections by obscuring them within a misrepresentation of the meaning of the term &ldquo;mystery&rdquo; - asserting that the Trinity is not intended to be comprehended, but merely accepted. Despite this attempt, the objections raised by Non-Trinitarianism remain entirely legitimate. God is, indeed, not the author of confusion, and the Trinity-Doctrine is the very epitome of confusion. It is entirely out of character for the Bible to offer such an incomprehensible explanation of God&#39;s being, and the simple and provable fact is that not only does the Bible never do so, but the intelligible statements that it does make regarding God&#39;s identity utterly contradict the Trinity-Doctrine&#39;s representation of Him.</p> <p>&mdash; &quot;Sleight Of Mind&quot; - Volume One - The Myth Of The Christian Trinity by Steven Blake<br /> &nbsp;</p>'),
(342, 1, 66, 21, 4, 1, 'Death eliminated', 99, '2022-12-15 13:22:21', '<p>&ldquo;Conditionalism argues that only the righteous will receive the gift of eternal life, while the wicked will be annihilated after judgement. This means that the devil, his angels, sin, evil, and the wicked will cease to exist in God&rsquo;s eternal kingdom. As the fire of hell eliminates sin, it will also eliminate death since the final result of sin is death (Rom 6:23). Therefore, in Conditionalism, Revelation 21:4 (&ldquo; He will wipe away every tear from their eyes. There will be no more death or mourning or crying or pain, for the old order of things has passed away&rdquo;) will be fulfilled literally&ndash;death will be eliminated. God&rsquo;s victory over death is total and complete&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; Conditional Immortality: The Case for Orthodoxy on the Doctrine of Annihilationism by Tanwin Tanoto<br /> &nbsp;</p>'),
(342, 1, 66, 21, 8, 1, 'Second Death', 99, '2022-12-15 11:58:03', '<p>The Bible has many verses that say the wicked will be destroyed and perish. Some only go so far as to say the wicked will be thrown into the fire, but Revelation 20:14lets us know that the Lake of Fire is the &ldquo;second death.&rdquo; People thrown into the fire die, they do not repent and then get saved. The clear meaning of the Bible should not be distorted or twisted to say that unsaved people will not perish, they will indeed perish (cp. Job 20:8-9; 27:8; Ps. 1:6; 9:7; 37:9-10, 20; 52:5; 73:17-19; 92:7; 145:20; Prov. 10:25; 11:7; 13:13; Isa. 41:11; Ezek. 18:4, 20; 33:13-16; Nah. 1:10; Mal. 4:1-3; Matt. 3:12; 5:29; 7:13, 19; 10:38; 13:40-42; 18:8-9; 25:41, 46; John 15:6; 2 Thess. 1:9; 2 Pet. 2:6; Rev. 20:15; 21:8). Even Romans 6:23 is pointless if no one ever dies forever. Why say the wages of sin is death if in fact everyone is saved and lives? That would make Romans 6:23 a lie, and it&rsquo;s not a lie, it&rsquo;s the truth.</p> <p>-From this commentary: Rom 6:23-</p>'),
(342, 1, 66, 22, 16, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-09 11:43:42', null),
(342, 1, 66, 22, 18, 4, 'Adding to Scripture', 99, '2023-01-08 13:47:14', '<p>&ldquo;As I previously pointed out, one fellow student asked me: &ldquo;What is your point?&rdquo; Well, dear reader, this is exactly my point. No one&mdash;absolutely no one&mdash;has the right to read into Scripture things that are definitely not there. In theological terminology this is called eisegesis (basically one&rsquo;s opinion).&rdquo;</p> <p>&mdash; The Tyranny of the Trinity: The Orthodox Cover-Up by P.R. Lackey<br /> &nbsp;</p>'),
(342, 1, 66, 22, 19, 4, null, 99, '2023-01-08 13:47:34', null),
(343, 0, 19, 5, 11, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-03 13:13:25', null),
(343, 0, 19, 12, 7, 0, null, 99, '2023-01-03 13:28:14', '<p>Psalm 12:7 reminds me of the Book of Acts where Peter speaks of this wicked generation. Need to find this.</p>'),
(343, 0, 19, 12, 8, 1, null, 99, '2023-01-03 13:38:33', '<p>Psalm 12:8 This is certainly prevalent in our culture today. The vileness of homosexuality and how the media is propounding this error is evident everywhere: books, magazines, TV commercials, movies, the vice president (a Roman Catholic) stands by silently as his president Obama declares homosexual couples can legally be married. This same politician, who is now president, stands by silently as HR ++++ accuses any person who verbally or in writing opposes homosexual marriage of being a homophobe and is guilty of hate crime punishable by fine, job loss, etc. Evil is clearly exalted in a godless society with no moral compass.</p>');
