(374, 1, 45, 2, 13, 2, 'Commentary suggests people after Christ can be saved by their works &ndash;', 99, '2023-01-07 19:42:12', '<p>It suggests that there are people who didn&rsquo;t hear about Christ but may have lived a loving life, doing the &ldquo;law&rdquo; without actually knowing the law and even though the law was fulfilled when Christ died.</p> <p>Makes sense the people before Christ will be judged but those after Christ died and resurrected, not so much. It bears the questions:</p> <p>Why then would Christ be needed if everyone still has the chance to be saved by how they live?</p> <p>Why does God say he would have that all men come unto a knowledge of the truth?</p>'),
